He was awarded a posthumous Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , which was awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .

He was a recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross , awarded to recognize extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership by Nazi Germany during World War II .

Manoj Punjabi ( born December 7 , 1972 in Jakarta ) is an Indian Indonesian film and television producer and owner of the biggest production house in Indonesia .
Raul Santoserpa ( born March 1939 in Las Villas , Cuba ) is a Cuban artist specializing in painting and engraving .
Gosse Ludigman ( elected 989 died in 1000 ) was the sixth potestaat ( or elected governor ) of Friesland , now a province of the Netherlands .
Pavel Tichý ( Czech pronunciation : ( ˈpavɛl ˈcɪxiː ) ; 18 February 1936 Brno , Czechoslovakia -- 26 October 1994 Dunedin , New Zealand ) was a Czech logician , philosopher and mathematician .
İbrahim Peçevi or Peçuyli İbrahim Efendi ( 1572 - -1650 ) ( Ottoman Turkish : پچوى إبراهىم افندى ) ( In Bosnia known as `` Ibrahim Alajbegović Pečevija '' ) was an Ottoman Bosnian historian ( chronicler ) of the Ottoman Empire .
Major General Ashraf Rashid ( Punjabi , Urdu : أشرف رشيد‎ ) ( May 23 , 1948 -- October 2 , 2004 ) was a two - star general in the Pakistan Army and the colonel commandant of the Special Service Group division within the Pakistan Army from October 1995 to September 1999 .
Eréndira Ibarra ( born September 25 , 1985 , Mexico City , Mexico ) , is a Mexican actress .
Tommaso Allan hails from a rugby family ; his Scottish father William Allan and his Italian mother Paola Berlato both played in Italy , while his uncle John Allan earned 9 caps for Scotland .

Dr. Datta Walvekar ( 30 March 1928 in Belgaon , India -- 16 March 2010 in Pune ) was an Indian Marathi singer and Music Director
Finn Helgesen ( 25 April 1919 -- 3 September 2011 ) was a speed skater from Norway .
Essie Summers ( born Ethel Snelson Summers on 24 July 1912 in Christchurch , New Zealand -- d. 27 August 1998 ) was a New Zealand author who wrote so vividly of the people and landscape of her native country that she was offered The Order of the British Empire for her contributions to New Zealand tourism .
Abdón Saavedra Mallea ( 1872 , La Paz -- 1942 ) served as Vice President of Bolivia from 1926 to 1930 , during the presidency of Hernando Siles Reyes .

Aaron Webster ( June 1959 - November 17 , 2001 ) was a gay man living in Vancouver , British Columbia , Canada , who was beaten by a group of men close to a gay cruising area in a woody part of Stanley Park near Second Beach on November 17 , 2001 .
Virgil Popescu , also known as Stanislav Popesku , ( born 1916 ) was a Romanian footballer and later coach .
Ben Offereins ( born 12 March 1986 ) is an Australian track & field athlete .
Carola Josefine Sundström Lindberg , ( born 6 September 1976 ) in Upplands Väsby is a Swedish television host , author and singer .
Sarah Hadland ( born 20 February 1971 ) is an English actress who is most notable for her role as Stevie in the BBC television series Miranda and her work with David Mitchell and Robert Webb .
Svend Bayer ( born 2 January 1946 in Uganda to Danish parents ) is a studio potter described by Michael Cardew as `` easily my best pupil . ''
Markus Weise ( born 19 December 1962 ) is a German field hockey coach .
Philippe Joubert ( born 5 June 1954 , in Saint - Etienne , France ) , is a French Brazilian business executive focused on building sustainability into the heart of business strategies to enable long - term growth .
Rolf Pfeifer ( born 1947 ) was professor of computer science at the Department of Informatics University of Zurich , and director of the Artificial Intelligence Laboratory , where he retired from in 2014 .
Mauro Vigorito ( born 22 May 1990 ) is an Italian professional football player currently playing for Vicenza .
Berit Nesheim ( born 28 January 1945 ) is Norwegian film director .
William K. Brehm ( born 1929 ) is a United States businessman who served as Assistant Secretary of the Army ( Manpower and Reserve Affairs ) from 1968 to 1970 , Assistant Secretary of Defense for Manpower and Reserve Affairs from 1973 to 1976 and Assistant Secretary of Defense for Legislative Affairs from 1976 to 1977 .

Bengt Saltin ( 3 June 1935 -- 12 September 2014 ) was a Swedish professor of sports science and exercise physiology , who spent parts of his career in Denmark .
Leo Hilokoski ( born 1941 Helsinki ) is a Finnish bowler .
Daniel Kox ( born 4 February 1952 , Brussels ) is a Belgian cartoonist and comics artist , best known for his comics series Agent 212 .
Luke O'Farrell ( born 25 February 1990 ) is an Irish hurler who plays as a right corner - forward for the Cork senior team .
Juraj Herz ( born 4 September 1934 ) is a Czech film director , actor , and scenic designer , born in Slovakia .
John Douglas Thompson ( born 1964 ) is an Obie Award - winning Canadian - American actor who has been described as `` one of the most compelling classical stage actors of his generation . ''
Darren Varley ( 1973 - -1999 ) was a man from Alberta , Canada who died after a scuffle with police in a jail cell in Alberta after he was arrested for drunkenness .
Stanley Falkow , PhD , ( born 1934 in Albany , New York ) is microbiologist and a professor of microbiology and immunology at Stanford University School of Medicine .
Christian Palin ( born 1 . February 1978 ) is the former lead singer of the neo - classical metal band Adagio .
Tural Jalilov ( Azerbaijani : Tural Cəlilov , born 28 November 1986 ) is an Azerbaijani professional footballer , who plays for Khazar Lankaran .
David Mark Richardson ( born 16 June 1958 ) is a South African ecologist , particularly known for his work on invasive species , especially invasive trees and shrubs .
Maurice FitzGerald , 9th Duke of Leinster ( born 7 April 1948 ) , styled Earl of Offaly before 1976 and Marquess of Kildare between 1976 and 2004 , is an Irish nobleman and landscape designer .
Amy Plum ( born 1967 ) is an American and French young - adult fiction writer , best known for her Die for Me series .
Marshall James ( born 4 October 1970 ) is a former professional darts player from Wales , whose only high - profile success in the game so far was being runner - up in the 1997 BDO World Championship , in his debut year at the championships .
Martina Grimaldi ( born 28 September 1988 ) is an Italian distance swimmer .
Professor Alastair Buchan ( born 16 October 1955 ) is a neurologist and researcher in stroke medicine .
Argelia Velez - Rodriguez ( born 1936 ) is a Cuban - American mathematician and educator .
Philippe Liégeois is a Belgian comic book artist , born on 8 July 1947 .
Mehdi El Ghazouani ( Arabic : المهدي الغزواني‎ , born 1 January 1976 ) is a retired Moroccan long jumper .

Beth Lygoe ( born 17 September 1981 ) is a British born Saint Lucian sailor .
Xaviera Hollander ( born 15 June 1943 ) is a former call girl , madam , and memoirist .
Rob du Bois ( 28 May 1934 -- 28 August 2013 ) was a Dutch composer , pianist , and jurist .
Adolphe Deitte ( 1879 - -1949 ) was a French colonial administrator ; from 1928 until 1929 he was lieutenant governor of Chad .
Gertrud Elisabeth Forsselius ( Forsell ) , later Elisabet Haeffner and Elisabet Fahlgren , ( 23 January 1771 -- 15 February 1850 ) , was a Swedish opera singer and actor , married to the German - born Swedish composer Johann Christian Friedrich Haeffner , and the actor and singer Johan Jacob Fahlgren .
Tor Håkon Holte ( born 1 August 1958 ) is a Norwegian cross country skier who competed from 1982 to 1987 .
Claude Lajeunesse ( born 1941 ) is a Canadian who is the president and chief executive officer of the Aerospace Industries Association of Canada , appointed to that post on Nov. 30 , 2007 .
Fred Barakat ( from Union City , New Jersey , April 8 , 1939-June 21 , 2010 ) was an American college basketball coach and Assistant Commissioner of the Atlantic Coast Conference .
John Laughland ( born 6 September 1963 ) is a British eurosceptic conservative journalist , academic and author who writes on international affairs and political philosophy .
Günther Matzinger ( born 16 May 1987 ) is an Austrian track and field athlete who competes in disability athletics in the T46 category .
John Rentoul ( born 1958 ) is a British journalist who has been the chief political commentator for The Independent on Sunday since February 2004 , and is seen as a `` Labour - leaning journalist '' .
Hirsch Lehren , also known as Tsebi Hirsch Lehren ( April 1784 , The Hague - September 1853 , Amsterdam ) was a Dutch Jewish merchant and community worker .
Jevgeņijs Miļevskis ( born 15 August 1961 ) is a former Latvian football striker of Jewish origin , together with Aleksandrs Starkovs he was the main goal scoring force of FK Daugava Rīga .
Elizabeth of York , Duchess of Suffolk ( 22 April 1444 -- c. 1503 ) was the sixth child and third daughter of Richard Plantagenet , 3rd Duke of York and Cecily Neville .

Aaron Payne ( born 18 November 1982 ) is an Australian rugby league player .

Besarion Udessiani , known as Besso Udessiani ( born Tbilisi , 14 March 1978 ) is a Georgian rugby union player .
James G. Evans ( born in New York City , September 1809 ) was an American artist most famous for painting the `` Celebration Of Washington 's Birthday at Malta On Board The USS Constitution , Commodore Jesse D. Elliott , 1837 '' now in the collection of the U.S. Naval Academy Museum .
Justus Köhncke ( born 1966 in Gießen ) is a German techno producer and pop musician from Cologne .

Rajacenna van Dam , who works under the name Rajacenna , ( born 24 January 1993 , Vlaardingen , Zuid Holland , Netherlands ) is a Dutch hyperrealistic pencil drawing artist .
Dewey Sullivan ( May 6 , 1935 -- November 8 , 2006 ) was an American high school football coach who coached more than 40 years at Dayton High School in Dayton , Oregon .
Mary Jemison ( Deh - he - wä - mis ) ( 1743 -- September 19 , 1833 ) was an American frontierswoman who was adopted in her teens by the Seneca .

Ayodele Aladefa ( born 29 December 1970 ) is a Nigerian former long jumper .

Jay Schellen ( born 20 May 1960 , Albuquerque , New Mexico ) is a U.S. drummer who is best known as a member of the hard - rock band Hurricane .

Dr Ra'anan Cohen ( Hebrew : רענן כהן‎ , born 28 February 1941 ) is a former Israeli politician who served as a government minister during the early 2000s .

Cecilia Ferrazzi ( 1609 -- 17 January 1684 ) was a Counter - Reformation Catholic prototype social worker , whose life was extensively involved with establishment and maintenance of women 's houses of refuge in seventeenth century Italy .
Simon May ( born 15 August 1944 ) is a British musician and composer , best known for composing some of British television 's best known theme tunes , including EastEnders and Howards ' Way , and for composing the music for the 1988 film The Dawning .
Younes Ali Rahmati ( Persian : یونس‌علی رحمتی‎‎ ; born 3 January 1983 ) is an Iranian - Qatari footballer .

Michael Ciaran Parker ( born 4 May 1952 ) , better known by his stage name Michael Barrymore , is an English comedian and television presenter of game shows and light entertainment programmes on British television in the 1980s , 1990s and 2000s .
Asawari Joshi ( born 6 May 1965 ) is a popular Indian actress .
Michael Glatthaar ( born 3 May 1953 ) is a German scholar of the Middle Ages , specializing in the documents of the Carolingians and the study of Saint Boniface .

Miles Martindale ( 1756 - -1824 ) was an English Wesleyan minister .
Robert Morham ( 31 March 1839 -- 5 June 1912 ) was the City Architect for Edinburgh for the last decades of the nineteenth century and was responsible for much of the `` public face '' of the city at the time .
Gérald Bastard ( born 3 April 1950 in Paris ) is a highly cited French physicist known for his work on semiconductor heterostructures .
Maria Temryukovna ( Мари́я Темрюко́вна , c. 1544 -- 1 September 1569 ) was a Circassian Tsaritsa of the Tsardom of Russia and second wife to Ivan IV of Russia .
Peter Wegner ( born in 1932 ) is an American computer scientist who has made significant contributions to both the theory of object - oriented programming during the 1980s and to the relevance of Church - Turing thesis for empirical aspects of computer science during the 1990s and present .
Richard of Salerno ( c. 1060 -- 1114 ) , who is not to be confused with his homonym cousin Richard of Hauteville , was a participant in the First Crusade and regent of the County of Edessa from 1104 to 1108 .
Geneviève Prémoy , alias Chevalier Balthazard ( 1660 - 1706 ) , was a French officer .
Eli Lancman ( Hebrew : אלי לנצמן ; born 1936 ) is a Jewish - Israeli historian of Japanese and East Asian art . Developer and director of the Tikotin Museum of Japanese Art in Haifa from 1966 to 1992 , and one of the founders of the Israel - Japan Friendship Society .
Hermann Haupt ( 24 January 1873 , Langensalza , Unstrut - Hainich , Thuringia -- 2 June 1959 , Halle , Saxony - Anhalt ) was a German entomologist who worked mainly on Auchenorrhyncha and Hymenoptera .
David - John Newman ( born 1956 ) is an artist and photographer who now lives in Wales .

Tony Kirkham ( born 30 August 1957 ) is the head Arboretum at Royal Botanic Gardens , Kew , where he has worked since 1978 .
Charles Killick Millard ( 1870 - -1952 ) was a British doctor who in 1935 founded the Voluntary Euthanasia Legalisation Society ( now Dignity in Dying ) , a movement that campaigned for the legalisation of euthanasia in Great Britain .
Edwin Brooks ( born 1 December 1929 ) is a British - born , Australia - resident academic who has been a Member of Parliament ( MP ) in England and a local politician both in England and in Australia .

William Clarence John McCarver , better known as Jack McCarver ( born 19 December 1896 Fort Worth , Texas , died 21 June 1959 , Waco , Texas ) was an American racecar driver .
Peter Gormley ( c. 1920 -- 8 May 1998 ) was an Australian born artist manager who guided the early careers of many recording artists , including Frank Ifield , Cliff Richard , The Shadows , Marvin Welch & Farrar , Labi Siffre and Olivia Newton - John .
Sir Justin Hickey JP ( 5 April 1920 -- 21 August 2005 ) was an Australian businessman , insurance executive and philanthropist .
Major General Sir Luke O'Connor VC , KCB ( 20 January 1831 -- 1 February 1915 ) was a British soldier from Ireland .
Rodrigo Álvarez ( Latin : Rudericus Aluari ) ( died 1187 ) was a Galician magnate in the Kingdom of León .
Karel Richard Richter ( 29 January 1912 -- 10 December 1941 ) was a German spy who was executed by hanging at Wandsworth Prison .
Hela Yungst ( January 15 , 1950 in Israel -- February 24 , 2002 in Livingston , New Jersey ) , also known as Hela Young , was an American television entertainer and beauty pageant winner .
George Cary Eggleston ( 26 November 1839 -- 14 April 1911 ) American author and brother of fellow author Edward Eggleston ( 1837 - -1902 ) .
Abraham Regelson ( 1896 - -1981 ; Hebrew : אברהם רגלסון ) was an Israeli Hebrew poet , author , children 's author , translator , and editor .
Eustace de Vesci ( 1169 - -1216 ) was an English lord of Alnwick Castle , and a Magna Carta surety .
Edith Gittins ( 1845 -- 1910 ) was an artist and social reformer , actively involved in promoting women 's rights .
Sir Eoin Higgins ( 14 June 1927 -- 2 September 1993 ) , known as `` The Honourable Mr. Justice Higgins '' , was a judge of the High Court of Northern Ireland .
Per Olof Hulth ( 2 June 1943 -- 26 February 2015 ) was a Swedish astroparticle physicist .
Clinton H. Stagg ( November 1888 -- 3 May 1916 ) was an American screenwriter , journalist , and author .
Vladimir Golschmann ( 16 December 1893 -- 1 March 1972 ) was a French - American conductor .
Howard Wright Cutler ( 1883 - 1948 ) was an American architect known primarily for his designs of churches , schools and public buildings in Washington , D.C. and adjacent Montgomery County , Maryland .
The Very Rev Thomas Hayley was the Dean of Chichester from 1735 to 1739 .
Gladys Reynell ( 1881 - -1956 ) was one of South Australia 's earliest potters and is known for her bold modernist style and her preference for working with native clays .
Beata Elisabet von Königsmarck ( 1637 - 1723 ) , was a Swedish countess and landowner .
William Hampson ( born 14 March 1854 in Bebington , Merseyside ( formerly : Cheshire ) , England -- died 1 January 1926 in Holland Park , London , England ) was the first person to patent a process for liquifying air .
Vong Savang ( Lao : ເຈົ້າຟ້າຊາຍມົງກຸດລາຊະກຸມານວົງສະຫວ່າງ ; 27 September 1931 -- 2 May 1978 ) was the Crown Prince to throne of the Kingdom of Laos .
Hafizullah Amin ( Persian : حفيظ الله امين‎‎ born 1 August 1929 -- 27 December 1979 ) was an Afghan politician and statesman during the Cold War .
Wilhelm Sebastian von Belling ( 15 February 1719 -- 28 November 1779 ) was a Prussian Hussar general under Frederick the Great .
Cornelius Bayley ( 1751 - -1812 ) , was an English Anglican cleric .
Samuel Albas ( 1697 -- 1749 ) was a rabbi in Fes , Morocco .
Annibale Fagnola ( 1866 - -1939 ) was one of the greatest Italian violin makers of the 20th century .
Abram Lyle ( 14 December 1820 -- 30 April 1891 ) is noted for founding the sugar refiners Abram Lyle & Sons which merged with the company of his rival Henry Tate to become Tate & Lyle in 1921 .
Nikolaos Vlachopoulos ( Greek : Νικόλαος Βλαχόπουλος , 1868 - -1957 ) was a Greek Army officer who rose to the rank of Lieutenant General .
Jean Gallon ( 25 June 1878 - 23 June 1959 ) was a French composer , choir conductor , and music educator .
Shlomo Rosen ( Hebrew : שלמה רוזן‎ , born 21 June 1905 , died 7 December 1985 ) was an Israeli politician and minister .
Trevor Stubley RP RBA RSW RWS ( 27 March 1932 , Leeds -- 8 January 2010 , Holmfirth ) was a Yorkshire portrait and landscape painter , and illustrator .
Thomas Turner à Beckett ( 13 September 1808 -- 1 July 1892 ) was a lawyer and politician in colonial Victoria ( Australia ) , member of the Victorian Legislative Council .
Foster Hedley ( 6 January 1908 -- 1983 ) was an English professional footballer who played for St Andrews ( Newcastle ) , South Shields , Corinthians ( Newcastle ) , Jarrow , Hull City , Nelson , Manchester City , Chester City , Tottenham Hotspur , Millwall and Swindon Town .
Edwin Ashby ( 2 November 1861 -- 8 January 1941 ) was an Adelaide based Australian property developer and a noted malacologist interested in chitons and ornithologist .
Sir Harry George Champion CIE ( 17 August 1891 -- 20 June 1979 ) was a forest officer in British India who created a classification of the forest types of India and Burma .
Er . Rachpal Singh Gill ( 3 April 1908- 10 August 2001 ) was a Sikh Indian civil engineer responsible for key engineering projects such as the Bhakra Nangal hydro power complex , Ranjit Sagar Dam , Pong Dam , and the thermal power plants at Bathinda as well as Roopnagar .
Asbjørn Aavik ( November 30 , 1902 -- November 20 , 1997 ) was a Norwegian Lutheran missionary to China and writer .
Pieter Philips Jurriaan Quint Ondaatje ( Colombo , 1758 -- Amsterdam , 18 April 1818 ) was a Dutch patriot and politician .
Jean - Marie - Raphaël Le Jeune ( born Jean - Marie , 12 April 1855 -- 21 November 1930 ) was a Canadian Roman Catholic priest , linguist , author , and newspaper publisher .
Carol Truax ( 3 October 1899 -- June 1986 ) was an American music administrator and an author of many cookbooks .
Ove Rode ( 31 August 1867 -- 11 July 1933 ) was a Danish politician , newspaper editor and Minister of Interior Affairs for Det Radikale Venstre .
Giovanni Francesco Fara ( February 4 , 1543 - 1591 ) was a Sardinian historian , geographer and clergyman , who wrote in Latin .
Vaughan Cornish ( 22 December 1862 - 1 May 1948 ) was an English geographer .
General Sir Robert Sloper KB ( 8 May 1729 -- 18 August 1802 ) was Commander - in - Chief , India .
The 6th Jebtsundamba Khutughtu ( 1842 - -1848 ) , was the sixth incarnation of the Jebtsundamba Khutuktu , the spiritual heads of the Gelug lineage of Tibetan Buddhism in Mongolia , and the fourth of Tibetan descent .
Thomas Harlan Ellett ( September 2 , 1880 -- 1951 ) was an architect who practiced in New York City .
Charles H. Yale ( 1856 - 1920 ) was an American theatre producer and performer .
Ovida , Obida or Odiva ( died December 9 , 480 ) was a general during the late Western Roman Empire and the last Roman ruler of Dalmatia .
Nathaniel Choate ( 1899 - 1965 ) was an American painter and sculptor who served as vice president of the National Sculpture Society .
Peter Durber ( 1873 - -1963 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Glossop North End and Stoke .
Cosme San Martín Lagunas ( 27 September 1849/1850 , Valparaíso - 1 April 1906 , Santiago ) was a Chilean painter and the first Director of the `` Academia de Pintura '' who was born in Chile .
John Bulbeck ( christened 30 December 1818 -- 1888 ) was an English cricketer .
Mohammad Tahir Vahid Qazvini ( Persian : محمد طاهر وحید قزوینی‎ , died 1699 ) , was a Iranian nobleman , who served as the vizier of the Safavid king ( shah ) Suleiman I ( r. 1666 - -1694 ) and the latter 's son Sultan Husayn ( r. 1694 - -1722 ) from 1691 to 1699 .
Raimundo Diosdado Caballero ( June 19 , 1740 - January 16 , 1830 or April 28 , 1829 ) was a Catholic miscellaneous writer , chiefly ecclesiastical .
Sir James Macdonald , 2nd Baronet , GCMG ( 14 February 1784 -- 29 June 1832 ) was a British politician .
Michael Dekel ( Hebrew : מיכאל דקל‎ , bhorn 1 August 1920 , died 20 September 1994 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Likud between 1977 and 1988 .
Stevie Hyper D ( born Stephen Austin , 20 September 1967 -- 5 July 1998 ) was a drum and bass MC .
Joseph Chayyim ben Isaac Selig Caro ( 1800 - -April 21 , 1895 , Włocławek , Russian Empire , now Poland ) was a German - Russian rabbi .
Dwijendranath Tagore ( Bengali : দ্বিজেন্দ্রনাথ ঠাকুর ) ( 11 March 1840 -- 19 January 1926 ) was an Indian poet , song composer , philosopher , mathematician , and a pioneer in Bengali shorthand and musical notations .
Hubert David Bentliff ( 28 May 1891 - 21 April 1953 ) was a British lawyer , civil servant , and politician .
Fran Roš ( pronounced ( ˈfɾaːn ˈɾoːʃ ) , 14 January 1898 -- 22 August 1976 ) was a Slovene writer , poet , and playwright .
Antoinette de Bourbon ( 25 December 1493 -- 22 January 1583 ) was a French noblewoman of the House of Bourbon .
Valentine Dale ( died 1589 ) was an English jurist and diplomat .
John Baildon ( 11 December 1772 -- 7 August 1846 ) was a Scottish pioneer in metallurgy in continental Europe .
Nicol Hugh Baird ( 26 August 1796 -- 18 October 1849 ) was a Scottish surveyor who worked for his uncle Charles Baird in St Petersburg for several years , and emigrated to Canada in 1828 .
George Matthew Snelson ( 22 November 1837 -- 31 October 1901 ) was the first Mayor of Palmerston North and is considered Palmerston North 's founding father .
Sir Nicholas Hyde ( c.1572 -- 25 August 1631 ) was Lord Chief Justice of England .
Hamzah Fansuri ( also spelled Hamzah Pansuri , d. c. 1590 ) was a Sumatran Sufi writer , the first known to pen mystical panentheistic ideas in the Malay language .
Jørgen Brunchorst ( 10 August 1862 -- 19 May 1917 ) was a Norwegian natural scientist , politician and diplomat .
Abdul Quadir ( 1 June 1906 -- 19 December 1984 ) was a Bangladeshi poet , essayist , and journalist .
Sir Anthony Mildmay ( died 1617 ) was a country gentleman from Northamptonshire , England , who served as Member of Parliament for Wiltshire from 1584 to 1586 and as English ambassador in Paris in 1597 .
Régis François Gignoux ( 1816 - -1882 ) was a French painter who was active in the United States from 1840 to 1870 .
Namık İsmail ( 1890 , Samsun - 30 August 1935 , Istanbul ) was a Turkish Impressionist painter and art educator , who received his training in France .
James M. Hare ( July 31 , 1910 -- March 10 , 1980 ) was the Michigan Secretary of State .
Thomas Edwardston ( died 1396 ) , was an Augustinian friar .
George James Anderson ( 1860 -- 15 December 1935 ) was a Reform Party Member of Parliament , and a minister in the Reform Government from 1912 to 1928 .
Mary Grey , Countess of Kent ( died 1 November 1702 ) , suo jure 1st Baroness Lucas of Crudwell ( née Mary Lucas ) , was an English peeress in her own right .
Jack Goldswain ( 22 July 1878 -- 5 November 1954 ) was a British boxer who won the English & Imperial ten stone title in 1906 and fought for the British welterweight title in 1910 .
George Herrick ( c. 1658 - -1695 ) was the `` Marshal '' for the Court of Oyer and Terminer during the Salem Witch Trials .
Edward Webster Bemis ( 7 April 1860 Springfield , Massachusetts -- 25 September 1930 ) was a United States economist and a public utility expert .
Sahir Ludhianvi is the pen name of Abdul Hayee ( 8 March 1921 -- 25 October 1980 ) who is popularly known as Sahir .
Vince Lascheid ( 26 December 1923 - 19 March 2009 ) was a prominent Pittsburgh organist , best known as the organist for the Pittsburgh Pirates from the 1960s to 2009 and from 1970 - 2003 the Pittsburgh Penguins .
Gordon Green ( 28 February 1890 -- 30 May 1973 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Donald Dinnie ( 1837 - -1916 ) was a Scottish strongman , born at Balnacraig , Birse , near Aboyne , Aberdeenshire .
Armand Philippon ( 27 August 1761 -- 4 May 1836 ) , sometimes called Philippon , was a French soldier during the French Revolution and the subsequent First French Empire .
James Charles Armytage ( 1802 or c. 1820 -- 28 April 1897 ) was an English engraver of the 19th century .
Alick Nkhata ( 1922 - -1978 ) was a popular Zambian musician and broadcaster in the 1950s through to the mid-1970s .
John Cazenove ( 1788 - -1879 ) was an English businessman and political economist .
John Bayliss ( 1919 - -2008 ) was a British poet and significant literary editor of the World War II period ; later in life a civil servant .
Simon Gunton ( 1609 - 1676 ) was an English clergyman and antiquary .
David Thompson Seymour ( 5 November 1831 -- 31 January 1916 ) , soldier and police commissioner , was born on 5 November 1831 at Ballymore Castle , County Galway , Ireland , son of Thomas Seymour , gentleman , and his wife Matilda Margaret , née Lawrence .
Padraig O'Keeffe ( Irish : Pádraig Ó Caoimh ) ( 1887 -- 1963 ) was a noted Irish traditional musician .
Arthur James Mason DD ( 4 May 1851 -- 24 April 1928 ) was an English clergyman , theologian and classical scholar .
Charles Julian Tennyson ( 1915 - -1945 ) was an English writer and historian most famous for his writings on his home county of Suffolk .
Henry Christian Timm ( July 11 , 1811 -- September 5 , 1892 ) was a German - born American pianist , conductor , and composer .
George Coke ( or Cooke ) ( 3 October 1570 -- 10 December 1646 ) was successively the Bishop of Bristol and Hereford .
Jakob Altenberg ( 1875 - -1944 ) was an Austrian businessman and picture frame dealer .
Sir Christopher Nugent , 6th ( or 14th ) Baron Delvin ( 1544 - -1602 ) was an Anglo - Irish nobleman and writer .
Fredrik Waldemar Bergroth ( 14 May 1852 , Humppila - 4 October 1928 ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman and politician .
Frank Pierce Milburn ( 1868 - -1926 ) was a prolific architect of the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Branislav Petronijević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Бранислав Петронијевић ; 6 April 1875 -- 4 March 1954 ) was a Serbian philosopher and scientist ( paleontologist ) who wrote books primarily in three languages , Serbian , German and French fluently .
Giovanni da Oriolo ( active 1439 ; died by 1474 ) was an Italian painter of the Quattrocento , active in Northern Italy , including Faenza .
Harry Raymond Eastlack , Jr. ( 1933 - -1973 ) suffered from fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva ( FOP ) , a rare and poorly understood disease in which the bone repair mechanism runs out of control , turning other tissue like muscles and tendons into bone .
Edwin Waterhouse ( 4 June 1841 -- 17 September 1917 ) was an English accountant .
Virginia Mariani , born Virginia Barlocci Ricardi , ( 1824 - -1898 ) was an Italian painter , active in Rome .
Charles William Bell ( 25 April 1876 -- 8 February 1938 ) was a Canadian playwright , lawyer and politician , born in Hamilton , Ontario .
Mary Dixon Jones ( 1828 - -1908 ) is known for being the first American physician to propose and perform a total hysterectomy to treat a tumor in the uterine muscle ( myoma ) .
Yoseph ben Ab - Hisda ben Yaacov ben Aaharon ; ( 1919 -- February 14 , 1998 ) , served as the Samaritan High Priest from January 26 , 1987 until his death .
André de Foix , Lord of Lesparre ( or Asparroz or Asparrots ) , ( 1490 -- 1547 ) was a French General .
Avraham Botzer ( Hebrew : אברהם בוצר ; 25 July 1929 -- 2 June 2012 ) was the Commander of the Israeli Navy between 1968 and 1972 .
Carolina Flores - Trinidad or Lina Flor ( died 1976 ) was a writer from the Philippines .
George Lambert , 2nd Viscount Lambert , TD ( 27 November 1909 -- 24 May 1989 ) was a British politician .
Benning Wentworth ( 24 July 1696 -- 14 October 1770 ) was the colonial governor of New Hampshire from 1741 to 1766 .
Arthur Ernest Guedel ( 1883 - -1956 ) was an American anesthesiologist .
Virginia Proctor Powell Florence ( October 1 , 1897 -- 1991 ) was a trailblazer in both African - American history and the history of librarianship .
Henry Thomas Alken ( 12 October 1785 -- 7 April 1851 ) was an English painter and engraver chiefly known as a caricaturist and illustrator of sporting subjects and coaching scenes .
František Šafránek ( 2 January 1931 in Praha - 27 June 1987 ) was a Czech football player .
Alan of Galloway ( before 1199 -- 1234 ) , also known as Alan fitz Roland , was a leading thirteenth - century Scottish magnate .
Robert Bree , MD ( 1759 - -1839 ) was an English physician .
Subhani ba Yunus ( 1931 - -2006 ; born in Aurangabad , British India ) was an accomplished Pakistani actor and television and radio personality whose distinct voice quality earned him a special place in Radio Pakistan .
Vinod Johri ( 10 June 1935 -- 10 May 2014 ) was an Indian astrophysicist .
Harold Thomas Henry Carter ( 15/28 September 1903 , Baku -- 16 November 1944 , Hollywood , Los Angeles , California ) , aka Boake Carter , was an American national news commentator in the 1930s and early 1940s .
William Edward Nairn ( 1812 -- 9 July 1869 ) was an English - born politician in Australia , president of the Tasmanian Legislative Council .
Robert Burnet , Lord Crimond ( 1592 -- 24 August 1661 ) was a Scottish advocate and judge .
Robert Steere ( 1833 - -1910 ) was a latter 19th century pioneer in California , nine years after U.S. statehood .
Martin Sigvart Grytbak ( 6 November 1883 -- 24 June 1953 ) was Norwegian born , American engineer Martin Sigvart Grytbak was born in Nedre Stjørdal in Nord - Trøndelag , Norway .
Pierre - François Brice ( 26 November 1714 ( baptised ) -- 13 May 1794 ) was a French artist who spent most of his career in what is now Belgium .
Florence Camm ( 1874 -- 1960 ) was an English stained glass designer , painter and decorative metalworker .
Jack Geggie ( 29 October 1881 -- 20 January 1973 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Essendon and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Alessandro Trentacinque ( also known as Alessandro Trentacinque d'Aquila , Alexander Trentacinquis , and Alexander Trentacinquius , 1541 - 1599 ) , was a jurist , writer and patrician from L'Aquila , Italy .
Barré Lyndon ( pseudonym of Alfred Edgar ) ( 12 August 1896 -- 23 October 1972 ) was a British playwright and screenwriter .
Alan Shulman ( 4 June 1915 -- 10 July 2002 ) was an American composer and cellist .
John Herne ( c.1593 - -1649 ) was an English barrister , involved in high - profile trials of the 1630s and 1640s .
Yidnekachew Tessema ( 1921 - 1987 ) was one of the Ethiopia 's top sport 's journalists , covering Olympic Games , and World Cups and served his country in the capacities of secretary of the soccer and sport federation , president of national Olympics committee and commissioner of Sport federation .
Stephen Fox - Strangways , 1st Earl of Ilchester PC ( 12 September 1704 -- 26 September 1776 ) was a British peer and Member of Parliament .
André van Gyseghem ( 18 August 1906 -- 13 October 1979 ) was an English actor and theatre director who also appeared in many British television programmes .
Küçük Hüseyin Pasha ( 1757 -- 7 December 1803 ) , also known as Tayazade Damat Küçük Hüseyin Pasha , was a Ottoman statesman and admiral who was Kapudan Pasha ( Grand Admiral of the Ottoman Navy ) from 11 March 1792 to 7 December 1803 .
Charles Louis Gabriel ( 25 June 1857 -- 10 February 1927 ) was an Australian photographer and medical practitioner .
Zofia Atteslander ( born March 12 , 1874 in Luborzyca , died c. 1928 in Berlin ) was a Polish painter , active between 1889 - 1928 in inter alia Berlin , Paris and Wiesbaden .
Daniel Legrand ( 1783 -- 16 March 1859 ) was a Swiss industrialist and philanthropist of the Reformed Church who spent most of his life in Alsace , France .
Edward Newman Fuller ( 1888 - -1969 ) was an English sportsman who played rugby union at an international level , touring Argentina with the 1910 Combined British rugby union side , an early incarnation of the British and Irish Lions .
Sir Thomas Frederick Lister CBE ( 1886/87 ? -- 13 March 1966 ) was the first chairman of the British Legion .
Leo Daft ( 1843 -- 1922 ) was an English professor and builder of early American urban railroads .
Charles Exshaw ( died 1771 ) was an Irish painter and engraver .
Gertrude Samuels ( 1910 - 2003 ) was a photojournalist and later a member of the editorial board of the New York Times .
Antonio María Martínez ( ? --1823 ) was a colonel in the infantry regiment of Zamora and the last governor of Spanish Texas .
Paskal Mitrevski ( Macedonian : Паскал Митревски ) ( 1912 - -1978 ) , also known as Paskal Mitrovski or Paschalis Mitropoulos , was a Greek - born communist partisan from the Greek province of Macedonia ( Aegean Macedonian ) and former President of the Macedonian National Liberation Front .
Seán Thomas ( died 24 June 1999 ) was an Irish football manager .
Otto Lington ( 5 August 1903 - 15 December 1992 ) was a Danish composer , bandleader and violinist .
Rudolf Kattnigg ( 9 April 1895 , in Carinthia -- 2 September 1955 , in Klagenfurt ) was an Austrian composer , pianist and conductor .
Rafael Ríos Rey ( 28 July 1911 - April 1980 ) was a Puerto Rican muralist .
Rudolf Mentzel PhD ( 28 April 1900 -- 5 December 1987 ) was a German chemist and a National Socialist science policy - maker .
Reginald Brabazon , 12th Earl of Meath , KP , GCVO , GBE , PC ( Ire ) ( 31 July 1841 -- 11 October 1929 ) was a British politician and philanthropist .
Gus McLaren died in Merimbula on the 29th of August 2008 .
Ernst David Bergmann ( Hebrew : ארנסט דוד ברגמן‎ ; 1903 -- April 6 , 1975 ) was an Israeli nuclear scientist and chemist .
Richard Stafford ( c1755 -- 1808 ) was a land speculator and pioneer of Hampshire County , West Virginia .
Leonard Pagliero OBE ( 22 August 1913 -- 8 August 2008 ) was Director of the Stationers Association and Chairman of The Kennel Club .
Sonam Tsemo ( tib . : bsod nams rtse mo ; 1142 - -1182 ) ( or Lobpon Sonam Tsemo ) , an important Tibetan sprititual leader and Buddhist scholar , was the second of the so - called Five Venerable Supreme Sakya Masters of Tibet , the founding fathers of the Sakya - tradition .
John Hay , 1st Lord Hay of Yester ( c. 1450 -- after October 1508 ) is the ancestor of the Marquesses of Tweeddale .
Abd al - Razzaq al - Dandashi ( Arabic : عبدالرزاق الرستم الدندشي‎ ; 1899 - -1935 ) was a Syrian intellectual and Arab nationalist activist .
A solitary personality but a talent fully acknowledged by critics and cherished by art lovers , Victor - Ferdinand Bourgeois died at Dieulefit on 6 October 1957 .
Elfrida Vipont was the pen name of Elfrida Vipont ( Brown ) Foulds ( 3 July 1902 -- 14 March 1992 ) , a British author of children 's books .
Eysteinn Erlendsson ( Modern Norwegian Øystein Erlendsson , Latin Augustinus Nidrosiensis ) ( died 26 January 1188 ) was Archbishop of Nidaros from 1161 to his death in 1188 .
Val McCalla ( 3 October 1943 in Kingston , Jamaica -- 22 August 2002 in Seaford , East Sussex ) is best known as the founder of The Voice , a British weekly newspaper aimed at the Britain 's black community .
Eugene Garin ( 1922 - -1994 ) was a contemporary seascape artist .
John Campbell , 2nd Marquess of Breadalbane KT , PC , FRS ( 26 October 1796 -- 8 November 1862 ) , styled Lord Glenorchy until 1831 and as Earl of Ormelie from 1831 to 1834 , was a Scottish nobleman and Liberal politician .
Frederick Southgate Taylor ( December 16 , 1847 - -February 16 , 1896 ) , was a businessman , politician , philanthropist , and founder of Pi Beta Phi fraternity .
Tunku Tan Sri Abdullah ibni Almarhum Tuanku Abdul Rahman ( 2 May 1925 -- 20 August 2008 ) was a Malaysian businessmen and a founder of the Melewar Corporation .
The `` Baroness de Calabrella '' ( c. 1788 -- 6 October 1856 , Paris ) , born Catherine Ball , was an English socialite , journalist , and writer .
William Edward Kilburn ( 1818 - 1891 ) was an English photographer , noted for his pictures of the British Royal family .
Colonel James Givins ( sometimes James Givens ) ( circa 1759 -- March 5 , 1846 ) was a British Army officer and militiaman who fought in the American Revolution and the War of 1812 .
Elisha Beman ( 1760 -- 14 October 1821 ) was a businessman involved in settlement and the trade derived from that endeavour .
Kong Yingda ( Chinese : 孔穎達 ; Wade -- Giles : K'ung Ying - ta ; 574 -- 648 ) , courtesy names Chongyuan ( 冲遠 ) and Zhongda ( 仲達 ) , was a Sui and Tang dynasty Confucianist , who is considered one of the most influential Confucian scholars in Chinese history .
Hörður Barðdal ( Hordur Barddal ) ( 22 May 1946 , Reykjavík -- 4 August 2009 ) was a competitive water polo player , competitive swimmer , competitive skier , competitive golfer , and a disabled athlete activist .
John Anthony Parsons ( 20 February 1938 -- 26 April 2004 ) was a British sports journalist and author .
Sir Edward Mansel , 4th Baronet ( ca . October 1637 -- 14 November 1706 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons in three periods between 1660 and 1689 .
Nelly Mazloum ( 9 June 1929 - 21 February 2003 ) , an Egyptian of Italian and Greek origin , was an actress , choreographer , dancer , and teacher of ballet , modern dance , Egyptian folkloric dance , traditional oriental dance and the creator of the oriental dance technique .
Herbert Denman ( born in Brooklyn , N. Y. , June 20 , 1855 - died 1903 in Idyllwild , California ) was a figure - painter .
Izaak van Oosten , Isaak van Oosten or Isaac van Oosten ( sometimes even : ' Izaak van Costen ' ) ( 10 December 1613 -- December 1661 ) was a Flemish Baroque landscape and cabinet painter .
Nathaniel Kolawole Onadipe ( 14 July 1922 -- 4 December 1988 ) , most commonly known as Kola Onadipe , was a Nigerian author best known for his children 's books .
Christian Friedrich Weber ( 1764 - -1831 ) was a German New Testament scholar of the Tübingen school .
Prince Adam Zygmunt Sapieha ( 2 May 1892 - 20 October 1970 ) was a military aviator and cavalry officer in the Polish Army .
Omar Pkhakadze ( Georgian : ომარ ფხაკაძე , Russian : Омар Пхакадзе ; 8 December 1944 -- 21 May 1993 ) was a Georgian sprint cyclist .
William Willoughby , 5th Baron Willoughby de Eresby KG ( c.1370 -- 4 December 1409 ) was an English baron .
Erik Amundsen ( 1 February 1937 -- 22 February 2015 ) was a Norwegian jazz musician ( upright bass ) from Oslo .
King Yeongyang of Goguryeo ( died 618 ) ( r. 590 - -618 ) was the 26th king of Goguryeo , the northernmost of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .
Víctor Ramón Navarro Serrano , under the alias of Megateo , ( 25 January 1976 -- 2 October 2015 ) was a Colombian guerrilla , narcotics dealer , and criminal .
John Basil Boothroyd ( 4 March 1910 -- 27 February 1988 ) was an English humorous writer , best known for his long association with Punch .
Sir Thomas Pelham , 2nd Baronet ( September 1597 -- 1654 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons of England variously between 1621 and 1654 .
Carl Emmermann ( 6 March 1915 -- 25 March 1990 ) was a German U - boat commander during World War II . In his time as commander , he succeeded in sinking 27 ships for a total tonnage of 152,080 gross register tons ( GRT ) .
Çapanzade or Çapanoğlu Agah Efendi ( 1832 - -1885 ) was an Ottoman writer and newspaper editor who , along with his colleague İbrahim Şinasi , published Tercüman - ı Ahvâl ( `` Interpreter of Events '' ) , the first private newspaper by Turkish journalists , and introduced postage stamps to the Ottoman Empire .
Ivan Radunsky ( 1872 -- 1955 ) played the part of Bim in the clown duo of Bim Bom .
Dade Moeller ( 27 February 1927 -- 26 September 2011 ) was an internationally known expert in radiation safety and environmental protection .
Malhar Rao Gaekwad ( 1831 - -1882 ) was the Maharaja of Baroda ( r.1870 - 19 April 1875 ) .
John Brynteson ( August 13 , 1871 , Ärtemark -- 1959 ) was one of the `` Three Lucky Swedes '' who founded and developed the Nome mining district .
Günther Anhalt ( 23 January 1906 -- 27 April 1945 ) was a high - ranking German officer in the Waffen - SS ( military wing of the Schutzstaffel ) during World War II .
Major Edmund Leopold de Rothschild , CBE , TD ( 2 January 1916 -- 17 January 2009 ) was an English financier , a member of the prominent Rothschild banking family of England , and a recipient of the Victoria Medal of Honour ( VMH ) , given by the Royal Horticultural Society .
Antônio Maria de Araújo Morais known as Antônio Maria ( Recife , 17 March 1921 - Copacabana , 15 October 1964 ) , was a Brazilian writer of pop music lyrics as well as radio sports commentator , poet , composer , and chronicler .
Nuchhungi Renthlei ( 1 January 1914 - 1 January 2002 ) was an Indian poet , singer and school teacher , known for her poems written in Mizo language .
Israel Roll ( 1937 - June 2010 ) was an Israeli archaeologist and academic .
Heinz Dörmer ( 1912 - -2001 ) was a German man who was imprisoned by the Nazis for homosexuality under Paragraph 175 .
Peter Pye ( 1902 -- 3 September 1966 ) , Dr Edward Arthur ( Peter ) Pye .
Edward Woolsey Bacon ( 1843 -- June 1887 ) was an American Congregational clergyman , as well as a sailor and a soldier .
Countess Palatine Ernestine of Sulzbach ( 15 May 1697 -- 14 April 1775 ) was the wife of Landgrave William `` the Younger '' of Hesse - Wanfried and after his death prioress of the Carmelite monastery in Neuburg an der Donau as Sister Augusta .
Alfred Wallis ( 18 August 1855 -- 29 August 1942 ) was a Cornish fisherman and artist .
Grenville Booth ( born 2 April 1925 - May 1990 ) is a former English footballer .
Cleofonte Campanini ( 1 September 1860 -- 19 December 1919 ) was an Italian Conductor .
Gusztáv Gegus ( 5 October 1855 - 19 February 1933 ) was a Hungarian politician and jurist , who served as Minister of Justice for several days in 1906 .
Einarr Rognvaldarson often referred to by his byname Torf - Einarr ( sometimes anglicised as Turf - Einarr ) , ( fl . early 890s -- c . 910 ) was one of the Norse Earls of Orkney .
Thomas Fisher Morgan ( 1908 -- 18 January 1959 ) was a Welsh singer and actor best remembered as a principal bass - baritone with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company during the 1950s .
Odda of Deerhurst ( before 993 -- 31 August 1056 ) was an Anglo - Saxon nobleman active in the period from 1013 onwards .
James Stanhope , 1st Earl Stanhope PC ( c. 1673 -- 5 February 1721 ) was a British statesman and soldier who effectively served as Chief Minister between 1717 and 1721 .
Lars Jørgen Madsen ( 19 July 1871 -- 1 April 1925 ) was a Danish rifle shooter who competed in the early 20th century in rifle shooting .
Frances Morrell ( née Frances Maine Galleway ; 28 December 1937 -- 10 January 2010 ) was a British Labour politician who led the Inner London Education Authority 1983 - -87 .
Manuel Lepe Macedo ( April 17 , 1936 in Puerto Vallarta , Jalisco -- September 9 , 1984 in Guadalajara , Jalisco ) Manuel Lepe was a Mexican artist who painted in a Naïve style , painting mostly themes based on the landscape and townscape of his native Puerto Vallarta .
John Tudor Gwynn ( 13 November 1881 in Ramelton , County Donegal , Ireland -- 17 May 1956 in Bangor , County Down , Northern Ireland ) was an Irish cricketer .
Jacob Wackernagel ( also Jakob ; 11 December 1853 -- 22 May 1938 ) was a Swiss linguist , Indo - Europeanist and scholar of Sanskrit .
John de Courcy Ireland ( 19 October 1911 -- 4 April 2006 ) was an Irish maritime historian and political activist .
Sreedharan Nair ( 11 September 1922 -- 19 October 1986 ) , popularly known as Kottarakkara Sreedharan Nair or just Kottarakkara , was an Indian film actor in Malayalam movies .
Louis Niesten ( 1844 -- 1920 ) was a Belgian astronomer working at the Brussels Royal Observatory .
Ömer Diler ( 1945 , Istanbul -- 18 March 2005 , Istanbul ) was a Turkish numismatist specializing in Islamic coins .
Anastasios Christodoulou died from cancer at the General Hospital , Milton Keynes , on 20 May 2002 .
Sigismund Casimir , Crown Prince of Poland ( Polish : Zygmunt Kazimierz Waza ) , ( 1 April 1640 -- 9 August 1647 ) - was the only legitimate son of King Władysław IV and his first wife Queen Cecilia Renata .
Milan Kangrga ( 1 May 1923 -- 25 April 2008 ) was a Croatian and Yugoslav philosopher who was one of the leading thinkers in the Praxis school of thought which originated in the 1960s in the Socialist Federal Republic of Yugoslavia .
Harry Desmond Briscoe ( 21 June 1925 -- 7 December 2006 ) was an English composer , sound engineer and studio manager .
Charles O. Bick ( 1909 - -1994 ) was the first chairman of the Metropolitan Toronto Board of Police Commissioners , the civilian body which oversaw the Metropolitan Toronto Police Force .
Paskoje Miličević Mihov ( around 1440 -- 1516 ) was a Croatian local builder .
Peter Tsao Kwang - yung , CBE ( 1989 ) ( Chinese : 曹廣榮 ; born 7 October 1933 , Shanghai -- died 6 June 2005 , Thailand ) was a career civil servant of Hong Kong .
Ambrose Corbie , also called Corby or Corbington ( 7 December 1604 -- 11 April 1649 ) was an English Jesuit , teacher and author .
Matthew George Easton ( 1823 - -1894 ) was a Scottish Presbyterian preacher and writer .
Johann Urban ( or Johannes Urban , 7 June 1863 -- 13 November 1940 ) was an Austrian chemist and industrialist .
Domhnall Ballach , also known as Donald Balloch MacDonald ( d. c. 1476 ) was a son of Iain Mòr Tànaiste MacDhòmhnaill and Margaret Bisset , daughter of MacEoin Bisset , Lord of The Glens .
John Houlding ( 1833 - -1902 ) was an English businessman , most notable for being Lord Mayor of Liverpool , and the founder of Liverpool Football Club .
Sir Thomas Joshua Platt KC ( 1788 or 1790 -- 1862 ) was a British judge who served as a Baron of the Exchequer .
Wajih ad - Din Mas'ud ( died 1344 ) was the leader of the Sarbadars of Sabzewar from 1338 - 1343 until his death .
Jorge Salazar Argüello ( 1939 -- 1980 ) , a Nicaraguan coffee grower and popular leader of UPANIC ( Union of Agricultural Producers of Nicaragua - Unión de Productores Agropecuarios de Nicaragua ) , seemed poised to become the leader of the opposition to the Sandinista government , until his death at the hands of State Security forces .
Shahbaz Khan Kamboh ( 1529 -- 11 November 1599 ) was one of the generals of Mughal Emperor Akbar .
Gérald Leblanc ( September 25 , 1945 -- May 30 , 2005 ) was an Acadian poet notable for seeking his own Acadian roots and the current voices of Acadian culture .
Joseph Mathen ( 1917 - -1995 ) was a member of the Kerala state Legislative assembly and the Rajya Sabha ( 1960 - -1966 ) .
Anna Jönsdotter ( 1820 - 1896 ) , known as Kloka Anna i Vallåkra ( Wise Anna of Vallåkra ) or Vallåkraflickan ( The Vallåkra Girl ) , was a Swedish cunning woman and natural healer .
Stafford Heginbotham ( 12 September 1933 -- 21 April 1995 ) was a British businessman and chairman of Bradford City football club at the time of 56 deaths in the Bradford City stadium fire , which occurred immediately after the club won league promotion that mandated a costly upgrading of spectator facilities .
Rev. Eliezer Williams ( baptised 4 October 1754 -- 20 January 1820 ) was a Welsh clergyman and genealogist , who served the Earl of Galloway as a family tutor and genealogical researcher .
Eugene Kleiner ( 12 May 1923 -- 20 November 2003 ) was an Austrian - born American engineer and venture capitalist .
Ioannis Pesmazoglou ( Greek : Ιωάννης Πεσμαζόγλου ; 1857 - -1906 ) was a Greek banker , economist and politician .
Richard Anthony Moore ( 23 January 1914 - 27 January 1995 ) was a lawyer , special counsel to President Richard M. Nixon , communications executive and U.S. Ambassador to Ireland ( 1989 - 1992 ) .
Dhirajlal Mahashankar Vishwanath Thaker ( 1897 - -1947 ) was a British colonial official and Paymaster General of the Port of Karachi ; the largest wheat and cotton exporting port in British India prior to partition , currently the largest port in Pakistan .
Hubert Joseph Walthère Frère - Orban ( 22 April 1812 - 2 January 1896 ) was a Belgian liberal politician and statesman .
William Clifford Massey ( 1917 - -1974 ) was an anthropologist who played a key role in the study of the prehistory of the Baja California Peninsula in Mexico .
Yekaterina von Engelhardt ( Russian : Екатерина Васильевна Энгельгардт ; 1761 - -1829 ) was a Russian lady in waiting and noble .
Frederic Dorr Steele ( 1873 - 1944 ) was an American illustrator best known for his work on the Sherlock Holmes stories .
Francis Cole Lowry Hamilton ( 26 April 1869 in Dublin , Ireland -- 16 December 1936 in Wicklow ) was an Irish cricketer .
Abraham Langford ( 1711 - -1774 ) was an English auctioneer and playwright .
Satish Dhawan ( 25 September 1920 -- 3 January 2002 ) was an Indian aerospace engineer , widely regarded as the father of experimental fluid dynamics research in India .
Sir Frank Douglas MacKinnon ( 11 February 1871 -- 23 January 1946 ) was an English lawyer , judge and writer , the only High Court judge to be appointed during the First Labour Government .
Antoine Aleksander Mirecki ( 13 April 1809 - 18 November 1882 ) , was a Polish violinist .
Francis Hobart Herrick ( 19 November 1858 Woodstock , Vermont - 11 September 1940 Cleveland , Ohio ) was an American writer , natural history illustrator and Professor of Biology at Adelbert College of Western Reserve University .
Isaac Jehner ( 2 December 1750 -- 1818 ) was a painter and engraver who worked in the West Country and London .
Ronald M. Cohen ( December 23 , 1939 , Chicago , Illinois -- April 21 , 1998 , Los Angeles , California ) was a US American screen writer and film producer .
Griffith Bodwrda ( 1621 - -1677 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1656 and 1660 .
Elhadi Adam Elhadi ( Arabic : الهادي آدم الهادي‎ ) , or Al - Hadi Adam Al - Hadi ( 1927 - 30 November 2006 ) , was a Sudanese writer and song writer born in El - Helalelih village , Al Jazirah state in central Sudan on the bank of the Blue Nile .
Cuth Harrison born Thomas Cuthbert Harrison ( 6 July 1906 -- 21 January 1981 ) was a British racing driver from England .
Herman Makkink ( 21 October , 1937 - 20 October 2013 ) was a Dutch sculptor , graphic artist and illustrator .
Kyprian Zochovskyj died on 26 October 1693 and was buried in Polotsk .
Archie Doyle ( died 1980 ) was one of three anti - Treaty members of the IRA who on 10 July 1927 assassinated the Irish Justice Minister Kevin O'Higgins .
Rhoda Boyd Smiley died there in 1823 .
Djadoeg Djajakusuma ( ( dʒaˈdʊʔ dʒajakuˈsuma ) ; 1 August 1918 -- 28 October 1987 ) , generally credited as D. Djajakusuma , was an Indonesian film director and promoter of traditional art forms .
Heinrich Rosenthal ( 7 July ( O.S. 25 June ) 1846 -- 10 May 1916 ) was an Estonian nationalist leader , doctor and author .
Per Brunsvig ( 1917 - -1997 ) was a Norwegian barrister .
Rifat Kukaj ( Serbian Cyrillic : Рифат Кукај ) ( 25 October 1938 -- 11 September 2005 ) was a Kosovar Albanian and the a successful writer in Albanian literature for grown ups and children .
France Avčin ( 6 October 1910 -- 21 February 1984 ) was a Slovene electrical engineer and mountain safety expert and early lobbyist for Environmental protection .
Charles Montague Birch ( 1884 - -1947 ) was a British musical conductor .
Luigi Riccardi ( Lione 1808 - - Milano 1877 ) was an Italian painter .
Anna de Waal ( 25 November 1906 , Culemborg -- 22 March 1981 , Arnhem ) , was a Dutch politician ( Catholic party ) .
Willie Dunn , Sr . ( 19 August 1821 -- 14 February 1878 ) was a Scottish professional golfer who played during the mid - to - late 19th century .
Sir Robert Rankin , 1st Baronet ( 18 October 1877 -- 11 October 1960 ) was a Liverpool shipbuilder , and British Conservative politician , who was elected a Member of Parliament for Liverpool Kirkdale in 1931 until 1945 .
Lieutenant General Julio Canessa Roberts ( 19 March 1925 -- 24 January 2015 ) was a Chilean military and political figure .
Abraham Fleming ( Flemyng ) ( c.1552 - -1607 ) was an English clergyman , and a prolific writer , translator , contributor to others ' texts , editor and poet .
Kazimierz Orlik - Łukoski ( 13 September 1890 -- 1940 ) was a Polish military commander and one of the Generals of the Polish Army murdered by the Soviet Union in the Katyń massacre of 1940 .
Thomas Denne ( 25 January 1808 in England -- 11 August 1876 at Hythe , Kent ) was an English cricketer with amateur status .
Francesco Lambardi ( 1587 - -1642 ) was a Neapolitan Baroque composer who participated in the staging of feste a ballo with Giovanni Maria Trabaci .
Barrington Bourchier ( c 1627 - 29 October 1695 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Ofonius Tigellinus , also known as Tigellinus Ofonius , Ophonius Tigellinus and Sophonius Tigellinus ( c. 10 - -69 ) , was a prefect of the Roman imperial bodyguard , known as the Praetorian Guard , from 62 until 68 , during the reign of emperor Nero .
Increase Nowell , ( 1590 - -1655 ) , was a colonial administrator , original patentee of the Massachusetts Bay Company , founder of Charlestown , Massachusetts , and first ruling elder of the First Church in Charlestown .
Free Frank McWorter ( 1777 - -1854 ) was an American slave who bought his own freedom and in 1836 founded the town of New Philadelphia in Illinois ; he was the first African American to found a town in the United States .
James Glynn ( 1800 - -1871 ) was a U.S. Navy officer who in 1848 distinguished himself by being the first American to negotiate successfully with the Japanese during the `` Closed Country '' period .
Ernesto de Zulueta e Isasi ( Bilbao , 26 April 1892 -- Madrid , 9 September 1969 ) , Spanish Diplomat .
Lord Sydney Godolphin Osborne ( 5 February 1808 -- 9 May 1889 ) was an English cleric , philanthropist and writer .
Walter Goodfellow ( 1866 - -1953 ) was a British zoological collector and ornithologist .
Thomas Lorango , American pianist , was born on June 8 , 1959 in Buffalo , New York ; he died of AIDS on December 30 , 1992 in New York City .
Bedřich Fritta ( 19 September 1906 , Višňová -- 8 November 1944 , Auschwitz ) was a Czech - Jewish artist and cartoonist .
Harry George Woolley ( 4 January 1942 -- 23 May 2009 ) was a Canadian player , coach , referee , manager , scout and advocate for the game of lacrosse .
Sarah Poulton Kalley or Sarah Poulton Wilson ( 25 May 1825 -- 8 August 1907 ) was a British missionary to Brazil who helped create a Portuguese language hymnal still in use today .
Swami Nityaswarupananda ( 1899 - -1992 ) was a monk of Sri Ramakrishna Math . His biography has been written by Dr. Shelly Brown .
James A. Wetmore ( 1863 - 1940 ) was an American lawyer and administrator , best known as the Acting Supervising Architect of the U.S. Office of the Supervising Architect from 1915 through 1933 .
Psamtik I ( also spelled Psammeticus or Psammetichus ; Greek : Ψαμμήτιχος ) ( r. 664 -- 610 BCE ) , was the first of three kings of that name of the Saite , or Twenty - sixth dynasty of Egypt .
Thomas Courtland Manning ( born in Edenton , North Carolina , in 1831 -- died in New York City , 11 October 1887 ) was an American jurist .
Valetta Swann ( 1904 -- 1973 ) was an English painter and sculptor , known for her work related to rural and indigenous life in Mexico and the United States .
Thomas Bell Poole ( 1818 - -1865 ) was under - sheriff of Monterey County , and member of the Knights of the Golden Circle serving as a crewman of the Confederate privateer J. M. Chapman .
Mary Waldegrave , Countess Waldegrave , DBE ( 25 March 1850 -- 8 November 1933 ) was a British peeress .
Ana Livia Cordero ( July 1931 -- 1992 ) was a Puerto Rican doctor and political activist .
Jack Loughnan ( 4 August 1889 -- 19 November 1949 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John David Digues La Touche ( 5 June 1861 Tours -- 6 May 1935 , Majorca ( at sea ) ) was an Irish ornithologist , naturalist , and zoologist .
Czesław Lejewski ( 1913 - -2001 ) was a Polish philosopher and logician , and a member of the Lwow - Warsaw School of Logic .
Pieter Neefs the Younger or Pieter Neeffs the Younger ( bapt . 23 May 1620 - -after 1675 ) was a Flemish painter who specialized in architectural interiors of churches .
Henry Pottinger Stephens , also known as Henry Beauchamp ( 1851 -- 11 February 1903 ) , was an English dramatist and journalist .
John Glendy ( 1755 - -1832 ) was a Scots - Irish Presbyterian clergyman who served as Chaplain of the Senate of the United States .
Seán Cronin ( 29 August 1922 -- 9 March 2011 ) was a journalist and former Irish Army officer and twice Irish Republican Army chief of staff .
Arthur Edward George ( 17 June 1875 -- 8 September 1951 ) was an accomplished sportsman , an aviation pioneer , aircraft designer , racing driver , engineer and businessman .
Hilmar Friedrich Wilhelm Bleyl , known as Fritz Bleyl ( 8 October 1880 -- 19 August 1966 ) , was a German artist of the Expressionist school , and one of the four founders of artist group Die Brücke ( `` The Bridge '' ) .
Pieter van Noort ( 1622 -- 1672 ) was a Dutch painter of still lifes , often featuring fish .
Grigore Alexandru Ghica or Ghika ( 1803 or 1807 -- 24 August 1857 ) was a Prince of Moldavia between 14 October 1849 , and June 1853 , and again between 30 October 1854 , and 3 June 1856 .
Valerio Bona or Buona ( c. 1560 -- c. 1620 ) was an Italian composer of the early Baroque ; he was also a Franciscan friar .
Arthur Baldwinson ( 1908 - 1969 ) was one of Australia 's first generation of prominent modernist architects to experience the European modernist movement first hand .
Randall V. Mills ( 1907 - 1952 ) was an English professor with a variety of interests related to the Pacific Northwest , including steamboats , railroads and folklore .
Henry Matthews , 1st Viscount Llandaff PC , QC ( 13 January 1826 -- 3 April 1913 ) was a British lawyer and Conservative politician .
Henry Glassford Bell ( 5 November 1803 -- 7 January 1874 ) , a Scottish lawyer , poet and historian .
Willem Thibaut , Tybaut , or Tibout ( 1524 - -1597 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Mikel Conrad ( 30 July 1919 -- 11 September 1982 ) was an American actor and film director , writer and producer .
Alfred Bettman ( 1873 -- 1945 ) was one of the key founders of modern urban planning .
Montague Scott ( 1835 -- 15 May 1909 ) , also known as `` Montagu Scott '' and affectionately as `` Monty '' , was an Australian artist of great versatility , who came to be known for his portraits of racehorses .
Marten Waefelaerts ( 1748 - 1799 ) was a Flemish 18th century landscape painter .
Juan Gilberto Funes Baldovino ( 8 March 1963 -- 11 January 1992 ) , nicknamed `` El Búfalo '' ( The Buffalo ) , was an Argentine football player , known for his physical style of play .
David Fisher ( I ) ( 1760 - -1832 ) , was an actor and a theatre manager .
Eric Julius Biörner ( modern Swedish spelling Erik Julius Björner ) was born July 22 , 1696 in the Swedish parish of Timrå in Medelpad and died in 1750 .
Nicholas Netterville , 5th Viscount Netterville ( 1708 - 1750 ) was an Irish peer , who is mainly remembered now for being tried and acquitted by his peers on a charge of murder .
Eske Brun ( 25 May 1904 -- 11 October 1987 ) was a high civil servant in Greenland and in relation to Greenland from 1932 till 1964 .
Karl König ( 25 September 1902 -- 27 March 1966 ) was an Austrian paediatrician who founded the Camphill Movement , an international movement of therapeutic intentional communities for those with special needs or disabilities .
William Simson ( 1798/99 -- 29 August 1847 ) was a Scottish portrait , landscape and subject painter .
John Berkeley , 5th Baron Berkeley of Stratton PC ( 16 May 1697 -- 18 April 1773 ) , styled The Honourable John Berkeley until 1741 , was a British politician , the last of the Bruton branch of the Berkeley family .
Lars Benzon ( 1687 --1742 ) was a landowner and a deputy ( deputeret ) in the commissariat general of the Danish navy .
Johnny Weissmuller , Jr. ( 23 September 1940 -- 27 July 2006 ) was an American actor and longshoreman .
Bill Dodds ( 23 April 1882 -- 4 September 1934 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Roger Jaques ( died 1653 ) was an English merchant and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1640 .
Franz Boluminski ( 12 November 1863 -- 28 April 1913 ) was a German colonial administrator .
Sir Christopher Seton ( 1278 - -1306 ) , also known as Christopher de Seton , was a 13th - century Scottish noble .
Kwasi Boakye ( 24 April 1827 -- 9 June 1904 ) , sometimes archaically spelt as Aquasi Boachi , was a Dutch mining engineer who was born a Prince of the Ashanti Empire .
Bertha van Heukelom ( died 1322 ) , was a Dutch noble , the legendary heroine of the Siege of IJsselstein Castle in 1296 .
William North , 6th Baron North and 2nd Baron Grey ( 22 December 1678 -- 31 October 1734 ) , known as Lord North and Grey , was an English soldier and Jacobite , and a peer for more than forty years .
Marion Coates Hansen , born Marion Coates ( c.1870 -- 2 January 1947 ) , was a feminist and women 's suffrage campaigner , an early member of the militant Women 's Social and Political Union ( WSPU ) and a founder member of the Women 's Freedom League ( WFL ) in 1907 .
Peter de Honestis ( c. 1049 -- 29 March 1119 ) was born at Ravenna .
Charles Cummings ( b. ca . 1870 , Indiana - d. 4 October 1918 , Los Angeles , California ) was an early American actor .
Ceolnoth is also known to have corresponded with Pope Leo IV . Archbishop Ceolnoth died on 4 February 870 .
Charles Bianconi ( 24 September 1786 -- 22 September 1875 ) was an Italo - Irish entrepreneur .
Saint Camillus de Lellis , M.I. , ( 25 May 1550 -- 14 July 1614 ) was an Italian priest who founded a religious Order dedicated to the care of the sick .
Farewell Watts ( 10 March 1904 -- 1970 ) was an English footballer who played as an inside right for Newport County and Tranmere Rovers .
According to the Vita Bonifatii auctore Willibaldo , on the morning of 5 June 754 , Boniface and 50 others , presumably including Eoban ( none of the companions are mentioned by name in the Vita ) , were killed at Dokkum ( The Netherlands ) by pagan Frisians .
Lieutenant General Alexander Duroure ( 1692 -- 1 February 1765 ) was a British Army officer who served as colonel of the 4th ( King 's Own ) Regiment of Foot .
Wensley Pithey ( 21 June 1914 -- 10 November 1993 ) was a South African - born character actor who had a long stage and film career in England .
Benedetto Rusconi , nicknamed the Diana , ( died 1525 ) was an Italian Renaissance painter , a companion of Vittore Carpaccio and Giovanni di Niccolò Mansueti , who lived in the latter part of the 15th and early part of the 16th centuries .
Vivek Shauq ( 21 June 1963 -- 10 January 2011 ) was a noted actor , comedian , writer and singer .
Kazi Golam Mahbub ( 23 December 1927 -- 19 March 2006 ) was a Bangladeshi activist and politician .
John Bascom Wolfe ( 8 July 1904 -- 5 January 1988 ) was an American social and behavioural psychologist best known for his study of the use of a token economy on chimpanzees .
Nikos Stavridis ( Greek : Νίκος Σταυρίδης ; 1910 -- 14 December 1987 ) was a Greek actor in film and theater .
Douglas Edward Hopkins ( born 23 December 1902 , died 1992 ) was a cathedral organist , who served at Peterborough Cathedral and Canterbury Cathedral .
Zsiga Pankotia ( or Pankotai ) was a 31-year - old Hungarian - born murderer who was hanged on Thursday , 29 June 1961 at Armley Gaol , Leeds , West Yorkshire , ( now HM Prison Leeds ) .
Humphrey Nicholls ( 1577 - 1643 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1628 to 1629 .
Ernst Arnold Lyongrün ( 1871 - -1935 ) was a German practitioner of the Jugendstil or Art Nouveau style of decorative arts and a painter in the Impressionistic mode .
Gotthard von Kettler ( also Ketteler , German : Gotthard Kettler , Herzog von Kurland ; 2 February 1517 -- 17 May 1587 ) was the last Master of the Livonian Order and the first Duke of Courland and Semigallia .
Bryant Walker ( 1856 - -1936 ) was an American malacologist who specialized in the non - marine Mollusca .
Michael Mavroudis was a martyr from Granitsa , who died in 1544 .
Emma Barrandeguy ( 8 March 1914 -- 19 December 2006 ) was an Argentine writer , journalist , poet , storyteller and playwright .
Charles Alexander Gunn or Charles A. Gunn ( 1870 - -1945 ) was an American architect active in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Margaret Mortimer , Baroness Berkeley ( 2 May 1304 -- 5 May 1337 ) was the wife of Thomas de Berkeley , 3rd Baron Berkeley .
Charles Golding Barrett ( 5 May 1836 , Colyton , Devon - 11 December 1904 , London ) was an English entomologist who specialised in Lepidoptera .
William John Clappison ( 27 June 1937 - 21 February 2013 ) was an English ceramic and glass designer .
Joseph Franklin Dye ( 1831 - -1891 ) , 49er , miner , teamster , alleged member of the Mason Henry Gang , lawman , rancher and early oilman in Southern California .
Edward Makula ( 4 July 1930 - 15 January 1996 ) was a Polish glider pilot and engineer .
Phillipena ( Ena ) Noël , AOM ( 30 July 1910 to 7 December 2003 ) best known by the name Ena Noël , was an inspirational school teacher and advocate for children 's literature and library services to children and young adults .
Étienne - Hippolyte Godde ( 26 December 1781 -- 1869 ) was a French neoclassic architect .
Nanya ( c.1835 -- 1895 ) was an Australian aboriginal man who founded a family that would be one of the last to live by traditional indigenous means in New South Wales .
Josiah Hardy ( 1715 - -1790 ) was a British merchant and colonial administrator who served as colonial Governor of New Jersey between 1761 and 1763 .
Orestis Laskos ( Greek : Ορέστης Λάσκος ; 11 November 1907 -- 17 October 1992 ) was a Greek film director , screenwriter and actor .
Thomas Hamilton , 6th Earl of Haddington KT FRCPE ( baptised 5 September 1680 -- 29 November 1735 ) was a Scottish politician and nobleman .
Abu'l - Qasim Ubaydallah ibn Abdallah ibn Khordadbeh ( Persian : ابوالقاسم عبیدالله ابن خردادبه‎‎ ) ( c. 820 -- 912 CE ) , better known as Ibn Khordadbeh , was the author of the earliest surviving Arabic book of administrative geography .
Johann Julius Walbaum ( 30 June 1724 , Wolfenbüttel -- 21 August 1799 ) was a physician , naturalist and taxonomist .
Aili Siiskonen ( 9 February 1907 in Mikkeli -- 15 January 1983 ) was a Finnish journalist , civil servant and politician .
Carl Wilhelm Rubenson ( 30 July 1885 -- 29 July 1960 ) was a Swedish - born Norwegian mountaineer and non - fiction writer .
Constance Stokes ( née Parkin , 22 February 1906 -- 14 July 1991 ) was a modernist Australian painter who worked in Victoria .
Franklin L. Sheppard ( 1852 - 1930 ) was a well - known Christian hymn composer who set the poem , This is My Father 's World , to music .
Thomas Jensen ( Copenhagen , 25 October 1898 -- Frederiksberg , 13 November 1963 ) was a Danish orchestra conductor .
George Geary Bennis ( 1790 - -1866 ) was a writer , originally from Limerick in Ireland .
Mina P. Shaughnessy ( 1924 - -1978 ) , born in the mining town of Lead , South Dakota , was a teacher and innovator in the field of basic writing at the City University of New York ( CUNY ) .
Dr. Mohammad Marwan Arafat ( 5 January 1945 -- 12 June 2012 ) was a Syrian footballer , referee , sports analyst , academic lecturer and journalist , well known for being the first Arabic and Asian football referee to be a linesman in a 3rd place Olympic game match ( Moscow 1980 ) .
Arthur Sparke ( 5 June 1628 -- 1677 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
Aryeh Altman ( Hebrew : אריה אלטמן‎ , 6 January 1902 -- 21 August 1982 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Herut and Gahal between 1951 and 1965 .
Jabez Allies ( 22 October 1787 -- 29 January 1856 ) was an English folklorist and antiquarian .
Tito Burns ( 7 February 1921 -- 23 August 2010 ) was a British musician and impresario , who was active in both jazz and rock and roll .
Sir Thomas Willys , 1st Baronet ( c. 1614 -- 17 November 1701 ) of Fen Ditton in Cambridgeshire , was a Member of Parliament for Cambridgeshire and Cambridge .
Edward de Courcy Clarke ( 10 November 1880 -- 30 November 1956 ) , was a teacher , researcher and field geologist , winner of the Clarke Medal in 1954 .
Baro Tumsa ( 1938 - -1978 ) was a pharmacist , lawyer and Oromo nationalist and political activist in Ethiopia .
Thomas Grissell ( 4 October 1801 -- 26 May 1874 ) was an English public works contractor who was responsible for constructing a number of prestigious buildings in England .
Beatrix de Rijke ( 1421 -- 1468 ) , was a Dutch foundling in Dordrecht in 1421 .
Henry Olerich ( 1851 - -1927 ) was a utopian author from Nebraska .
Frank D. Yuengling ( 27 September 1876 - 29 January 1963 ) was an American businessman , the president and owner of the Pottsville , Pennsylvania brewer , Yuengling .
Hermann Josef Fanger ( aka Herman Fanger ) ( 27 Mar 1895 - Aug 1971 ) was a Swiss - born inventor best known for contributions to technologies ranging from the coaxial speaker to sonar .
Richard Molyneux , 1st Viscount Molyneux ( 1594 - -1636 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1628 when he was created a peer .
Pierre Courteys ( d. 1602 ? ) was a French enamel painter , working in Limoges .
Varsken ( Middle Persian : Vazgēn ) , was a Iranian prince from the Mihranid family of Gardman , who served as the viceroy of Gugark from 470 to 482 .
Murad Ashurly ( Azerbaijani : Murad Aşurlu ; born August 31 , 1972 in Baku , Azerbaijani SSR , USSR - 22 October 2014 in Ama Dablam , Nepal ) was an Azerbaijani mountaineer , cousin of the prominent climber Israfil Ashurly .
Nils Carl Gustaf Fersen Gyldenstolpe ( 30 September 1886 - 10 April 1961 ) was a Swedish explorer , zoologist and ornithologist .
Gunnar A. Sjögren ( `` GAS '' , 1920 - -1996 ) was a Swedish engineer who worked for Saab Automobile and the author of The SAAB Way - the first 35 years of Saab cars , 1949 - 1984 .
Magdalena of Sweden ( Swedish : Magdalena Karlsdotter 1445 -- August 1495 ) was a Swedish princess .
Jacob Alting ( 27 September 1618 -- 20 August 1679 ) was a Dutch philologist and theologian .
Charles Patrick Fitzgerald ( better known as C. P. Fitzgerald ) ( 5 March 1902 -- 13 April 1992 ) was a British historian .
Pawlo Humeniuk ( c. 1884 -- January 24 , 1965 ) was a Ukrainian - American fiddler from the early 20th century , one of the biggest stars of the era 's ethnic music .
Pierre Guérin de Montaigu ( died 1230 ) was a nobleman from Auvergne , who became the 13th Grand Master of the Knights Hospitaller , in 1207 - -28 .
Constance of Świdnica ( c. 1313 -- 21 November 1363 ) was a member of the Piast dynasty in the Świdnica - Jawor branch and by marriage Duchess of Głogów .
First Lieutenant Alejandro Bello Silva ( 1887 - c. 1914 ) was a Chilean aviator who disappeared during his qualifying flight for certification as a military pilot .
Saint Stephen the Sabaite ( 725 - -796 ) was a Christian monk from Julis , a district of Gaza .
Tang Ching - sung ( traditional Chinese : 唐景崧 ; simplified Chinese : 唐景嵩 ; pinyin : Táng Jǐngsōng ) ( 1841 - -1903 ) was a Chinese general and statesman .
Robert Bontine Cunninghame Graham ( 24 May 1852 -- 20 March 1936 ) was a Scottish politician , writer , journalist and adventurer .
Štěpánka Haničincová ( née Hubáčková ; 30 September 1931 -- 27 October 1999 ) was a Czechoslovak actress , screenwriter , dramaturge and children 's television presenter .
Jedaiah ben Abraham Bedersi ( c. 1270 -- c. 1340 ) ( Hebrew : ידעיה הבדרשי ) was a Jewish poet , physician , and philosopher ; born at Béziers ( hence his surname Bedersi ) .
Thomas Michael Greenhow ( 5 July 1792 -- 25 October 1881 ) was an English medical doctor .
Maurice Tompkin ( 17 February 1919 -- 27 September 1956 ) was an English sportsman who played first - class cricket with Leicestershire and professional football for Bury , Leicester City , Huddersfield Town and Kettering Town .
Bruce Bellas ( 1909 -- 1974 ) was an influential photographer of the physique of nude males .
Joseph Knibb ( 1640 - -1711 ) was an English clockmaker of the Restoration era .
Sophus Frederik Kühnel ( 11 Maj 1851 -- 13 October 1930 ) was a Danish architect best known for his design of Mejlborg and a number of other buildings in Aarhus .
Captain Fergus Bowes - Lyon ( 18 April 1889 -- 27 September 1915 ) was a British soldier and older brother of Elizabeth Bowes - Lyon , Queen consort of the United Kingdom from 1936 until 1952 .
William de Lacy Aherne ( 1867/8 -- 4 December 1945 ) was an English architect , notable for the design of a large number of houses in Arts and Crafts styles in the Moseley area of Birmingham .
'' John McGahern ( 12 November 1934 -- 30 March 2006 ) is regarded as one of the most important Irish writers of the latter half of the twentieth century .
Sir George William Kekewich ( 1 April 1841 -- 5 July 1921 ) was a British Civil Servant and Liberal Party politician .
Ralph Helstein ( 11 December 1908 - 14 February 1985 ) was an American labour union official .
Faustino Bocchi ( 1659 - -1742 ) was an Italian painter , active in Brescia , who specialized in bizarre paintings of dwarfs .
Mutallip Hajim ( died 2008 ) was a prominent Uyghur businessman from Xinjiang province in China who died while in police custody .
Louis Bamberger ( 15 May 1855 -- 11 March 1944 ) was Newark , New Jersey 's leading citizen from the early 1900s until his death in 1944 .
Kishor Shantabai Kale ( 1970 - -2007 ) was a Marathi writer and social worker from Maharashtra , India .
David E. Weston ( 19 January 1929 -- 16 November 2001 ) was an English physicist , who worked at the Admiralty Research Establishment .
Eliska Vincent ( née Eliska Girard 1841 - -1914 ) was a Utopian socialist and militant feminist in France .
Arughtai , also known as Alutai ( Chinese : 阿魯台 ; Wade -- Giles : A - lu - t’ai ; d. 1434 ) , was a chingsang of the Northern Yuan dynasty based in Mongolia , who fought against the Yongle Emperor of Ming dynasty China and the Four Oirats .
Tobias Crisp D.D. ( 1600 - -1643 ) was an English clergyman and reputed antinomian .
Stevan Simić ( Kratovo , 9 May 1882 -- Skopje , 25 June 1962 ) was a Serb geographer , educational and national worker in Macedonia and a MP in the Kingdom of Yugoslavia .
Robert Fotherby ( died 1646 ) was an early 17th - century English explorer and whaler .
Omer Létourneau ( 13 March 1891 -- 14 August 1983 ) was a Québécois pianist , organist , composer and orchestra conductor .
James P. Aykroyd ( 1810 - - July 1835 Nashville , Tennessee ) was an early American composer , arranger , and music educator of piano , organ , and voice in New Bern , North Carolina , Raleigh , North Carolina , and Nashville , Tennessee .
Filippo di Matteo Torelli ( active 1440 - 1468 ) was an Italian painter and illuminator .
Teodora Ricci - Bàrtoli ( Verona 1750 - Venezia 1806 ) , was a Venetian actress .
Walter Nausch ( 5 February 1907 -- 11 July 1957 ) was an Austrian footballer , who later became a football manager .
Léon Vanderkindere ( 22 February 1842 - -9 November 1906 ) was a Belgian historian , academic and politician .
Christine Chaundler ( 5 September 1887 - 15 December 1972 ) was a British children 's author , who also wrote under the name `` Peter Martin '' .
Jürg Neuenschwander ( 14 January 1947 -- 23 March 2014 ) was a Swiss organist and musician .
Yerucham Gorelick ( 1911 - -1983 ) was a distinguished Rosh yeshiva in the Rabbi Isaac Elchanan Theological Seminary ( RIETS ) for forty years ( 1943 - -1983 ) .
Edward Thaddeus Barleycorn Barber ( 1865 - -1948 ) was born on 1 July 1865 in the Spanish colonized capital city of Santa Isabel on the island of Fernando Po in West Africa .
Winifred Emma May ( 4 June 1907 -- 28 August 1990 ) was a poet from the United Kingdom , best known for her work under the pen name Patience Strong .
Aubrey Martyn ( 4 January 1907 -- 13 February 1989 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Lieutenant - Colonel John Pitt Kennedy ( 1796 - -1879 ) was a British military engineer , agricultural reformer and civil servant .
Ethel Colburn Mayne ( 7 January 1865 - 30 April 1941 ) was an Irish novelist , short - story writer , biographer , literary critic , journalist and translator .
Antonio De La Fuente ( August 24 , 1902 -- January 1970 ) was a Mexican American professional boxer in the Heavyweight division .
Evander Bradley McGilvary Ph.D. ( July 19 , 1864 - -September 11 , 1953 ) was an American philosophical scholar , born in Bangkok to American Presbyterian missionaries , the Rev. Daniel McGilvary and Mrs. Sophia McGilvary .
Jon St. Ables , born Jon Stables , ( December 23 , 1912 -- 1999 ) was a British - born cartoonist .
Lars Fletre ( June 22 , 1904 -- September 9 , 1977 ) was a prominent Norwegian - American designer and sculptor .
Franz Lefler ( 1831 , Langenbruck ( now Dlouhý Most ) , Bohemia - 19 June 1898 , Weißenbach an der Triesting ) was an Austrian painter .
Virginia Field ( 4 November 1917 -- 2 January 1992 ) was a British - born film actress .
