Guy Maxwell Aylwin AAdipl FRIBA ( 1889 - -1968 ) was a notable British architect , practising almost wholly in the West Surrey area around Farnham .
Ernesto de Quesada López Chaves ( 1 November 1886 -- 1972 ) was the Cuban - born impresario who founded Conciertos Daniel , the classical music management agency now known as Hispania Clásica .
Seraphina Sforza ( 1434 -- 8 September 1478 ) , born Sveva da Montefeltro , was an Italian noblewoman and nun , a Poor Clare after her husband Alessandro Sforza discarded her .
Bivin of Gorze ( 810/830 - -863 ) was a Frank from the Bosonid - family .
Edward Dexter Sohier ( 1810 - -1888 ) was a United States lawyer , best remembered for defending John White Webster in a murder trial in 1850 .
Andrija Maurović ( 29 March 1901 -- 2 September 1981 ) was a renowned comic book author , often called the father of Croatian and Yugoslav comics .
William ap Thomas ( died 1445 ) was a member of the Welsh gentry family that came to be known as the Herbert family through his son William Herbert , 1st Earl of Pembroke and is an ancestor of the current Earls of Pembroke .
Jules Bourcier ( 1797 , Cuisery -- 9 March 1873 , Batignolles ) was a French naturalist .
Dr. Andrey Avinoff ( 14 February 1884 - 16 July 1949 ) ( sometimes referred to as Andrej Nikolajewitsch Avinoff or Andrei Avinoff ) , was a Russian entomologist .
Wang Duo ( 王鐸 ) ( died 884 ) , courtesy name Zhaofan ( 昭範 ) , formally the Duke of Jin ( 晉公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Yizong and Emperor Yizong 's son Emperor Xizong .
Morris Moss ( May 31 , 1842 - 1896 ) was a British Columbian colonist and Canadian pioneer .
Johannes Gysius ( born about 1583 -- died 1652 ) was a Dutch historian and minister .
Dr Joseph George Davidson FRSE ( 1892 - 1969 ) was an American chemist and inventor .
Francis Mezger ( 25 October 1632 -- 11 December 1701 ) was an Austrian Benedictine academic and writer , of St. Peter 's Archabbey , Salzburg .
Yi Yu - won ( Hangul : 이유원 ; 1814 - -1888 ) was a scholar - official of the late Joseon period .
Djanira da Motta e Silva ( Avaré , 20 June 1914 -- Rio de Janeiro , 31 May 1979 ) was a Brazilian painter , illustrator and engraver .
Hussein Dey ( also spelled Husayn Dey ; 1765 , Smyrna - 1838 , Alexandria ) ( Arabic : حسين داي‎ ) , was the last of the Ottoman provincial rulers of the Regency of Algiers .
Nicholas Orsini ( Greek : Νικόλαος Ορσίνι , Nikolaos Orsini , Italian : Nicola d'Epiro ) was count palatine of Cephalonia from 1317 to 1323 and ruler of Epirus from 1318 to 1323 .
Lord Edward Charles Cavendish - Bentinck ( 3 March 1744 -- 8 October 1819 ) , known as Lord Edward Bentinck , was a British politician .
Captain James Murison MLC ( 1816 - 1885 ) was an influential member of the Legislative Council of the Parliament of the Cape of Good Hope .
The Honourable William Napier Bruce CH CB ( 18 January 1858 -- 20 March 1936 ) was a British lawyer and educationalist .
Robert Wydow ( c. 1446 -- 1505 ) was an English poet , church musician , and religious figure .
Sir Samuel Knox Cunningham , 1st Baronet , QC ( 3 April 1909 - 29 July 1976 ) was a Northern Irish barrister , businessman and politician .
Mohamed Lamine Sanha ( died 6 January 2007 ) was a Bissau - Guinean Naval Chief of Staff .
Eric Gurney ( 1910 - -1992 ) was a Canadian - American cartoonist and illustrator .
Alphonse Hasselmans ( 5 March 1845 -- 19 May 1912 ) was a Belgian - born French harpist , composer , and pedagogue .
Bertram Lichtenstein ( 28 October 1918 -- 7 June 1989 ) was an American clothing manufacturer .
James Fitzpatrick ( died 1778 ) , better known as Sandy Flash , was a highwayman who operated in the areas west of Philadelphia , Pennsylvania ( now parts of Chester and Delaware counties ) in the late 18th century .
Carlo Antonio Porporati ( Volterra , 18 November 1741 -- Turin , 16 June 1816 ) was an Italian engraver and painter .
Aminath Faiza ( ca . 29 September 1924 -- 25 February 2011 ) was a Maldivian Dhivehi language poet and author .
Frank Saldo ( 10 July 1882 -- 1 June 1939 ) ( born as Frank Harold Woollaston ) was an early bodybuilder , and with his brothers Monte Saldo and Edwin Woollaston was a member of the strongman act The Montague Brothers in the early twentieth century .
Giovan Maria Salati ( 1796 - 1879 ) was a Napoleonic soldier who was the first person to swim across the English Channel .
George Keats ( 28 February 1797 -- 24 December 1841 ) was a businessman and civic leader in Louisville , Kentucky , as it emerged from a frontier entrepôt into a mercantile center of the old northwest .
Ljupčo Jordanovski ( Macedonian : Љупчо Јордановски , pronounced ( ʎupt͡ʃɔ jɔrdanɔfski ) ; 13 February 1953 -- 7 October 2010 ) was a Macedonian seismologist and politician .
François - Xavier Babineau ( 21 March 1825 -- 16 April 1890 ) was a Canadian Catholic priest , and the first New Brunswick - born Acadian to become a Catholic priest .
Howard Fox ( 10 December 1836 -- 15 November 1922 ) was a shipping agent and played a large part in the economic and cultural development of the town of Falmouth , Cornwall .
Casimir Lefaucheux ( 26 January 1802 -- 9 August 1852 ) was a French gunsmith .
Irene Ighodaro ( 16 May 1916 -- 29 November 1995 ) was a Sierra Leonean physician and social reformer .
Peter Claussen ( 1804 - 1855 ) was a Danish natural history collector born in Copenhagen .
Eugene Halliday ( 1911 - -1987 ) was a British artist , writer , and teacher .
Andronikos Asen Zaccaria or Asanes Zaccaria ( died 1401 ) was a Frankish lord of the Principality of Achaea in southern Greece .
Charles Bagge Plowright ( 3 April 1849 -- 24 April 1910 ) was a British doctor and mycologist .
Humphrey Fenn ( died 1634 ) , was an English puritan divine .
Carl Robin Geary , Sr , was elected mayor of Tracy City , Tennessee on April 13 , 2010 .
Diana Russell , Duchess of Bedford ( née Lady Diana Spencer ; 31 July 1710 -- 27 September 1735 ) , was a member of the Spencer family known for the unsuccessful attempt of marriage with Frederick , Prince of Wales .
Frederick Cathcart ( 1859 - 1934 ) was a British impresario , who was the Clerk of the Course and Chairman of Cheltenham Racecourse from 1908 to 1934 .
Jocelyn Herbert RDI ( 22 February 1917 -- 6 May 2003 ) was a highly influential British stage designer .
Hasmukh Dhirajlal Sankalia ( હસમુખ ધીરજલાલ સાંકળિયા ) ( 10 December 1908 - 28 January 1989 ) was an Indian archaeologist , specializing in Proto- and Ancient Indian history .
Arthur Adamov ( 23 August 1908 -- 15 March 1970 ) was a playwright , one of the foremost exponents of the Theatre of the Absurd .
Big Bear also known as Mistahi - maskwa ( c.1825 -- 17 January 1888 ) was a powerful and popular Cree chief who played many pivotal roles in Canadian history .
Humphrey Sturt ( c. 1724 -- 20 October 1786 ) was a British architect and Member of Parliament .
Willie Finnigan ( 24 November 1912 -- 23 April 2006 ) was a Scottish football player and coach , who played for Hibernian and Dunfermline Athletic .
Lieutenant - General Sipho Binda MMS ( 13 July 1952 - 10 November 2006 ) was a South African military commander who served as Chief of the Joint Operations Division of the South African National Defence Force before his death on 10 November 2006 .
Edmund Trowbridge Dana ( 29 August 1818 , in Cambridge , Massachusetts -- 18 May 1869 , in Cambridge , Massachusetts ) was a United States jurist and a nephew of Judge Edmund Trowbridge .
Emily Soldene ( 30 September 1838 -- 8 April 1912 ) was an English singer , actress , director , theatre manager , novelist and journalist of the late Victorian era and the Edwardian period .
Tepure Tapaitau QSM ( died 14 November 2010 ) was a Cook Islands politician , Cabinet Minister , and Deputy Leader of the Cook Islands Democratic Party and also the first Cook Islander to become the Commissioner of Police .
Tsagaanlamyn Dügersüren ( Mongolian : Цаганламын Дугэрсурэн ; 1914 - 1986 ) was acting Chairman of the Presidium of the State Little Khural(acting titular head of state ) of Mongolian People 's Republic from May 20 , 1972 to June 29 , 1972 following the death of Jamsrangiin Sambuu .
Maureen O'Carroll ( née McHugh ; 29 March 1913 -- 9 May 1984 ) was an Irish Labour Party politician who sat from 1954 to 1957 as Teachta Dála ( TD ) for Dublin North--
Richard Claridge ( 1649 - -1723 ) was an English Anglican priest and Quaker convert .
Anthony Cottrell ( 21 March 1806 -- 4 May 1860 ) was a farmer and one of fifteen investors in the Port Phillip Association .
Major - General Sir Trevor Chute KCB ( 31 July 1816 -- 12 March 1886 ) was an Irish soldier in the British army , whose six week campaign during the Second Taranaki War was the last to be carried out in New Zealand by imperial troops .
Heinrich Rantzau or Ranzow ( Ranzovius ) ( 11 March 1526 -- 31 December 1598 ) was a German humanist writer and statesman , a prolific astrologer and an associate of Tycho Brahe .
Zheng Wenguang ( Chinese : 郑文光 ; pinyin : Zhèng Wén Guāng , 9 April 1929 - 17 June 2003 ) was a Chinese science fiction writer .
Francis Webb Sheilds ( 8 October 1820 -- 18 January 1906 ) was a civil engineer on the Sydney Railway Company during its construction but before its opening .
Sir Shri Maharana Bhupal Singh Bahadur KCIE ( 1884 -- 4 July 1955 ) , also spelt Bhopal Singh , was the ruler of the Indian princely state of Udaipur ( or Mewar ) from 1930 and also Rajpramukh of Rajasthan from 1948 until his death on 4 July 1955 .
Franklin Leonard Pope ( 2 December 1840 -- 13 October 1895 ) was an American engineer , explorer , and inventor .
Joseph Bonomi the Younger ( 9 October 1796 -- 3 March 1878 ) was an English sculptor , artist , Egyptologist and museum curator .
James Brudenell , 5th Earl of Cardigan ( 20 April 1725 -- 24 February 1811 ) , styled The Honourable James Brudenell until 1780 and known as The Lord Brudenell between 1780 and 1790 , was a British politician and courtier .
Ibrahim Hussein Berro ( Arabic : ابراهيم حسين برّو‎ ) ( c. 1973 -- 1994 ) was a member of Hezbollah allegedly responsible for the 1994 AMIA Bombing in Buenos Aires , which killed 85 people .
Perley Ason Ross ( 6 April 1883 - 13 March 1939 ) was a U.S. experimental physicist who worked , carefully and without seeking publicity , at some essential problems in the behaviour of X - rays .
Swami Shambhavananda ( 1894 - -1972 ) was an Indian Hindu monk who pioneered beekeeping in Kodagu and secondary education in Mysore .
Abdel Moneim Amin ( Arabic : عبد المنعم أمين‎ ) ( 1912 - -1996 ) was an Egyptian military figure and politician .
Lenoir C. Wright ( 1911- March 18 , 2003 ) was a professor emeritus of History and Political Science at the University of North Carolina at Greensboro where he taught Asian history and culture .
Francis Adam Goodman ( 1827 - -1898 ) served the public most of his life as a politician and as a Union Army soldier .
Edward Dalby ( c. 1616/1615 - 30 March 1672 ) was a Recorder of Reading .
James Dalzell , 3rd Earl of Carnwath ( 1648−1683 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Franciscus Plante ( 21 April 1613 ( bapt . ) -- 1690 ) was a Dutch poet and chaplain .
Paul Tangi Mhova Mkondo ( 23 December 1945 -- 9 May 2013 ) was a Zimbabwean nationalist , academic , and businessman .
Sir Allan Maclean , 3rd Baronet of Morvern ( 1645 - -1674 ) was the 19th Clan Chief of Clan Maclean from 1651 to 1674 .
Germinal Pierre Dandelin ( 12 April 1794 -- 15 February 1847 ) was a mathematician , soldier , and professor of engineering .
Henry Percy , 2nd Earl of Northumberland ( 3 February 1393 -- 22 May 1455 ) was an English nobleman and military commander in the lead up to the Wars of the Roses .
In August 2003 , Maurice Ascalon succumbed to complications related to Parkinson 's Disease , an illness he endured during most of the final decade of his life .
Hugh Clifford , 3rd Baron Clifford of Chudleigh was born on 14 April 1700 and died on 26 March 1732 in Ugbrooke , where he was buried .
Robert Campin ( c. 1375 -- 26 April 1444 ) , now usually identified as the artist known as the Master of Flémalle , is usually considered the first great master of Flemish and Early Netherlandish painting .
Derek Taylor ( 7 May 1932 -- 8 September 1997 ) was an English journalist , writer and publicist .
Allan Hope ( 19 February 1903 -- 2 August 1984 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sir Arthur Rutledge ( 29 August 1843 -- 8 February 1917 ) was a lawyer and politician in Queensland ( Australia ) .
Dricky Beukes ( 29 December 1918 , Prieska , Northern Cape -- 9 November 1999 ) was a writer of Afrikaans novels , short stories and radio dramas .
Leonard Waldemar Hoff ( 22 May 1886 -- 16 July 1947 ) was a Norwegian railway director .
Edgar Feuchtinger ( 9 November 1894 -- 21 January 1960 ) was a German General ( Generalleutnant ) during the Second World War .
Eva Pflug ( 12 June 1929 -- 5 August 2008 ) was a German film and television actress , as well as a voice actress .
John Macdonald Cameron ( 8 April 1847 -- 3 September 1912 ) was a Scottish chemist and Liberal Party politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1892 .
Major - General Sir Hamilton Bower KCB ( 1858 - -1940 ) was a British Indian Army officer who wrote about his travels through Chinese Turkestan and Tibet .
Albertino Mussato ( 1261 -- 31 May 1329 ) was a Northern Italian statesman , poet , historian and playwright .
Paddy Chew ( 29 March 1960 -- 21 August 1999 ) was the first Singaporean AIDS victim to come out to the general public .
Thomas Boston ( 17 March 1676 -- 20 May 1732 ) was a Scottish church leader , theologian and philosopher .
Norman Pellegrini ( 18 July 1929 , Chicago - 2 July 2009 , Chicago ) was an American radio executive , producer , and personality .
Zong Chen ( Chinese:宗臣 , Zōng Chén;1525 - -1560 ) was a major Chinese scholar - official of the Ming Dynasty .
Hugh Algernon Weddell ( 22 June 1819 -- 22 July 1877 ) was a physician and botanist , specialising in South American flora .
Pedro Morales Torres ( born 1 January 1967 -- 13 September 2000 ) was a Chilean former football manager .
John Mór Tanister ( Scottish Gaelic : Eòin Mòr Tànaiste or Iain MacDhòmhnaill , died 1427 ) was the second son of John Macdonald ( John of Islay , Lord of the Isles ) and Princess Margaret Stewart of Scotland , daughter of King Robert II . He is the founder of Clan MacDonald of Dunnyveg .
Vice - Admiral Peregrine Osborne , 2nd Duke of Leeds ( 1659 -- 25 June 1729 ) , styled Viscount Osborne between 1673 and 1689 , Earl of Danby between 1689 and 1694 and Marquess of Carmarthen between 1694 and 1712 , was an English Tory politician .
John Arbuthnott , 8th Viscount of Arbuthnott DL FRSE ( 16 January 1778 -- 10 January 1860 ) was a Scottish peer and soldier .
Robert Dormer , 1st Earl of Carnarvon ( 1610 -- 20 September 1643 ) was an English peer .
John Hoadly ( 1678 - -1746 ) was an Anglican divine in the Church of Ireland .
Thomas Van Renssalaer Gibbs ( 1855 - -1898 ) was a politician and a member of the 1886 Florida Constitutional Convention .
Zhang Tingfa ( Chinese : 张廷发 ; 9 April 1918 -- 25 March 2010 ) was a Chinese Communist revolutionary and a major general of the People 's Liberation Army Air Force ( PLAAF ) .
Archdeacon Hone Kaa ( 9 April 1941 -- 29 March 2012 ) was an Auckland - based Anglican church leader , child welfare advocate and social - justice campaigner .
Pilt Carin Ersdotter ( 1814 - 1885 ) , was a Swedish milkmaid from Djura in Dalarna who became famous for her beauty .
Ivar Bergersen Sælen ( 19 November 1855 -- 24 November 1923 ) was Norwegian Minister of Education and Church Affairs in 1923 .
Anna Maria Franziska Charlotta Almlöf , née Ficker , ( June 16 , 1813 -- 1882 ) , was a Swedish stage actress .
Rodolfo Sciammarella ( 1902 - -1973 ) was an Argentine composer who worked on many film scores during his career .
Aratius ( Greek : ' Αράτιος , d. 552 ) was an Armenian military commander of the 6th century .
Dorothy Catherine of Brandenburg - Ansbach ( 23 February 1538 , Ansbach -- 18 January 1604 , Toužim ) was a princess of Brandenburg - Ansbach and by marriage burggravine of Meissen .
Rudolf Trümpy ( 1921 -- 30 January 2009 ) was a Swiss Geologist , who was born in the small Swiss town of Glarus .
Alvan Williams ( 21 November 1932 -- December 2003 ) was a Welsh former professional footballer and manager .
Gustav Adolf Semler ( 14 March 1885 -- 24 February 1968 ) was a German film actor of the silent era .
Yenovk Shahen ( Armenian : Ենովք Շահէն ; 3 February 1881 -- 28 May 1915 ) was an Armenian actor and director who lived in the Ottoman Empire .
Otto Eugene Adams ( Sr . ) ( 1889 - 1968 ) , the architect , was born in Baltimore November 1 , 1889 to a family with Baltimore and German ancestry .
Rangaswamy Narasimhan ( 1926 - 2007 ) was an Indian computer and cognitive scientist , regarded by many as the father of computer science research in India .
Bartolomeo Barbarino ( known as `` Il Pesarino '' ) ( ca . 1568 - -ca . 1617 or later ) was an Italian composer and singer of the early Baroque era .
Pope Pius VI ( 25 December 1717 -- 29 August 1799 ) , born Count Giovanni Angelo Braschi , reigned from 15 February 1775 to his death in 1799 .
Theophile Meerschaert ( 24 August 1847 -- 21 February 1924 ) was a Belgian - born prelate of the Roman Catholic Church .
Vinod Mehta ( 31 May 1942 -- 8 March 2015 ) was an Indian journalist , editor and political commentator .
Vera Nikolaevna Maslennikova ( Russian : Вера Николаевна Масленникова ; 29 April 1926 -- 14 August 2000 ) was a Russian Mathematician known for her contributions to the theory of partial differential equations .
Silvester Petra Sancta ( 1590 , in Rome -- 6 May 1647 , in Rome ) was an Italian Jesuit priest , and heraldist .
Hannah Greg ( née Lightbody ) ( 1766 - -1834 ) was the daughter of a wealthy Unitarian Liverpool merchant , Adam Lightbody ( 1729 - -1778 ) and Elizabeth Tylston ( 1735 - -1801 ) .
Ferris de Joux ( 1935 - -2009 ) was a designer , engineer and constructor of sports cars .
Arthur Wellington Clah ( 1831 -- 1916 ) was a Canadian First Nations employee of the Hudson 's Bay Company at Lax Kw'alaams ( Port Simpson ) , B.C. , who was also a hereditary chief in the Tsimshian nation , an anthropological informant , a Methodist missionary , and an extensive diarist .
Arthur Rose ( also found as Ross ; 1634 - -1704 ) was a Scottish minister , Archbishop of St Andrews , and , informally , the first Episcopal Primate of Scotland , after the fall of the Restoration Episcopate in 1689 .
Ted Cordner ( 31 January 1919 -- 4 March 1996 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1940s .
Thomas Netter ( c. 1375 -- 2 November 1430 ) was an English Scholastic theologian and controversialist .
Arthur Nicolson , 1st Baron Carnock , GCB , GCMG , GCVO , KCIE ( 19 September 1849 - -5 November 1928 ) , known as Sir Arthur Nicolson , 11th Baronet , from 1899 to 1916 , was a British diplomat and politician during the last quarter of the 19th century to the middle of World War I.
Leslie Barringer ( 1895 - -1968 ) was an English editor and author of historical novels and historical fantasy novels , best known for the latter .
Frederick William Pavy ( 29 May 1829 -- 19 September 1911 ) was a British physician and physiologist and the discoverer of Pavy 's disease , a cyclic or recurrent physiologic albuminuria .
Henriette Louise de Waldner de Freundstein ( or Waldner de Freunstein ) , Baronne d'Oberkirch ( 5 June 1754 at Schweighouse - Près - Thann , in Alsace -- 10 June 1803 ) is known for having written her Mémoires , which end in 1789 .
Captain James Octavius Machell ( 1837 - -1902 ) was an influential figure in British horse racing during the final decades of the 19th century .
Bartolomeu Velho ( died 1568 ) was a sixteenth - century Portuguese cartographer and cosmographer .
Francis Essex ( 24 March 1929 -- 5 March 2009 ) was a British television and stage producer , author and composer .
Charles Trevor Edmunds ( 7 December 1903 -- 1975 ) was a Welsh professional footballer who played as an inside right .
Johann Christoph Strodtmann ( 1717 - -1756 ) was a German author , writing on theology , philology , classical studies , history of law and history of scholarship , active during the reign of Frederick II . Strodtmann was born in Wehlau ( now Znamensk ) , East Prussia .
Antonio Lorenzini ( 1655 - -1740 ) was an Italian painter and engraver of the Baroque , active in his native Bologna , as well as in Florence .
Sir Alastair Forbes , ( 3 January 1908 - August 2001 ) , served with the Colonial Legal Service and ended his career as President of the Courts of Appeal for St Helena , the Falkland Islands and British Antarctic Territories from 1965 until 1988 .
Nicholas Goodrick - Clarke ( 15 January 1953 -- 29 August 2012 ) was a British historian and professor of Western Esotericism at University of Exeter , best known for his authorship of several scholarly books on esoteric traditions .
Øystein Olsen Ravner ( 1893 - 1975 ) was a Norwegian appointed councilor of state in the NS government of Vidkun Quisling 1940 - 1941 , and minister 1941 - 1942 .
Rexheb Beqiri ( 18 August 1901 - -10 August 1995 ) , better known by the religious name Baba Rexheb , was an Albanian Islamic scholar and Sufi .
Gwerful Fychan ( fl.1420 - 1490 ) was a poet during the period of the Welsh Beirdd yr Uchelwyr during the late Middle Ages .
George Bernard O'Neill ( 17 July 1828 -- 23 September 1917 ) , was a prolific Irish genre painter , from 1859 a member of the Cranbrook Colony of artists .
John Clarkson Jay ( 11 September 1808 New York City -- 15 November 1891 Rye , New York ) was a physician and notable conchologist .
Antoinette Cellier ( 23 June 1913 -- 18 January 1981 ) was an English film and theatre actress .
Rajko Pavlovec ( 15 January 1932 -- 25 August 2013 ) was a Slovene professor of geology , specialist in paleontology , stratigraphy and regional geology .
Jan Boner ( before 1463 - -1523 ) , also known as Hans Boner , was a German - born Polish merchant and banker .
Rev. William Linwood M.A. , M.R.A.S. ( 1817 -- 7 September , 1878 ) was an English classical scholar .
John Lyon , 6th Lord Glamis ( died 1528 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Ezra Ripley ( 1 May 1751 , Woodstock , Connecticut -- 21 September 1841 , Concord , Massachusetts ) was a clergyman of Concord , Massachusetts .
Hieronymus Praetorius ( 10 August 1560 -- 27 January 1629 ) was a north German composer and organist of the late Renaissance and very early Baroque eras .
Henry William Inwood ( 1794 - -1843 ) was an English architect , archaeologist , classical scholar and writer .
James Rosier ( 1573 - 1609 ) was an English explorer who is notable for his account of a 1605 expedition to America in which describes native peoples and fauna of northern New England .
Sjoerd Huisman ( 19 June 1986 -- 30 December 2013 ) was a Dutch speed skater who specialised in marathon speed skating .
Peter Grain ( c. 1785 -- 1857 ) was a French - American artist who achieved success in the United States .
Ira Schreiber Nelson ( 1912 - -1965 ) was an American botanist , working in Louisiana .
Antoine Philippe de Marigny de Mandeville ( 17 July 1721 - 6 Nov 1779 ) , Chevalier de St. Louis , was a French geographer and explorer .
Darrett B. Rutman ( 4 March 1929 -- 11 April 1997 ) was a noted historian of early America .
Arthur Arrowsmith ( 1869 -- 1954 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Stoke and Wolverhampton Wanderers .
Major Charles B. Lohmiller ( circa 1867 -- 21 June 1932 ) was also known as Hum - Pa - Zee ( which is Sioux for `` Yellow Shoes '' ) .
Joseph Bramah ( 13 April 1748 -- 9 December 1814 ) , born Stainborough Lane Farm , Stainborough , Barnsley Yorkshire , was an English inventor and locksmith .
Hemashree Hosahalli Nagaraju ( 1982 -- 9 October 2012 ) was Indian actress who worked in Kannada television soap operas .
Dirk Willems ( died 16 May 1569 ) ( also spelled Durk Willems ) was a Dutch martyred Anabaptist who is most famous for escaping from prison , turning around to rescue his pursuer -- who had fallen through thin ice while chasing Willems -- to then be recaptured , tortured and killed for his faith .
Sir Bernard Gascoigne ( Italian : Bernardo Guasconi ) ( 1614 - -1687 ) was an Italian military adventurer and diplomat , known as a royalist officer of the English Civil War .
Thierry d'Orca ( French : Thierry d'Orgue or Their d'Orguenes , Latin : Theodoricus de Orca , before 1174 - 1207 ) was Lord of Arsuf for marriage in the Kingdom of Jerusalem .
Lucien Laubier ( 22 September 1936 -- 15 June 2008 ) was a French oceanographer .
Adam Keir Rodger ( 1855 - -1946 ) was Coalition Liberal MP for Rutherglen from 1918 to 1922 .
Jay Velie ( 16 May 1892 -- 22 April 1982 ) was an American actor and singer who appeared in many Broadway shows during a career that spanned more than fifty years .
François - Marie Bissot , Sieur de Vincennes ( 17 June 1700 -- 25 March 1736 ) was a French Canadian explorer and soldier who established several forts in what is now the U.S. state of Indiana , including Fort Vincennes .
Harutiun Alpiar ( Armenian Յարութիւն Ալբիար , born July 12 , 1864 in Smyrna , † 5 April 1919 ) was an ethnic Armenian journalist and humorous writer .
Nikolaus von Schönberg ( 11 August 1472 -- 7 September 1537 ) was a German Archbishop of Capua .
Jacques Baby , dit Dupéron ( 1731 -- August 1789 ) was a Canadian fur trader and an employee of the British Indian Department .
Charles Alexander Bruce ( 11 January 1793 -- 23 April 1871 ) was a soldier , explorer and author who is best known for being the father of the tea industry in India .
John Boylen ( 29 March 1898 -- 5 November 1961 ) was a Scottish footballer who made 64 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City , Wigan Borough and Grimsby Town .
Charles Stourton , 15th Baron Stourton ( 2 March 1702 -- 11 March 1753 ) was the son of Charles Stourton ( 1669 - -1739 ) , himself the third son of William Stourton , 12th Baron Stourton .
Gregorio Bundio Nuñez ( 14 May 1928 − 7 March 2015 ) was a former football player and manager .
Robert Ibbitson ( fl . 1648 - -1654 ) was a 17th - century publisher in London .
Marta Abreu de Estévez ( 13 November 1845 -- 2 January 1909 ) was one of the most influential figures of her time in central Cuba , especially in her birth city and province of Santa Clara .
Isobel Hogg Kerr Beattie ( 25 August 1900 -- 13 July 1970 ) was possibly the first woman in Scotland to practice architecture on a regular basis .
Feltrino Gonzaga ( c. 1330 -- 28 December 1374 ) was an Italian condottiero , a member of the Gonzaga family .
Rachid Baba Ahmed ( Arabic : رشيد بابا أحمد‎ ; 20 August 1946 -- 15 February 1995 ) was an Algerian musical producer involved in the regional genre known as raï .
Carlo Pedrotti ( 12 November 1817 -- 16 October 1893 ) was an Italian conductor , administrator and composer , principally of opera .
Elizabeth Timothy or Elisabet Timothee ( 30 June 1702 -- April 1757 ) was a prominent colonial American printer and newspaper publisher in the colony of South Carolina who worked for Benjamin Franklin .
Sakari Pinomäki ( 1933 - -2011 ) was a Finnish systems engineer , who pioneered the mechanized forestry industry .
George Walter Thornbury ( 13 November 1828 , London -- 11 June 1876 , London ) was an English author .
Elena Altieri ( born Elena Capucci ) ( 27 July 1916 -- 1 May 1997 ) was an Italian film and stage actress .
Wacław Hański ( 1782 - -1841 ) was a Polish noble ( Korczak coat of arms ) , landowner , marszałek of the nobility in the Volhynian Governorate .
Daniel O'Brien , 4th Viscount Clare ( died 1693 ) was the son of Daniel O'Brien , 3rd Viscount Clare and Philadelphia Lennard .
Hugo Dewar ( 1908-June , 1981 ) was a Trotskyist activist influential in founding many of the early British Trotskyite groups .
Augustus , Grand Duke of Oldenburg ( 13 July 1783 -- 27 February 1853 ) was the Grand Duke of Oldenburg from 1829 to 1853 .
Zacharias Janssen ( also Zacharias Jansen or Sacharias Jansen ) ( 1585 -- pre-1632 ) was a Dutch spectacle - maker from Middelburg associated with the invention of the first optical telescope .
James Johnston Thornton ( November 24 , 1816 , in Highland County , Ohio -- c. 1882 , Guadalupe County , Texas ) was a prominent military reconstruction judge , land developer , and quartermaster of the Union Army .
Charles Beaubrun ( Charles Bobrun ) ( 1604 - -1692 ) was a French portrait painter active in Paris between 1630 and 1670 .
Michel Branamour Menard ( 1805 - 1856 ) was a Canadian - born trader , merchant , and co - founder of Galveston , Texas .
Ruth Popkin ( 13 June 1913 - 2 January 2015 ) led Hadassah and the Jewish National Fund .
Jerry McAuley ( 1839 , Ireland -- 18 September 1884 ) , along with his wife , Maria , was the founder of the McAuley Water Street Mission in New York City .
Mother Eugenia Elisabetta Ravasio ( San Gervasio d’Adda , 4 September 1907 -- 10 August 1990 ) was an Italian nun , visionary and mystic , from the Roman Catholic Church .
Dentist Dr. Frederick B. Moorehead ( 1875 - 1944 ) led the fight to make what is now the University of Illinois at Chicago College of Dentistry part of the University of Illinois .
George Butt ( 26 December 1741 -- 30 September 1795 ) was a British poet , teacher , cleric .
Jacqueline Malouf ( 3 July 1941 -- 12 October 1999 ) was an actress , artist and teacher .
Vito D'Ancona ( August 12 , 1825 -- January 9 , 1884 ) was an Italian painter of the Macchiaioli group .
Robin of Isenburg - Covern was the Count of Isenburg - Covern from 1277 until 1306 .
William Stewart , 1st Viscount Mountjoy ( 1653 -- 24 August 1692 ) , was an Anglo - Irish peer and soldier .
Henry IV , Count of Holstein - Rendsburg ( 1397 -- 28 May 1427 ) was Count of Holstein - Rendsburg and Duke of Schleswig from 1404 until his death .
Fryderyk de Melfort ( 1763 - 1797 ) was a notable Polish military officer and a freedom fighter .
Marion Couthouy Smith ( 1853 - -1931 ) was a poet .
Mark Sheridan ( 11 September 1864 -- 15 January 1918 ) , born Frederick Shaw , was an English music hall comedian and singer .
Major - General Thomas Victor Anderson DSO , CD ( July 4 , 1881 -- 1972 ) was a Canadian soldier and Chief of the General Staff , the head of the Canadian Army from 21 November 1938 until 6 July 1940 .
Frank Strawbridge ( 26 October 1891 -- 25 October 1971 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Archibald Watson FRCS ( 27 July 1849 -- 30 July 1940 ) was an Australian surgeon and professor of anatomy at the University of Adelaide .
Hannah White Arnett ( 1733 - 1823 ) was an American woman who is known for preventing a group of men in Elizabethtown , New Jersey ( now Elizabeth ) from proclaiming their loyalty to Great Britain in exchange for `` protection of life and property . ''
Sir Francis Ashley ( 24 November 1569 -- 1635 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1614 and 1625 .
Gunapala Piyasena Malalasekera , OBE , JP ( Sinhala : ගුණපාල මලලසේකර ) ( 8 November 1899 -- 23 April 1973 ) was a Sri Lankan academic , scholar and diplomat .
Robert Delafield Rands ( 1890 - -1970 ) was an American agronomist and mycologist .
Ellen Marion Delf - Smith FLS ( née Delf , 31 January 1883 -- 23 February 1980 ) was a British botanist .
William Cuffay ( 1788 -- July 1870 ) was a Chartist leader in early Victorian London .
Reginald Harrison FRCS ( 24 Aug. 1837 - 28 Feb. 1908 ) was a British surgeon , sometime Vice - President and Member of the Council of the Royal College of Surgeons and Consulting Surgeon to St Peter 's Hospital .
William Petyt ( or Petit ) ( 1641?--1707 ) was an English barrister and writer , and a political propagandist in the Whig interest .
N. M. R. Subbaraman ( 14 August 1905 -- 25 January 1983 ) was an Indian freedom fighter and politician from Tamil Nadu .
Nathaniel Finch ( died 1649 ) was an English lawyer and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1640 .
Gabriel Caldwell Wharton was born in Springfield , Washington County , Kentucky , 13 June 1839 and died in Louisville , Kentucky , 22 February 1887 .
Lewis Owen ( 1622 -- 22 January 1692 ) was a Welsh politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1659 .
Wilhelm Ludwig Ewald Schmidt ( 4 May 1805 , Nattwerder ( near Potsdam ) -- 5 June 1843 , Stettin ) was a German physician , botanist , and entomologist .
Ambroise - Dydime Lépine ( 18 March 1840 -- 8 June 1923 ) was a military leader of the Métis under the command of Louis Riel during the Red River Rebellion of 1869 - 1870 .
Joyce Carey , OBE ( 30 March 1898 -- 28 February 1993 ) was an English actress , best known for her long professional and personal relationship with Noël Coward .
Aldo Ferraresi ( Ferrara , 14 May 1902 -- San Remo , 29 June 1978 ) was a celebrated Italian concert violinist and violin pedagogue .
Thomas St Lawrence , 13th Baron Howth ( 1659 - -1727 ) was an Irish nobleman of the later Stuart and early Georgian era .
Ian Macfarlan ( born John Robert Macfarlan ; 21 November 1881 -- 19 March 1964 ) was the Deputy Leader of the Australian Liberal Party in the Australian state of Victoria during 1945 .
Sinan ibn Thabit ibn Qurra سنان بن ثابت بن قرة ) ( 880 ; † 943)was an ethnic Mandean physician and a Sabian who later converted to Islam .
Peder Paulsen Balke ( 4 May 1779 -- 6 September 1840 ) was a Norwegian farmer and non - commissioned officer in the military .
Gertrude Rachel Levy ( 1884 - 1966 ) was an author writing on comparative mythology , matriarchy , epic poetry and archaeology .
John McFarlane Gray ( or J. Macfarlane Gray ; 7 April 1831 -- 14 January 1908 ) was a Scottish engineer who invented a portable steam riveting machine and a steam steering mechanism for Isambard Kingdom Brunel 's famous SS Great Eastern .
Erich Leibenguth ( 31 March 1917 - 2 June 2005 ) was a German former footballer who played internationally for Saarland as a striker .
Gireesh Puthenchery ( 1 May 1961 -- 10 February 2010 ) was a noted Malayalam lyricist and screenwriter .
Anthony Gross CBE , RA ( 1905 - -1984 ) , was a British printmaker , painter , war artist and film director of Hungarian - Jewish , Italian , and Anglo - Irish descent .
Una Winifred Atwell ( 27 February or 27 April 1910 or 1914 -- 28 February 1983 ) was a Trinidadian pianist who enjoyed great popularity in Britain and Australia from the 1950s with a series of boogie - woogie and ragtime hits , selling over 20 million records .
Bärbel Bohley ( 24 May 1945 -- 11 September 2010 ) was an East German opposition figure and artist .
Lola Folman ( 1908 - -1979 ) was a Polish Jewish singer and composer popular in Poland in the 1930s .
The Honourable Sir William Macarthur ( December 1800 -- 29 October 1882 ) was an Australian botanist and vigneron .
William Pickford ( 1861 - -1938 ) was an English football administrator , who played an important role in the early development of The Football Association .
Herwald Ramsbotham , 1st Viscount Soulbury GCMG GCVO OBE MC PC DL ( 6 March 1887 -- 30 January 1971 ) was a British Conservative politician .
Lieutenant General Henry Wase Whitfield ( Chinese : 威非路 ) ( 1814 - 30 March 1877 ) was the Lieutenant Governor of Hong Kong and Commander of British Troops in China , Hong Kong and the Straits Settlements .
Diana Holman - Hunt ( 25 October 1913 -- 10 August 1993 ) was an English memoir writer and art critic .
Paul O'Montis ( 1894 - -1940 ) was a German singer , impersonator and cabaret artist .
Dean Spratt ( 1952 - -2007 ) was an American traffic reporter .
Gilbert Bourne ( date of birth unknown ; d. 10 September 1569 at Silverton , Devon ) was the last Roman Catholic Bishop of Bath and Wells , England .
Francis Leigh , 1st Earl of Chichester ( 1598 -- 21 December 1653 ) was a Royalist politician and courtier around the period of the English Civil War .
Charles Mason ( 13 April 1863 - 3 February 1941 ) was an English professional footballer , who played for Wolverhampton Wanderers .
Bendix Grodtschilling , also Bendix Grodtschilling the Elder , ( c. 1620 -- March 1690 ) was a Danish painter and carpenter .
Alexander Kedie ( ca 1746 -- 1817 ) was a carpenter and political figure in Nova Scotia .
Ramchandra Shripad Jog ( Devanagari : रामचंद्र श्रीपाद जोग ) ( 1901- 1980 ) was a Marathi writer from Maharashtra , India .
Jutok Kaneko ( 金子寿徳 ) ( 1958 -- 24 January 2007 ) was a Japanese guitarist and vocalist , and is best known for his work with Tokyo underground psychedelic rock group Kousokuya ( 光束夜 ) , who specialised in rock - based soundscapes characterised by the feeling of infinite space , desolate emotion and imminent chaos .
Oliver Hogue ( 1880 - -1919 ) was an Australian soldier and writer .
Timothy Neve ( 1724 - -1798 ) was an English churchman and academic .
Albert III , Margrave of Brandenburg - Salzwedel ( c. 1250 -- between 19 November and 4 December 1300 ) was a Margrave of Brandenburg .
Don Smoothey ( 11 April 1919 -- 17 May 2015 ) was a British stage actor , variety entertainer and comic .
Karl Schliephacke ( 2 August 1834 , Halberstadt -- 3 June 1913 , Blasewitz ) was German bryologist known for his studies of sphagnum mosses .
Francis Dreyfus ( 1940 -- 24 June 2010 ) was a French record producer , who focused on jazz and electronic music , publishing Jean - Michel Jarre 's first commercially successful work , Oxygène .

Haviv Shimoni ( Hebrew : חביב שמעוני‎ , born 13 January 1933 , died 13 July 1994 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Alignment between 1974 and 1977 .

Cirilo Marmolejo ( 1890 , Teocaltiche , México - 1960 , México ) , was a folk musician of guitarrón and vihuela , and pioneer in the development of the mariachi band .

Margery Deane was the pen name of Marie J. Davis Pitman ( née Davis 1850 - -1888 ) , an American author .
Lieutenant - General Sir Neil Douglas KCB KCH ( 1779 - 1 September 1853 ) was a British Army officer who fought at the 1815 Battle of Waterloo and later became Commander - in - Chief , Scotland .

Tamblot was a babaylan or native priest from Bohol , Philippines , who led the Tamblot Uprising in 1621 to 1622 during the Spanish era .

Horace Crotty ( 9 October 1886 -- June 1952 ) was a noted liberal Anglican bishop .
Edward Stillingfleet ( 17 April 1635 -- 27 March 1699 ) was a British theologian and scholar .
Andre Stander ( 1946 -- 13 February 1984 ) was a South African criminal and policeman .
Princess Yeshashework Yilma ( died 1982 ) was the daughter of Dejazmatch Yilma Makonnen , governor of Harar and niece of Emperor Haile Selassie of Ethiopia .
George Seddon ( 23 April 1927 -- 9 May 2007 ) was an Australian academic who held university chairs in a range of subjects .
William Howe Guion I ( 1817 - 1884 ) headed the Williams and Guion Black Star Line .
Tom Eckersley ( 30 September 1914 -- 4 August 1997 ) was an English poster artist and teacher of design .
James Alan Montgomery ( 1866 - -1949 ) was an American Episcopalian clergyman , Oriental scholar , and Biblical scholar who was professor of Old Testament and Semitics ( Hebrew and Aramaic ) , first at the Philadelphia Divinity School , and later , from 1913 to 1948 , at the University of Pennsylvania .
Hasan Polatkan ( 1915 -- 16 September 1961 ) was a Turkish politician and Minister of Labor and Finance , who was executed by hanging after the coup d'état in 1960 along with two other cabinet members .
Bernhard Lund ( 20 February 1889 -- 9 January 1968 ) was a Norwegian yacht racer .
Virginia Mixson Geraty ( 1915 - -2004 ) was a writer and outspoken defender of the Gullah language .
Lucio Fulci ( Italian : ( ˈlutʃo ˈfultʃi ) ; 17 June 1927 -- 13 March 1996 ) was an Italian film director , screenwriter and actor .

José Manuel da Cunha Faro Menezes Portugal da Gama Carneiro e Sousa ( 12 January 1788 - 24 October 1849 ) was a Portuguese count and the President of the Council of Ministers from 10 September to 4 November 1836 .

George Barraud ( born 17 December 1889 , Paddington , London , England -- d . 1970 , London , England ) was a British film actor .
Konstantinos Sapountzakis ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Σαπουντζάκης , 1846 - -1931 ) was a Greek Army officer .
Thomas Shingles ( 3 April 1903 -- 31 May 1984 ) was the Master Engraver of the Royal Canadian Mint from 1943 until his retirement in 1965 ; he first began work at the Mint in 1939 .
Eva Koppel née Ditlevsen ( 1 January 1916 , Copenhagen -- 2 August 2006 , Copenhagen ) was a Danish architect who together with her husband Nils ran one of Denmark 's largest architectural firms ( KKET , later KKE ) .
Abul Mansur Ahmed ( 3 September 1898 -- 18 March 1979 ) was a Bangladeshi littérateur , politician and journalist .
Albert Cullum ( November 1921 -- July 2003 ) was an American Elementary school teacher in the 1960s .
Brother Othmar Weldon MBE ( 20 Sept 1920 -- 2 June 2008 ) was the religious name of William George Weldon , an Australian Marist Brother who was from 1964 to 1972 the provincial head of the Marist order in Sydney .
William Penny Brookes ( 13 August 1809 -- 11 December 1895 ) was an English surgeon , magistrate , botanist , and educationalist especially known for inspiring the modern Olympic Games , the Wenlock Olympian Games and for his promotion of physical education and personal betterment .
William Penman Saunders ( September 15 , 1912 -- 1980 ) was a business manager and politician in Newfoundland .
George McIver ( 1859 - 1945 ) was a Scottish born Australian science fiction writer .
Sayyid Wasif Ali Mirza Khan Bahadur , KCSI , KCVO ( 7 January 1875 -- 23 October 1959 ) was the Nawab of Murshidabad during 1906 - -1959 .
Kenny Graham , born Kenneth Thomas Skingle ( 19 July 1924 - -17 February 1997 ) was a British jazz saxophonist , arranger , composer and essayist , described as `` one of Britain 's foremost jazz composers and arrangers '' , and as `` a genuine , often overlooked pioneer of the modern jazz movement in Britain '' .
Hans Krell ( c. 1490 - 1565 or 1586 ) , also Krehl ou Kreil , was a German painter of the Renaissance , mainly known as a portrait painter .

Werner van den Valckert ( ca . 1585 - after 1635 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter and engraver .
Walter Terence Stace ( 17 November 1886 -- 2 August 1967 ) was a British civil servant , educator , public philosopher and epistemologist , who wrote on Hegel , mysticism , and moral relativism .
Fadzil Mahmood ( 1936/37 -- 9 June 2010 ) was a Malaysian politician who served as the Speaker of the Perlis State Assembly from 9 September 1986 until 4 October 1990 during the administration of Abdul Hamid Pawanteh as Menteri Besar of Perlis .
Thomas Kimmwood Peters ( June 27 , 1879 -- 1973 ) was a pioneer American motion picture producer , newsreel cameraman , photographer , educator , and inventor .
Leslie Lievesley ( July 1911 -- 4 May 1949 ) was an English footballer and football manager .
Alfred Leyman ( 27 September 1856 -- 1933 ) was a Devon born watercolour artist whose works covered many aspects of late 19th century/ early 20th century Devonion rural life .
Joseph Sortain ( 1809 - -1860 ) was a British nonconformist minister , an evangelical Independent , philosophy tutor at Cheshunt College , and biographer of Francis Bacon .
Ellis Worth ( c. 1587 -- 1659 ) , or Woorth , was a noted English actor in the Jacobean and Caroline eras .
Per Håland ( 7 January 1919 -- 9 October 1999 ) was a Norwegian journalist and newspaper editor , and proponent for the Nynorsk language .
Mathilde Verne ( née Wurm ; 25 May 1865 -- 4 June 1936 ) was an English pianist and teacher , of German descent .
Saint Rupert of Bingen ( German : Rupert von Bingen ) ( 712 - -732 ) was the son of Bertha of Bingen , a Christian noblewoman .
John Lawrence Marye , Jr. ( November 4 , 1823 -- August 1902 ) , was a Conservative Party politician who served as the tenth Lieutenant Governor of Virginia from 1870 until 1874 .
William M'Culloch ( 1691 -- 18 December 1771 ) was Minister of Cambuslang during the extraordinary events of the Cambuslang Work ( 1742 ) when 30,000 people gathered in the hillsides near his church for preaching and communion .
Johann IV , Count of Katzenelnbogen ( died 1444 ) was one of the last members of the younger line of the Hessian House of Katzenelnbogen .
Laurie Dearle ( 16 October 1919 -- 25 October 1979 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1940s .
Mosleh Zamani ( also referred to as Moslah Zamani ) was a 23-year - old Iranian Kurd who was executed on December 17 , 2009 for having an `` illicit relationship with his girlfriend '' when he was 17 years old .
William Sawtrey ( died March 1401 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest who was executed for heresy .
Ali Bey , Prince of Dulkadir , was a former governor of Dulkadir , appointed by the Ottoman sultan Selim I. After resisting threats to his authority , he fell under suspicion of treason by Selim and was removed as governor in 1522 .
Ljubo Novaković ( Serbian Cyrillic : Љубо Новаковић ; 1883 - -1943 ) was a Montenegrin officer in the Royal Yugoslav Army who became a Chetnik commander during World War II . He initially fought for the Chetniks of Draža Mihailović and those of Kosta Pećanac , but became disillusioned with both movements .
Hrant Maloyan ( Armenian : Հրանտ Մալոյան ; 29 November 1896 - 1978 ) , also known as Hrant Bek , was a Syrian - Armenian military serviceman who became the general officer of the Syrian army and was appointed General Command of the Internal Security Forces in Syria .
Michael Doheny ( 22 May 1805 -- 1 April 1863 ) was an Irish writer and member of the Young Ireland movement .
Major General Edward Maitland Makgill Crichton OBE ( 1916 - -2009 ) was a senior British Army officer .
Jean - Baptiste Philippe Cannissié ( 19 January 1799 , in Landau -- 7 August 1877 , in Lille ) was a French architect and painter .
Fritz Gegauf ( 1893 - 1980 ) was a Swiss inventor and founder of the Bernina Sewing Machine Factory .

Trygve Bjørgo ( 5 January 1916 -- 2 March 1997 ) was a Norwegian educator and lyricist .

Thomas Moule ( 1784 -- January 1851 ) was an English antiquarian , writer on heraldry , and map - maker .
John Grimston , 6th Earl of Verulam ( 17 July 1912 -- 15 April 1973 ) , known as the Honourable John Grimston until 1960 , was a British peer and Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) .

Johann Adam Birkenstock ( also Birckenstock , Birkenstok , Berkenstock ; 1 February 1687 -- 26 February 1733 ) was a German composer and violinist .
Alarik Frithiof Holmgren ( 1831 - -1897 ) was a Swedish physiologist and professor at Upsala University and a vocal opponent of vivisection , and particularly the use of curare to immobilize subjects so they appeared peaceful while feeling great pain .
Paul Baynes ( Bayne , Baines ) ( c.1573 - -1617 ) was an English clergyman .
Ralph de Greystoke , 3rd Baron Greystoke , ( 18 October 1353 -- 6 April 1418 ) was an English peer and landowner .

Charles Doran ( 1 January 1877 -- 5 April 1964 ) was an Irish actor , one of the last of the touring actor - managers in the tradition of Frank Benson , John Martin - Harvey and Ben Greet .
Tapan Raychaudhuri ( 8 May 1926 -- 26 November 2014 ) was an Indian historian specialising in British Indian history , Indian economic history and the History of Bengal .

Grantly Dick - Read ( 26 January 1890 -- 11 June 1959 ) was a British obstetrician and a leading advocate of natural childbirth .
Karibasavaiah ( 1959 -- 3 February 2012 ) was an Indian actor who appeared in Kannada cinema and a theatre personality .
Richard St. Barbe Baker ( 9 October 1889 -- 9 June 1982 ) was an English forester , environmental activist and author , who contributed greatly to worldwide reforestation efforts .
Guy Daignault ( died 27 January 2005 ) was a Canadian short track speed skater .
Wilfrid Holland ( 27 June 1920 -- 15 September 2005 ) was a British born composer , choral and orchestral conductor , pianist and teacher who spent the last 45 years of his life based In Canberra , Australia .
Max Krook ( 1913 -- 4 August 1985 ) was an American mathematician and astrophysicst .
Frances Batty Shand ( c.1815 - -1885 ) was an early charitable activist in Cardiff , Wales .
Annie Sophie Cory ( 1 October 1868 -- 2 August 1952 ) was the author of popular , racy , exotic novels under the pseudonyms Victoria Cross(e ) , Vivian Cory and V.C. Griffin .

Richard Lewknor ( c1589 - 27 May 1635 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1621 and 1629 .
Gerard Luz A. James , better known as G. Luz A. James , ( circa 1926 - September 16 , 2006 ) was a U.S. Virgin Islander politician , lawyer , businessman and broadcaster .
Sir Henry Hartstonge , 3rd Baronet ( c. 1725 -- 1797 ) was an Irish politician and landowner who sat in the Irish House of Commons for Limerick ; he was a close associate of his powerful brother - in - law Edmund Pery , 1st Viscount Pery .
Robert Lascoe ( 1715 - -1771 ) was a native of Bromley in Kent .
Ethel Lina White ( 1876 -- 13 August 1944 ) was a British crime writer , best known for her novel The Wheel Spins ( 1936 ) , on which the Alfred Hitchcock film , The Lady Vanishes ( 1938 ) , was based .
Edgar Rumney ( 15 September 1936 -- 18 August 2015 ) was an English professional footballer who played for Colchester United .
Peter Maxwell Daniel FRCP FRCS FRCPath FRCPsych FLS FIBiol ( 14 November 1910 -- 19 November 1998 ) was a British medical doctor , who specialised in neuropathology .
Johann Mészáros von Szoboszló ( 1737 -- 17 November 1801 ) joined the Austrian army in 1756 and fought the Prussians , Ottoman Turks , and French during a long military career .
Felix Santschi ( 1 December 1872 -- 20 November 1940 ) was a Swiss entomologist known for discovering that ants use the sun as a compass and for describing about 2000 taxa of ants .
Kazimierz Kierzkowski ( 10 August 1890 in Międzyrzec Podlaski -- March 1942 in Auschwitz ) was a Polish political and social activist , major of the Polish Army and member of the Armia Krajowa .
Jabez Wolffe ( ca . 1877 - October 22 , 1943 ) attempted to swim the English Channel from 1906 to 1913 in 22 attempts .
John II , Count of Nassau - Beilstein ( died 1513 ) was a son of Count Henry IV and his wife , Eva of Sayn .
Randolph Adolphus Turpin ( 7 June 1928 -- 17 May 1966 ) , better known as Randolph Turpin , and in the United States also as Randy Turpin , was an English boxer who was considered by some to be Europe 's best middleweight boxer of the 1940s and 1950s .
Caroline Bray , known as Cara Bray , née Hennell ( 4 June 1814 -- 21 February 1905 ) was a British writer of children 's stories and school textbooks .
Emilia Lanier ( 1569 - -1645 ) , also spelled Lanyer , was the first Englishwoman to assert herself as a professional poet through her single volume of poems , Salve Deus Rex Judaeorum ( 1611 ) .
Les Watkins ( 23 May 1914 -- 5 July 1974 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Alfred Hollins ( 11 September 1865 -- 17 May 1942 ) was an English organist , composer and teacher , who was noted as a recitalist in Scotland .
Benjamin Boothby ( 5 February 1803 -- 21 June 1868 ) was a South Australian colonial judge , who was removed from office for misbehaviour .
Kanthirava Narasaraja II was the Wodeyar ruler of the Indian state of Mysore from 1704 to 1714 CE . He was born deaf and came to be called Múk - arasu ( literally `` mute king '' ) .
Giorgio Gaslini ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈdʒordʒo ɡaˈzliːni ) ; 22 October 1929 -- 29 July 2014 ) was an Italian jazz pianist , composer and conductor .

Robert Gillan ( died 1879 ) was a Church of Scotland minister .
Friedrich Eckenfelder ( 6 March 1861 -- 11 May 1938 ) was a Swiss - German impressionist painter , best known for his portrayals of farm horses and for townscapes with a background of the Swabian Alps .
John Cousen ( Bradford 1804 - -1880 London ) , was a landscape engraver .
Katharine Elliot , Baroness Elliot of Harwood DBE ( née Tennant ; 15 January 1903 -- 3 January 1994 ) was British public servant and politician .
Edward Dumaresq ( 16 June 1802 -- 23 April 1906 ) was a landowner , magistrate and acted as Surveyor General of Van Diemen 's Land ( now Tasmania ) .
Elizabeth Maitland , Duchess of Lauderdale ( née Murray ; 28 September 1626 -- 5 June 1698 ) was an influential Scottish noblewoman .
Joshua ben Hananiah ( Hebrew : יהושע בן חנניה d. 131 CE ) was a leading tanna of the first half - century following the destruction of the Temple .
Giles Fettiplace ( died 1641 ) , of Poulton , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
Yosef Lishansky ( Hebrew : יוסף לישנסקי‎ ; 1890 -- 16 December 1917 ) was a Jewish paramilitary and a spy for the British in Ottoman Palestine .
Edward José ( c. 1880 -- 18 December 1930 ) was a Belgian film director and actor of the silent era .
Husain al - Rahhal ( 1900 - 1971 ) was an Iraqi translator , journalist and Communist activist , who helped found the Iraqi Communist Party Al - Rahhal came from a family of officials and merchants .
Bronisław Żurakowski ( 26 June 1911 -- 4 October 2009 ) was a Polish engineer , aeroplane constructor , and glider test pilot .
Tommaso Temanza ( 9 March 1705 -- 14 June 1789 ) was an Italian architect and author of the Neoclassic period .
Isidore of Kiev , also known as Isidore of Thessalonica ( Greek : Ἰσίδωρος τοῦ Κιέβου ; Russian : Исидор ; Ukrainian : Ісидор ; b. Peloponnesus , 1385-d . Rome , 27 April 1463 ) was a Greek Metropolitan of Kiev , cardinal , humanist , and theologian .
John Bacchus Dykes ( 10 March 1823 -- 22 January 1876 ) was an English clergyman and hymnist .

Antonio Rivas Mercado ( 26 February 1853 -- 3 January 1927 ) was a Mexican architect , engineer and restorer .
Edoardo Raimondi ( Parma , July 26 , 1837 - Reggio , April 12 , 1919 ) was an Italian painter , known for landscapes and genre subjects .
Yi Kyu - won ( Korean : 이규원 , Hanja : 李奎遠 ; 19 March 1833 -- 11 November 1901 ) was a military official in the Joseon Dynasty .
Thornton Dial ( 10 September 1928 -- 25 January 2016 ) was a pioneering African - American artist who came to prominence in the late 1980s .
Sir John Milsom Rees GCVO ( 20 April 1866 -- 25 April 1952 ) was a Welsh surgeon and a specialist in laryngology .
George Armitstead , 1st Baron Armitstead ( 28 February 1824 in Riga , Latvia -- 7 December 1915 in London ) was a British businessman , philanthropist and Liberal politician .
Charles Macfaull ( 1800 -- 13 Dec 1846 ) was an early settler in the Swan River Colony , now Western Australia .
Diane Hamilton was the pseudonym of Diane Guggenheim ( 1924 - -1991 ) , an American mining heiress , folksong patron and founder of `` Tradition Records '' .
Andreas Bloch ( 29 July 1860 -- 11 May 1917 ) was a Norwegian painter , illustrator and costume designer .
James Boydell ( died January 1860 ) was a British inventor of steam traction engines .
Attila Hörbiger ( 21 April 1896 - 27 April 1987 ) was an Austrian stage and movie actor .
Edmund II ( died 30 November 1016 ) , usually known as Edmund Ironside was King of England from 23 April to 30 November 1016 .
Friedrich Ernst Ruhkopf ( Latin : Fridericus Ernestus Ruhkopf ; 1760 -- 1821 ) was a German philologist and educator born near Hildesheim .
Willy Reisvang ( 23 May 1923 -- 17 February 2001 ) was a Norwegian sports official .
Rhys ap Tewdwr ( before 1065 -- 1093 ) was a king of Deheubarth in Wales and member of the Dinefwr dynasty , a branch descended from Rhodri the Great .
Johann Samuel Beyer ( 1669 in Gotha -- 9 May 1744 in Karlsbad ) was a German composer and writer of a manual on singing ( 1703 ) .
Art Atkinson ( 2 April 1878 -- 7 August 1943 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Bern Dibner ( 18 August 1897 -- 6 January 1988 ) was an electrical engineer , industrialist , and historian of science and technology .
Koratala Satyanarayana ( 24 September 1923 -- 1 July 2006 ) was a communist politician from Andhra Pradesh , India .
Thomas Burdick ( November 17 , 1795 ( or 1797 ) -- November 6 , 1877 ) was a leader in the early Latter Day Saint movement , a Mormon pioneer , and a politician in Los Angeles County , California .
Abu Khalil Qabbani ( Arabic : أبو خليل القباني‎ / ALA - LC : Abū Khalīl al - Qabbānī ; 1835 - -1902 ) was a Syrian playwright and composer of Turkish origin .
Henrietta Matilda Jane Evans ( née Congreve ) ( 7 August 1827 -- 22 October 1886 ) was an Australian novelist , who wrote under the pseudonym Maud Jean Franc .
Margret Dünser ( 27 July 1926 - 5 June 1980 ) was an Austrian journalist known for her work in High Society and who wrote the book High Life .
Gustavo Sannia ( Napoli , 13 May 1875 -- 21 December 1930 ) was an Italian mathematician working in differential geometry , projective geometry , and summation of series .
Wang Zhihuan ( traditional Chinese : 王之渙 ; simplified Chinese : 王之涣 ; pinyin : Wáng Zhīhuàn , 688 - -742 ) and whose name has been traditionally been transcribed `` Wang Tsu - huan '' was a Chinese poet of the Tang dynasty 's Kaiyuan era .
Athirajendra Chola ( 1070 CE ) reigned for a very short period of few months as the Chola king succeeding his father Virarajendra Chola .
Rogers Ruding ( 1751 - -1820 ) was an English cleric and academic , known as a numismatist and the author of the Annals of the Coinage .
Rick Griffiths ( 1948 -- 13 December 2010 ) was an Australian Aboriginal activist and representative .
William John Wills ( 5 January 1834 -- c . June / July 1861 ) was a British surveyor who also trained for a while as a surgeon .
Alexander Hamilton Sands ( 1828 - -1887 ) was an American lawyer , writer , and Baptist minister , born in Williamsburg , Virginia .
Stephan Körner , FBA ( 26 September 1913 -- 17 August 2000 ) was a British philosopher , who specialised in the work of Kant , the study of concepts , and in the philosophy of mathematics .
Constantia Zierenberg ( 1605 - -1653 ) was a singer and musician from Danzig(Gdańsk ) in the Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
Robert Allan Smith CBE FRS PRSE ( 14 May 1909 - 16 May 1980 ) was a Scottish physicist .
Kugan Ananthan ( died 20 January 2009 ) was a person Royal Malaysian Police detainee who died in the police lock - up while under arrest for suspicion of alleged car robbery .
William Cleland ( ca . 1661 -- 21 August 1689 ) was a Scottish poet and soldier .
Ulrik Frederik Gyldenløve , Count of Laurvig ( 20 July 1638 -- 17 April 1704 ) was the leading general in Norway during the Scanian War , whose Norwegian leg is conventionally named the `` Gyldenløve War '' after him .
Joseph Buckner Killebrew ( 1831 - -1906 ) was an American planter and geologist .
Hujr ibn ' Adi al - Kindi ( died 660 CE ) was a companion of the Islamic prophet Muhammad .
Joannes Philippus Spalthoven , or Spalthof ( c. 1680 , Antwerp -- c. 1722 , Antwerp ) , was a Flemish Baroque painter .
Bingham Baring , 2nd Baron Ashburton PC DL FRS ( William Bingham Baring ; June 1799 - -23 March 1864 ) was a British businessman and a Whig politician who later became a Tory .
Primo Riccitelli ( 9 August 1875 -- 27 March 1941 ) , was an Italian composer .
Abraham Ortelius ( also Ortels , Orthellius , Wortels ; 14 April 1527 -- 28 June 1598 ) was a Flemish cartographer and geographer , conventionally recognized as the creator of the first modern atlas , the Theatrum Orbis Terrarum ( Theatre of the World ) .
He died on 2 May 1773 , and his son , Thomas Snelling , carried on business as a printseller at 163 Fleet Street , and published posthumously two of his father 's works .
Richard Crawley ( 1840 - -1893 ) was a Welsh writer , an academic who eventually pursued a career in insurance .
William Peryn ( died 1558 ) was an English Catholic theologian and prior of St Bartholomew 's , Smithfield , London .
Paolo Aretino ( 1508 - 1584 ) or Paolo Antonio del Bivi was a Renaissance era Venetian composer known for sacred music .
Sir Felix Edward Aylmer Jones , OBE ( 21 February 1889 -- 2 September 1979 ) , known as Felix Aylmer , was an English stage actor who also appeared in the cinema and on television .
Paolo Gerolamo Piola ( 1666 - -1724 ) was an Italian people
Francis Pierpoint Burton , later Francis Conyngham , 2nd Baron Conyngham ( c. 1725 -- 22 May 1787 ) was an Irish peer and politician .
Dennis Storer ( born 1932 , died 2007 ) was a rugby and soccer coach , best known for being the first Head Coach of the United States national rugby union team when it formed in 1976 .
Herman Musaph ( Dutch : Heijman Musaph ) ( 7 January 1915 -- 18 November 1992 ) was a Dutch Holocaust survivor , psychiatrist , dermatologist and sexologist .
Herbert Runge ( 23 January 1913 -- 11 March 1986 ) was a German heavyweight boxer .
Herbert Stern , 1st Baron Michelham KCVO ( 28 September 1851 -- 7 January 1919 ) , known as Sir Herbert Stern , Bt , between July and December 1905 , was a British financier and philanthropist .
William Odlin ( April 5 , 1865 -- May 1929 ) was an American lawyer and college football coach .
Thomas Jefferys ( c. 1719 -- 1771 ) , `` Geographer to King George III '' , was an English cartographer who was the leading map supplier of his day .
Marjorie Lewty , née Lobb ( b. 8 April 1906 in Wallasey , Cheshire , England , UK -- d. 21 January 2002 ) was a British writer of short stories and over 45 romance novels from 1958 to 1999 to Mills & Boon .
Joseph Throckmorton ( June 16 , 1800 -- December 1872 ) was an American steamboat builder and captain during the 19th century .
Robert Hugh McWilliams , Jr. ( April 27 , 1916 -- April 10 , 2013 ) was an American United States federal judge from the Tenth circuit .
Coching Chu or Zhu Kezhen ( simplified Chinese : 竺可桢 ; traditional Chinese : 竺可楨 ; pinyin : Zhú Kězhēn ; Wade -- Giles : Chu K'o - chen ; 7 March 1890 -- 7 February 1974 ) was a prominent Chinese meteorologist , geologist and educator .
Sir Alfred Herbert Brewer ( 21 June 1865 -- 1 March 1928 ) was an English composer and organist .
Anders Christian Jensen - Haarup ( 8 January 1863 -- 30 January 1934 ) was a Danish entomologist who specialised in Hymenoptera .
Sir David Lindsay of Edzell , Lord Edzell ( 1551?--1610 ) was a Scottish judge .
José Leitão de Barros ( 22 October 1896 -- 29 June 1967 ) was a Portuguese film director and playwright .
Timothy Holmes FRCS ( 9 May 1825 , Islington , Greater London -- 8 September 1907 ) was an English surgeon , known as the editor of several editions of Gray 's Anatomy .
Pablo José Arriaga or Pablo José Arriga ( Vergara , Biscay , 1564 -- died at sea , 1622 ) was a Spanish Jesuit missionary in South America .
Philip Hutchinson ( born 25 January 1862 in West Dean , England , died 30 September 1925 in Durban , Natal ) was a South African cricketer who played in two Tests in 1889 .
Roger Borsa ( 1060/1 -- 22 February 1111 ) was the Norman Duke of Apulia and Calabria and effective ruler of southern Italy from 1085 until his death .
Lu Xisheng ( 陸希聲 ) ( d. 895 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving briefly as chancellor during the reign of Emperor Zhaozong .
Anne Goldthwaite ( 1869 - -1944 ) was an American painter and printmaker and an advocate of women 's rights and equal rights .
Dina Sfat , born Dina Kutner ( 28 October 1938 -- 20 March 1989 ) was a Brazilian actress born to Polish Jewish immigrants .
Matteo Martinolich ( 10 February 1860 - 23 December 1934 ) was a Croatian master shipbuilder , and was the first to use Mississippi pine in the building of seagoing vessels , which was approved by the Marine Underwriters .
Per Saugman ( 26 June 1925 -- 25 November 2005 ) was a Director of Blackwell Scientific Publications and a Fellow of St Cross College , Oxford .
Thomas Southey Baker ( 29 June 1848 -- 24 June 1902 ) was an amateur sportsman who was on the winning crew that won The Boat Race in 1869 and played for England in the fourth unofficial football match against Scotland in November 1871 .
Henry Hunt Snelling ( 8 November 1817 -- 24 June 1897 ) was a 19th - century American photographer , editor , author and inventor .
Dawson Millward ( 1870 - -1926 ) was a British stage and film actor .
Don Carlos de Beistegui y de Yturbe ( 1895 -- 17 January 1970 ) , also known as Charles or Charlie de Beistegui , was an eccentric multi - millionaire art collector and interior decorator and one of the most flamboyant characters of mid-20th - century European life .
Alastair Ross Goobey CBE ( 6 December 1945 -- 2 February 2008 ) was a leading British investment manager and pension fund manager .
Antonio Valeriano ( ca . 1531 - -1605 ) was a colonial Mexican , Nahua scholar and politician .
Lidiya Tseraskaya ( Russian : Лидия Петровна Цераская ) ( 1855 - 1931 ) was a Soviet astronomer .
Itala Mela ( 28 August 1904 - 29 April 1957 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic who was a lapsed Christian until a sudden conversion of faith in the 1920s and as a Benedictine oblate assumed the name of `` Maria della Trinità '' .
Richard Salwey ( 1615 -- 1685 ? ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons variously between 1645 and 1659 .
Walt Partymiller ( 1912 - -1991 ) was an American cartoonist and artist known for his watercolors .
Fatou Ndiaye Sow ( 1956 - -2004 ) was a Senegalese poet , teacher and children 's writer .
Thomas Langlois Lefroy ( 8 January 1776 -- 4 May 1869 ) was an Irish - Huguenot politician and judge .
Pete Glatter ( born January 1949 ) was a British based radical analyst of the Soviet Union and Russia , whose developing career was cut short by degenerative illness in March 2008 .
William Gregory `` Greg '' Kelsall ( 1893 - 1967 ) , known by the stage name Greg Kelsey , was an English born actor and entertainer who gained fame in the USA in the 1930s and 1940s .
Babu Gulab Singh ( died 1857 ) was an Indian Talukdar and one of the rebels of the Indian Rebellion of 1857 .
René Gabriel ( 14 September 1890 -- 30 October 1950 ) was a French decorative artist and designer who specialized in furniture series ( meuble de série ) .
Sir Edward Seymour , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1580 -- 5 October 1659 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1601 and 1625 .
Antonietta Stefanini ( 3 December 1926 -- 18 January 2016 ) , best known as Antonella Steni , was an Italian actress , voice actress , comedian and presenter .
John Hare Powel ( 22 April 1786 , Philadelphia , Pennsylvania -- 14 June 1856 , Newport , Rhode Island ) was an American agriculturist , art collector and philanthropist .
Andreas Franz Wilhelm Schimper ( 12 May 1856 -- 9 September 1901 ) was a botanist and phytogeographer who made major contributions in the fields of histology , ecology and plant geography .
David Conforte ( c. 1618 -- c. 1685 ) ( Hebrew : דוד קונפורטי ) was a Hebrew literary historian born in Salonica , author of the literary chronicle known by the title Ḳore ha - Dorot .
Lars Magnus Moen ( 29 November 1885 -- 22 April 1964 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Education and Church Affairs 1948 - 1951 and 1951 - 1953 .
William Hammond Hall ( 1846 in Hagerstown , Maryland , United States of America - 1934 ) was a civil engineer who was the first State Engineer of California , and designed Golden Gate Park in San Francisco , CA .
Theodore Maly ( 1894 -- 20 September 1938 ) was a former Roman Catholic priest and Soviet intelligence officer during the 1920s and 1930s .
Enver Maloku ( 1954 , Podujevo -- 11 January 1999 ) was a Kosovar Albanian journalist and writer and head of the Kosovo Information Centre .
Thomas Leverett Nelson ( 1827 - -1897 ) was U.S. District Court judge in Massachusetts .
Lewis Doxat ( 1778 , Calcutta , India - 4 March 1871 , London , England ) was an English newspaper editor .
Constance Chapman ( 29 March 1912 -- 10 August 2003 ) was an English character actor working in theatre and television .
Akeem Anifowoshe ( 11 September 1968 -- 1 December 1994 ) , popular as `` Kid '' Akeem , was a Nigerian Super Flyweight professional boxer .
Josef Mayr - Nusser ( 27 December 1910 - 24 February 1945 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic who served as the President of the Saint Vincent de Paul Conference of the Bolzano division as well as a member of Catholic Action .
Jacob Ernst von Reider ( 1784 -- December 1853 in Ludwigsstadt in Bavaria ) was a German zoologist and botanist .
Johan van der Burg ( Delft , ? --1640 ) was the Dutch Governor of Formosa from 1636 to 1640 .
Robert King , 2nd Baron Kingston ( died 1693 ) was an Irish nobleman , the eldest son of John King , 1st Lord Kingston .
Yvonne McCain ( 1948 - 2011 ) was the lead plaintiff in a lawsuit , which led to a landmark ruling in 1986 by the Appellate Division of the State Supreme Court in Manhattan , stating that New York City could not deny emergency shelter for homeless families with children .
Sattar Bahlulzade ( Azerbaijani : Səttar Bəhlulzadə ; , 15 December ( O.S. 2 December ) 1909 -- 14 October 1974 ) was the founder of contemporary Azerbaijani landscape painting .
Matthew White Ridley , 2nd Viscount Ridley MP DL JP ( 6 December 1874 -- 14 February 1916 ) was a British peer and Conservative politician .
Shiv Singh died of heart attack in a private hospital at Panchkula , Haryana on 26 June 2015 .
Giles H. Miller ( 1902 or 1903 -- 2005 ) was born in his parents ' home in Lynchburg , Virginia , while Theodore Roosevelt was serving his first term as President of the United States .
Edmund Burke Wood ( 13 February 1820 in Fort Erie , Ontario -- 7 October 1882 in Winnipeg , Manitoba ) was a Member of the Legislative Assembly of Ontario for Brant South , and served as the first provincial treasurer of Ontario from 1867 to 1871 under Premier John Sandfield Macdonald .
Liam an Dúna Mac Cairteáin , Irish poet , 1668 - -1724 .
Helge Kvamme ( 1938 -- 5 August 1996 ) is a Norwegian jurist and businessperson .

Bill Hore ( 24 March 1890 -- 15 September 1971 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda , Carlton and Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Johanna Hård , née Jungberg ( 3 December 1789 - 12 March 1851 ) , was a Swedish pirate .

Joyce Reason ( December 1894 - 18 September 1974 ) was a British author of missionary biographies and historical fiction for young readers .

Stanley Pinker ( 1924 -- 16 June 2012 ) was a Namibian - born painter and printmaker .
Nijaz Duraković ( 1 January 1949 -- 29 January 2012 ) was a Bosnian author , intellectual , professor and politician .
Konrad von Marburg ( sometimes anglicised as Conrad of Marburg ) ( born 1180 -- died 30 July 1233 ) was a medieval , German priest and nobleman .
Sir German Sims Woodhead , KBE ( 29 April 1855 -- 29 December 1921 ) was an English pathologist , born at Huddersfield .
Theodor Szántó , also seen as Tivadar Szántó ( 3 June 1877 -- 7 January 1934 ) was a Hungarian Jewish pianist and composer .
Norman Worker ( 1927 - 5 February 2005 ) was a British comic book writer , best known for his work on comic books featuring Lee Falk 's The Phantom .

Johannes Magirus ( 26 March 1537 -- 4 July 1614 ) was a German Lutheran Theologian .
Susenghphaa ( reign 1603 - -1641 ) , also Pratap Sinha ( Singha ) ( Assamese : স্বৰ্গদেউ প্ৰতাপ সিংহ ) , was the 17th and one of the most prominent kings of the Ahom kingdom .
Jesse Lewisohn ( 1872 -- 30 November 1918 ) , was a businessman involved in copper trading with Lewisohn Brothers , and an owner of racehorses .
John Robert Parker Ravenscroft , OBE ( 30 August 1939 -- 25 October 2004 ) , known professionally as John Peel , was an English disc jockey , radio presenter , record producer and journalist .
Nicholas I Garai ( Hungarian : Garai I Miklós , Croatian : Nikola I Gorjanski ) ( c. 1325 -- 25 July 1386 ) was a most influential officeholder under king Louis I and queen Mary of Hungary .
Walter Calverley ( died 1605 ) was an English squire and murderer .
Theodor Ketterer ( 1815 - 1884 ) was a renowned Black forest clockmaker who worked in Furtwangen , ( Germany ) .
John Valentine Ellis ( 14 February 1835 -- 10 July 1913 ) was a Canadian journalist and parliamentarian .
K. M. Mathew ( Malayalam : കെ.എം.മാത്യു ) ( 2 January 1917 -- 1 August 2010 ) was a former Chief Editor of leading Malayalam daily Malayala Manorama .

Martin Bílek ( 7 January 1973 -- 1 August 2000 ) was a Czech shot putter .
William Cunningham Blest ( born 1800 - died 1884 ) was an Anglo - Irish doctor , the president of the first Medical Society of Chile , creator of the first School of Medicine in Chile , a politician and father of the novelist Alberto Blest Gana .
William Byron , 3rd Baron Byron ( 1636 -- 13 November 1695 ) was an English peer and unskilled poet .
Nicolai Emanuel de Thygeson ( 19 April 1772 -- 16 May 1860 ) or Niels Emanuel de Thygeson , was a Danish - Norwegian landowner and government official .
Meeli Truu ( 27 April 1946 -- 7 August 2013 ) was an Estonian architect .

Douglas Hamilton , 8th Duke of Hamilton and 5th Duke of Brandon KT ( 24 July 1756 -- 2 August 1799 ) was a Scottish peer .
George W. Lakin ( March 29 , 1816 -- 1884 ) was an American schoolteacher and lawyer , originally from Maine , who became a pioneer leader of Wisconsin .
Bernard Natan ( born Natan Tannenzaft ; July 14 , 1886 -- October 1942 ) was a Franco - Romanian film director and actor of the 1920s and 1930s .
Molly Luft ( 19 March 1944 -- 24 November 2010 ) was a German prostitute , noted for her obesity and lurid make - up .
Ivor Bennett ( 16 June 1913 -- 16 June 2003 ) was a Welsh rugby union and professional rugby league footballer of the 1930s and 1940s .
Otto Liiv ( 6 September ( O.S. 24 August ) 1905 in Narva -- 10 December 1942 in Tartu ) was an Estonian historian and archivist .
P. A. Backer ( Malayalam : പി.എ. ബക്കർ ; 1940 -- 22 November 1993 ) was one of the `` new wave '' Malayalam film directors of the 1970s and 1980s .
Blessed Pey Berland ( or Peyberland , from Pierre Berland ; c. 1380 -- January 1458 ) was the Archbishop of Bordeaux from 1430 until his abdication , during a pivotal time in the history of the city and of Gascony .
Henri Piet ( 1 January 1888 -- 4 May 1915 ) was a French Lightweight boxer .
Agnes C. Hall ( née Scott ) ( 1777 - -1846 ) was a Scottish writer of novels and non - fiction articles .
Carlmann Kolb ( 29 January 1703 -- 15 January 1765 ) was a German priest , organist , and composer .
Fanny McIan ( c. 1814 -- 7 April 1897 ) was an English artist who specialized in Scottish historical scenes .
Jin Zhun ( 靳準 ) ( died 318 ) was an official of the Chinese / Xiongnu state Han Zhao , who in 318 staged a coup against the Han Zhao emperor and his son - in - law Liu Can and then massacred the imperial Liu family .
Peter Riedemann ( Rideman , Rydeman , Ryedeman ) ( 1506 -- 1 December 1556 ) is considered the second founder of the Hutterite brotherhood , a branch of Anabaptist Christianity .
