Godred Crovan ( died 1095 ) , known in Gaelic as Gofraid Crobán , Gofraid Meránach , and Gofraid Méránach , was a Norse - Gaelic ruler of the kingdoms of Dublin and the Isles .
Michael Grumley ( 1942 - -1988 ) was an American writer and artist .
Ole Munch Ræder ( 3 May 1815 -- 10 March 1895 ) was a Norwegian jurist and diplomatist .
Sir Fred Schonell ( 3 August 1900 -- 22 February 1969 ) was an Australian educationist , and vice - chancellor of the University of Queensland from 1960 to 1969 .
Paul Paray ( French : ( pɔl paʁɛ ) ; 24 May 1886 -- 10 October 1979 ) was a French conductor , organist and composer .
John Simopoulos ( 12 June 1923 - 4 March 2015 ) was a philosopher and fellow of St. Catherine 's College , Oxford .
Joseph Hathaway Cosby ( June 2 , 1902 -- October 11 , 1998 ) was an American pastor , US Army chaplain , and the second President of Hargrave Military Academy .
Peter Jeffrey ( 18 April 1929 -- 25 December 1999 ) was an English actor with many roles in television and film .
Lorenzo Bartolini ( 7 January 1777 -- 20 January 1850 ) was an Italian sculptor who infused his neoclassicism with a strain of sentimental piety and naturalistic detail , while he drew inspiration from the sculpture of the Florentine Renaissance rather than the overpowering influence of Antonio Canova that circumscribed his Florentine contemporaries .
Leonard C. Lewin ( 2 October 1916 -- 28 January 1999 ) was an American writer , best known as the author of the bestseller The Report from Iron Mountain ( 1967 ) .
Francis Henry de la Motte , or François Henri de la Motte , was a French citizen and ex - French army officer executed in London for High Treason on 27 July 1781 .
Iwuchukwu Amara Tochi ( 1985 or 1986 - -26 January 2007 ) was a Nigerian national convicted of drug trafficking in Singapore .
Annibale Rigotti ( 30 October 1870 -- 8 March 1968 ) was an Italian architect , teacher , designer and urban planner .
Peter Dudley ( 21 June 1935 -- 20 October 1983 ) was an English character actor best known for his role as Bert Tilsley in the ITV television series Coronation Street ; a role he played continuously from 1979 until 1983 .
Ruth Milles ( 19 April 1873 -- 11 February 1941 ) was a Swedish sculptor and writer .
Simion Coman ( born 1890 , died 1971 ) was a Romanian Brigadier - General during World War II . In 1941 , he started his career as Commanding Officer 3rd Dorobanti Infantry Regiment .
Abuna Yesehaq , born Laike Maryam Mandefro in Adwa , Ethiopia , 1933 ; died 29 December 2005 Newark , New Jersey , was a leader of the Ethiopian Orthodox Tewahedo Church in the Western hemisphere .
Somchandbhai Solanki ( December 31 , 1920 - 1985 ) was an Indian politician and was a Member of the Parliament of India in the 4th Lok Sabha and 5th Lok Sabha .
John Prideaux Lightfoot , D.D. ( 23 March 1803 -- 23 March 1887 ) was an English clergyman who served as the Rector of Exeter College , Oxford from 18 March 1854 until his death and as Vice - Chancellor of Oxford University from 1862 to 1866 .
Frank Finn FZS , MBOU ( 1868 -- 1 October 1932 ) was an English ornithologist .
Franco Lechner , best known as Bombolo ( 22 May 1931 -- 21 August 1987 ) , was an Italian character actor and comedian .
Brian Rawlinson ( 12 November 1931 -- 23 November 2000 ) was an English actor and writer for films and TV from the 1950s .
Sir Thomas Palmer , 4th Baronet , of Carlton ( 1702 -- 14 June 1765 ) was a British politician .
Marian Lutosławski ( 1871 -- 5 September 1918 ) was a Polish mechanical engineer and inventor born during the foreign partitions of Poland .
Ned Jenkins ( 28 July 1904 - 8 November 1990 ) was an international rugby union lock who represented Wales and played club rugby for Aberavon .
Patrick Adair ( 1625?--1694 ) was an Irish presbyterian minister , notable for his part in negotiations with government for religious liberty and settlement through his career .
Herbert Feith ( 1930 -- 15 November 2001 ) was an Australian academic and world leading scholar of Indonesian politics .
Alfred Worcester ( 1855 - -1951 ) was a general practitioner in Waltham , Massachusetts known for pioneering work in patient care , the treatment of appendicitis , and the use of Caesarean section .
Antti Lovag ( 1920 -- 27 September 2014 ) was a Hungarian architect .
Ted Buckley ( 23 June 1912 -- 4 February 1984 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Peer Raben ( 3 July 1940 -- 21 January 2007 ) was a German composer best known for his work with German filmmaker Rainer Werner Fassbinder .
Prakash Mehra ( Hindi : प्रकाश मेहरा , 13 July 1939 -- 17 May 2009 ) was a legendary Hindi film producer and director .
Gloria Lasso ( 25 October 1922 -- 4 December 2005 ) was a Spanish - born singer , long based in France .
Bogdan Baltazar ( 22 September 1939 -- 28 December 2012 ) was a leading Romanian banker and the first spokesman of the Romanian government following the fall of the communist regime .
Zhang Gongduo ( 張公鐸 ) ( died 945 ) was a general and official of the Chinese Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms Period state Later Shu .
Thomas Scot ( or Scott ; died 17 October 1660 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1645 and 1660 .
Mamai ( Tatar : Мамай , Mamay , 1335 - 1380 ) , of Kiyat descent , was a powerful military commander of the Blue Horde in the 1370s .
Chen Xianqi ( 陳仙奇 ) ( died 786 ) was a general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty .
James Miln ( 1819 -- 1881 ) was a Scottish antiquary who excavated many sites around the French village of Carnac in Brittany from around the 1860s .
William Plaxton ( 1843 - -1907 ) was a Canadian politician who served as a Member of the Legislative Assembly of the Northwest Territories .
Sergei Dolgov , also transliterated as Sergey or Serhei , ( ca . 1964 ) , was a Ukrainian journalist who served as editor for the Vestnik Pryazovya and Khochu v SSSR in Mariupol , Ukraine before he went missing and was killed in 2014 .
Jack Wilson Lydman ( 1914 - -2005 ) was an actor , Foreign Service Officer , and a United States Ambassador to Malaysia ( 1969 - -1973 ) .
Erik Sætter - Lassen ( 15 July 1892 -- 24 December 1966 ) was a Danish sport shooter who competed at the 1920 , 1924 , 1936 and 1948 Summer Olympics .
John Hough James ( 1800 - 1881 ) was an American lawyer , banker , railroad builder , scientific farmer and stockbreeder , legislator , politician , editor , lecturer and writer .
Marie Bloede ( 29 September 1821 - 12 March 1870 ) was an American author of German descent , who also published under the pseudonym Marie Westland .
Giambattista Canano ( 1515 - -1579 ) was a notable anatomist and professor at the University of Ferrara of the 16th century who was wrongly credited with the discovery of the circulation of the blood which was presented to him and other scholars by Amato Lusitano .
Marie Fel ( 24 October 1713 -- 2 February 1794 ) was a French opera singer and a daughter of the organist Henri Fel .
Sir Matthew Carew ( died 1618 ) was an English lawyer .
David Saperton ( 1889 - -1970 ) was an American pianist known especially for being the first pianist to play the entire original compositions as well as the complete transcriptions of his father - in - law , Leopold Godowsky .
Gus Edwards ( 18 August 1879 -- 7 November 1945 ) was an American songwriter and vaudevillian .
Edward Nares ( 26 March 1762 -- 23 July 1841 ) was an English historian and theologian , and general writer .
V. Ishwaraiah MBBS , MRCP , FRFPS ( 1898 - -1983 ) was an eminent professor of Pharmacology in India .
Hugh Pembroke Vowles ( 1885 in Pembroke , Wales -- 1951 in `` The Leaze '' , Oxlynch , Stonehouse , Gloucestershire , England ) was a British engineer , socialist and author .
Ohno Bakufu ( Japanese : 大野麦風 , 1888 - -1976 ) was a Japanese painter and printmaker .
Sir Augustine Nicolls or Nicholls ( 1559 - -1616 ) was an English judge .
Johann Georg Wunderlich ( February 1755 -- 1819 ) was a German composer and flautist .
Dr. Ian Munro Ross FREng ( 15 August 1927 -- 10 March 2013 ) was an early pioneer in transistors , and for 12 years President of Bell Labs .

Arthur Romilly Fedden ( 1875 - -1939 ) was an English artist and watercolourist .

Josip Jović ( 21 November 1969 -- 31 March 1991 ) was a Croatian police officer who was killed by Serb forces during the Plitvice Lakes incident .

Frank Ertel Carlyle ( April 7 , 1897 -- October 2 , 1960 ) was a United States Representative of the Democratic Party from the state of North Carolina .
Aris Spiliotopoulos ( Greek : Άρης Σπηλιωτόπουλος ) ( born 28 October 1966 ) is a Greek politician of the New Democracy party .
Prior to her first cabinet appointment , Louka Katseli had been the spokesperson for Economics for the Panhellenic Socialist Movement ( PASOK ) .
Waytha Moorthy Ponnusamy sometimes spelt Waythamoorthy ( born 16 July 1966 ) is a Malaysian lawyer of Tamil origin who is currently an activist of the HINDRAF campaign to fight discrimination against Malaysian Hindus .
Vasilica Viorica Dăncilă ( born 16 December 1963 ) is a Romanian politician , who , since the 2009 election has been a Member of the European Parliament for Romania , representing the Social Democratic Party .
Stephen A. Mikulak is an American Republican Party politician who served two terms in the New Jersey General Assembly , from 1992 to 1996 , where he represented the 19th Legislative District , which covers portions of Middlesex County .
Bockarie Stevens is a prominet member of the All People 's Congress ( APC ) political party .
Mohamed Najib Boulif , commonly known as Najib Boulif ( born 1964 in Tangier , Morocco ) is a Moroccan politician from the Justice and Development Party .
Samrath Lal Meena is the Bharatiya Janata Party ( BJP ) politician in Rajasthan , India , and former Speaker of Rajasthan Legislative Assembly from 24 July 1998 to 4 January 1999 .
Paul Crête ( born April 8 , 1953 in Hérouxville , Quebec ) is a Canadian politician , who served as a Member of Parliament for the Bloc Québécois in the House of Commons of Canada from 1993 until 2009 , when he announced that he was moving to provincial politics .
Miroslavs Mitrofanovs or Miroslav Mitrofanov , ( Russian : Мирослав Борисович Митрофанов ) , ( born December 18 , 1966 in Daugavpils , Latvia ) , is a Latvian journalist and politician , Member of the 7th and 9th Saeima for For Human Rights in United Latvia .
Soledad Sosa ( born c. 1986 ) is a member of the Workers ' Party and a deputy in Mendoza Province in Argentina .
Kim Gangte ( born 30 October 1962 ) is a politician , educator and human rights activist , who was a Member of Parliament elected from the Outer Manipur Lok Sabha constituency in India in 1998 , as a Communist Party of India candidate .
Chiang Chung - ling ( simplified Chinese : 蒋仲苓 ; traditional Chinese : 蔣仲苓 ; pinyin : Jiǎng Zhònglíng , September 21 , 1922 -- March 18 , 2015 ) was a Taiwanese army general , former Minister of Defense and Vice Chairman of the Kuomintang ( Chinese Nationalist Party ) .
Ir . Arie van den Brand ( born 22 February 1951 in Oostvoorne ) is a Dutch GreenLeft politician .
Rana Goswami is an Indian National Congress politician from Assam .
Margarita Arellanes Cervantes is a Mexican politician born in Monterrey affiliated to the National Action Party .
Ho Hsin - chun ( traditional Chinese : 何欣純 ; simplified Chinese : 何欣纯 ; pinyin : Hé Xīnchún ; Wade -- Giles : Ho Hsin - ch'un ) is a member of the Democratic Progressive Party who is a member of the Legislative Yuan in Taiwan .
Indalecio Prieto Tuero ( 30 April 1883 -- 11 February 1962 ) was a Spanish politician , a minister and one of the leading figures of the Spanish Socialist Workers ' Party ( PSOE ) in the years before and during the Second Spanish Republic .
Stein Ørnhøi ( born 15 November 1935 in Trondheim ) is a Norwegian politician for the Socialist Left Party , he was the last party leader of the Socialist People 's Party of Norway .
Clair Engle ( September 21 , 1911 -- July 30 , 1964 ) was an American politician of the Democratic Party and a United States Senator from California .
Anton Cottier ( born 4 December 1943 in Jaun , Switzerland ) was a Swiss politician with the Christian Democratic People 's Party of Switzerland ( CVP ) .
Fraser Kemp ( born 1 September 1958 ) is a British Labour Party politician who was the Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Houghton and Washington East from 1997 to 2010 , and had previously been a full - time employee of the Labour Party .
Francisco González de la Vega e Iriarte ( Durango , December 3 , 1901 - Mexico City , March 3 , 1976 ) , Mexican jurist , he was Attorney General of the Republic ( 1946 to 1952 ) , Governor of Durango ( 1956 - -1962 ) by Institutional Revolutionary Party ( PRI ) .
Pina Picierno ( born 10 May 1981 at Santa Maria Capua Vetere ) is an Italian politician and member of the Democratic Party ( Italy ) who , since 2014 , serves as a Member of the European Parliament .
William Beckett - Denison ( 10 September 1826 -- 23 November 1890 ) was an English banker and Conservative Party politician who sat in the House of Commons in two periods between 1876 and 1890 .
Louise Bours ( full name Louise van der Bours ; born 23 December 1968 ) is a Member of the European Parliament politician for the North West England region for the UK Independence Party .
Anand Paranjpe was born on 16 May 1973 to Mother Supriya Paranjpe and Father Paranjape Prakash Vishvanath , who was also a member of the Shiv Sena party and served as a member of the Lok Sabha from 1996 until his death in 2008 due to cancer .
Rita Verma ( born 15 July 1953 , Patna ) is an Indian politician and a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party .
Bob Aylward ( February 1911 -- 18 July 1974 ) was a Fianna Fáil politician from County Kilkenny in Ireland .
Guido De Padt ( born 23 May 1954 ) is a Belgian politician and Senator for the Open Flemish Liberals and Democrats .

Jan Ertsborn , born 1944 , is a Swedish Liberal People 's Party politician .
Dr. Ramlakhan Singh ( born 20 December 1950 ) is an Indian politician and a member of the Bharatiya Janata Party ( BJP ) political party .
Rita Borsellino ( born 2 June 1945 in Palermo ) is a Sicilian anti - Mafia activist , politician and Member of the European Parliament for the Democratic Party .
Bjørgulv Froyn ( born 23 September 1945 ) is a Norwegian trade unionist and politician for the Socialist Left Party and the Norwegian Labour Party .
Mathilde Berghofer - Weichner ( January 23 , 1931 in Munich - May 29 , 2008 ) was a German politician , representative of the Christian Social Union of Bavaria .
Elżbieta Więcławska - Sauk ( born November 14 , 1947 ) is a Polish politician , member of Law and Justice party .

Jakob Axel Nielsen ( born 12 April 1967 in Hadsund ) is a Danish lawyer and politician representing the Conservative People 's Party .
Hynek Fajmon ( born 17 May 1968 in Nymburk ) is a Czech politician and Member of the European Parliament with the Civic Democratic Party , part of the European Democrats and sits on the European Parliament 's Committee on Budgets .
Sir James Heath , 1st Baronet ( 26 January 1852 -- 24 December 1942 ) was a businessman and Conservative Party politician in the United Kingdom .
Sir Joseph Gurney Braithwaite , 1st Baronet ( 24 May 1895 -- 25 June 1958 ) was an English Conservative Party politician .
The Pfinz is a right tributary of the Rhine in Baden - Württemberg .
The Hocking River is a tributary of the Ohio River in southeastern Ohio in the United States .
Salem Creek ( also known as Stone Church Hollow Creek , Seyberts Creek , or Varners Creek ) is a tributary of the Susquehanna River in Luzerne County , Pennsylvania , in the United States .
Blaxland Creek rises in the western suburbs of Sydney , about 4 kilometres ( 2.5 mi ) east south - east of Mulgoa and flows generally north by east , and then north - east by east before reaching its confluence with South Creek , in the suburb of Orchard Hills .
The Riss ( Ger : Riß ) is a small river in Baden - Württemberg , south - western Germany , right tributary of the Danube .
Wolli Creek , an urban watercourse of the Cooks River catchment , is located in the southern suburbs of Sydney , in New South Wales , Australia .
The Albany River is a river in Northern Ontario , Canada , which flows northeast from Lake St. Joseph in Northwestern Ontario and empties into James Bay .
The Cowlitz River is a river in the state of Washington in the United States , a tributary of the Columbia River .
Cabramatta Creek , an urban watercourse of the Georges River catchment , is located in the south - western region of Sydney , in New South Wales , Australia .
The Noxubee River ( NAHKS - uh - bee ) is a tributary of the Tombigbee River , about 90.6 miles ( 145.8 km ) long , in east - central Mississippi and west - central Alabama in the United States .
The Barima River is a tributary of the Orinoco River , entering 6 kilometres ( 4 mi ) from the Atlantic Ocean .
Iron Cove Creek ( also known as Dobroyd Stormwater Channel ) , a southern tributary of the Parramatta River , is an urban stream west of Sydney Harbour , located in the inner - western Sydney suburbs of Croydon , Ashfield , Haberfield and Five Dock in New South Wales , Australia .
The Feller Bach is a right tributary of the Moselle River in Rhineland - Palatinate ( Germany ) .
Dniester Estuary , or Dniester Liman ( Ukrainian : Дністровський лиман , Romanian : limanul Nistrului ) is a liman , formed at the point where the river Dniester flows into the Black Sea .
The Naab ( Czech : Nába ) is a river in Bavaria , Germany , and is a left tributary of the Danube .
Koyva River ( Russian : Койва ) is a river in Perm Krai in Russia , a right tributary of the Chusovaya River ( Kama 's basin ) .
The Oloy River ( Russian : Олой ) is a river in Magadan Oblast in Russia , a right tributary of the Omolon River ( Kolyma 's basin ) .
The Kanangra Creek ( officially designated as a river ) rises near Mount Wallarra , below the Boyd Plateau on the western slopes of Mount Thurat , and flows generally south - east and north - east through Kanangra Gorge , joined by one minor tributary , before reaching its confluence with the Coxs River at Konangaroo Clearing .
The Arbia is a torrent in Tuscany , central Italy , an affluence of the Ombrone river .
The Subansiri River is a tributary of the Brahmaputra River in the Indian states of Assam and Arunachal Pradesh , and the Tibet Autonomous Region of China .
Yowrie River rises on the eastern slopes of the Badja Range within Wadbilliga National Park , southwest of Cobargo and flows generally northeast , north , northeast , and then north northwest , joined by one minor tributary before reaching its confluence with the Wadbilliga River below Belowra Mountain .
The Dolores River is a tributary of the Colorado River , approximately 241 miles ( 388 km ) long , in the U.S. states of Colorado and Utah .
After passing the gorges , the Ebro bends again eastwards near Tortosa before discharging in a delta on the Mediterranean Sea close to Amposta in the province of Tarragona .
Newark Bay is connected to Upper New York Bay by the Kill Van Kull and to Raritan Bay by the Arthur Kill .
The Lukuga River is a tributary of the Lualaba River in the Democratic Republic of the Congo ( DRC ) that drains Lake Tanganyika .

Rainer Osselmann ( born 25 July 1960 ) is a former German water polo player who competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics and in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Krasimira Gyurova ( Bulgarian : Красимира Гюрова ) ( 26 October 1953 -- 30 March 2011 ) was a Bulgarian basketball player who competed in the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Viktor Omelyanovich ( Ukrainian : Віктор Омелянович ; born 13 April 1958 in Dnipropetrovsk ) is a Ukrainian rower who competed for the Soviet Union in the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Artūras Kasputis ( born 22 February 1967 in Klaipėda ) is a retired track and road racing cyclist from Lithuania , who represented the USSR at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul , South Korea .
J. Bertrand was a French swimmer and water polo player who won a silver medal in the Men 's 200 metre team swimming event at the 1900 Summer Olympics .
Wong Choong Hann played badminton at the 2004 Summer Olympics in men 's singles , defeating Przemysław Wacha of Poland in the first round .
Katy Lennon ( born 16 October 1984 in Carshalton ) is a British artistic gymnast that represented Great Britain at the 2004 Summer Olympics .
Sven Anders Gärderud ( born 28 August 1946 ) is a Swedish former track and field athlete , winner of the 3000 m steeplechase event at the 1976 Summer Olympics .
Massimo Cartasegna ( June 30 , 1885 -- April 15 , 1964 ) was an Italian athlete who competed at the 1908 Summer Olympics in London .
Casey Henwood ( born 16 December 1980 ) is a New Zealand field hockey player who competed in the 2008 Summer Olympics .
Jonathan Winter ( born 18 August 1971 in Masterton ) is a member of the Ngai Tahu Maori tribe and a former backstroke swimmer from New Zealand , who competed at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta , United States , for his native country .
Gizela Farkaš Todorović ( born 22 October 1942 in Novi Sad ) is a Serbian former middle distance runner who run for Yugoslavia in semi final of 800 m at the 1964 Summer Olympics .
Roy Sherwood ( born 11 June 1932 ) is an American former ski jumper who competed in the 1956 Winter Olympics .
André Sicard ( 19 February 1915 -- 30 November 1973 ) was a French long - distance runner who specialised in the 10 km . In this event he finished 19th at the 1936 Summer Olympics and 8th at the 1938 European Championships .
Qi Guangpu ( born October 20 , 1990 ) is a Chinese aerial skier who competed at the 2010 Winter Olympics .
Marianne Zechmeister ( born 12 April 1960 , in Berchtesgaden ) is a German former alpine skier who competed in the 1980 Winter Olympics .
Peng Bo ( Chinese : 彭勃 ; pinyin : Péng Bó ; born February 18 , 1981 in Nanchang , Jiangxi ) is a Chinese diver who competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the men 's 3 m springboard diving event with a score of 787.38 .
Paolo De Chiesa ( born March 14 , 1956 ) is an Italian journalist and former alpine skier who competed in the 1980 Winter Olympics and in the 1984 Winter Olympics .
Douglas Golder ( born 1 February 1948 ) is a retired field hockey player from Australia , who was a member of the national team that won the silver medal at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .
Peter Koech ( born February 18 , 1958 ) is a former long - distance runner from Kenya who won a silver medal in the 3,000 meters steeplechase event at the 1988 Summer Olympics .
Gerry Rinaldi ( born 25 June 1945 ) is a retired Canadian alpine skier who competed in the 1968 Winter Olympics .
Zorigtbaataryn Enkhzorig ( Mongolian : Зоригтбаатарын Энхзориг ; born February 27 , 1987 ) is an amateur boxer from Mongolia who competed at the 2006 Asian Games in the Featherweight ( -57 kg ) division , beat Galib Jafarov and won the silver medal in a lost match against Uzbekistan 's Bahodirjon Sultonov 15 - 37 .
Mehmet Ali Demirtaş ( born 2 March 1951 in Bingöl Gökçedal Deşti village close to Yayladere ) is a Turkish former wrestler who competed in the 1972 Summer Olympics .
Jirachai Linglom ( born 13 October 1978 in Thailand ) is a Thai sprinter who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics and other prestigious track and field competitions .
Christoph Bechmann ( born November 23 , 1971 in Speyer am Rhein , Rheinland - Pfalz ) is a field hockey player from Germany , who was a member of the Men 's National Team that won the bronze medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens , Greece .
Nazario Fiakaifonu ( born 27 March 1988 in Port Vila ) is a Vanuatuan judoka who competed in the heavyweight division of Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics .
Julius Lenhart ( November 27 , 1875 in Vienna -- November 10 , 1962 in Vienna ) was an Austrian gymnast who competed in the 1904 Summer Olympics .
Kang Yong - gyun ( born July 23 , 1974 ) is a North Korean wrestler who competed in the Men 's Graeco - Roman 54 kg at the 2000 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal .
Jan Erik Vollebregt ( born 10 December 1954 , in Leiden ) is a sailor from the Netherlands who represented his native country at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Kingston , Ontario .
Walter Wu ( born 14 August 1972 ) is an S13 classified Canadian swimmer who has competed and set records at the 1996 , 2000 , and 2004 Summer Paralympics .
María Mercedes Margalot ( born June 28 , 1975 in Buenos Aires ) is a retired field hockey player from Argentina , who won the silver medal with the national field hockey team at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney .
Ismail Rafaat ( born 1 January 1908-date of death unknown ) was an Egyptian football midfielder who played for Egypt in the 1934 FIFA World Cup .
Arūnas Savickas ( born 24 March 1975 ) is a retired freestyle swimmer from Lithuania , who was the oldest member ( 25 years , 174 days ) of the national squad ( 5 men and 1 woman ) competing at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney , Australia .
Ambrogio Levati ( March 14 , 1894 - May 8 , 1963 ) , was an Italian gymnast who competed in the 1920 Summer Olympics .
Samar Banerjee ( born 1931 ) was an Indian footballer who played in the 1956 Summer Olympics in Melbourne as captain of the India national football team .
Berni Huber ( born 11 July 1967 in Obermaiselstein ) is a retired German alpine skier who competed in the 1992 Winter Olympics .
Paolo Meneguzzi 's Italian debut occurred with his participation in the young artists section at the Sanremo Music Festival in 2001 .

Carmen Valero Medes ( born October 4 , 1955 in Teruel , Aragon ) is a former middle - distance runner from Spain , who represented her native country at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal , Canada .

José Amado García Gabriel ( born 13 September 1977 ) is a Guatemalan long - distance runner who competed in the 2004 Summer Olympics , the 2008 Summer Olympics and the 2012 Summer Olympics .

Xu Zhiming ( born 29 January 1980 ) is a former Chinese judoka who competed in the 2000 Summer Olympics .
Adrian Anthony Gill ( born 28 June 1954 in Edinburgh ) is a British writer and critic who uses the bylines A. A. Gill and AA Gill .
John Maessner ( born June 2 , 1969 in Hackensack , New Jersey ) who spent six seasons in Major League Soccer , two in France , two in USISL , two in the National Professional Soccer League and one in Germany .

Nature Chemical Biology is a monthly , peer - reviewed , scientific journal , which is published by Nature Publishing Group .

Urban Yeti ! is an action video game developed by Cave Barn Studios and published by Telegames for the Game Boy Advance .
The Radicalism of the American Revolution is a nonfiction book by historian Gordon S. Wood , published by Vintage in 1993 .
The Sunken Billions is a study jointly published in 2008 by the World Bank and by the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations ( FAO ) .
NCAA Football 08 is a college football video game created by EA Sports , the sports video gaming subsidiary of Electronic Arts .
The Syracuse Law Review , established in 1952 , is an intense legal research and writing program for student editors at Syracuse University College of Law and a national forum for legal scholars who contribute to it .
The Journal of Computational and Graphical Statistics is a quarterly peer - reviewed scientific journal published by Taylor & Francis on behalf of the American Statistical Association .
The Spell of Conan is a 1980 collection of essays , poems and fiction edited by L. Sprague de Camp , published in paperback by Ace Books .
Anthropology of Consciousness is the primary publication of the Society for the Anthropology of Consciousness , published by American Anthropological Association ( AAA ) since 1990 .
Honor Thyself is a novel written by Danielle Steel and published by Random House in February 2008 .
The American Journal of Physiology is a peer - reviewed scientific journal on physiology published by the American Physiological Society .
The International Journal on Artificial Intelligence Tools was founded in 1992 and is published by World Scientific .
Kasparov 's Gambit or simply Gambit is a chess playing computer program created by Heuristic Software and published by Electronic Arts in 1993 based on Socrates II , the only winner of the North American Computer Chess Championship running on a common microcomputer .
The Journal of Higher Education Outreach and Engagement is a peer - reviewed open - access academic journal published by the University of Georgia .
The Twenty - One Balloons is a novel by William Pène du Bois , published in 1947 by the Viking Press and awarded the Newbery Medal for excellence in American children 's literature in 1948 .
The Journal of Economic Behavior and Organization is an academic journal published by Elsevier .
Saint Errant is a collection of short stories by Leslie Charteris , first published in 1948 by The Crime Club in the United States and in 1949 by Hodder and Stoughton in the United Kingdom .
The Ancient Art of War at Sea is a computer game developed by Brøderbund and released for the Apple Macintosh and MS - DOS IBM in 1987 as a sequel to The Ancient Art of War .
The book was written by Paul Cornell , Martin Day and Keith Topping and was first published as Doctor Who - The Discontinuity Guide on 1 July 1995 by Virgin Books .
Blast Corps is a 1997 action video game for the Nintendo 64 in which the player uses vehicles to destroy buildings to clear a path for a runaway nuclear missile carrier .
Divided City is a novel written by Theresa Breslin and published in 2005 by Doubleday .
The American Journal of Archaeology ( AJA ) , the peer - reviewed journal of the Archaeological Institute of America , has been published since 1897 ( continuing the American Journal of Archaeology and of the History of the Fine Arts founded by the institute in 1885 ) .
Clinical Colorectal Cancer is a peer - reviewed medical journal published by CIG Media Group ( Cancer Information Group ) from 2001 to 2010 and by Elsevier since 2011 .

Renewable Agriculture and Food Systems is an academic journal published by Cambridge University Press on sustainable agriculture .
Aurail is a scrolling shoot 'em up arcade game developed by Westone and released by Sega in 1990 .
The Journal of Parasitology is a peer - reviewed medical journal covering research on parasites published bimonthly by the American Society of Parasitologists .
The Water of the Wondrous Isles is a fantasy novel by William Morris , perhaps the first writer of modern fantasy to unite an imaginary world with the element of the supernatural , and thus a precursor of much of present - day fantasy literature .

Blasiales is an order of liverworts with a single living family and two species .
Nepticulidae is a family of very small moths with a worldwide distribution .
Vir philippinensis is a species of saltwater shrimp found in the Maldives that was first described in 1984 .
Stigmatorhynchus is a genus of plants in the Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1913 .
Nebria taketoi is a species of black coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Japan .
Callicarpa macrophylla is a species of beautyberry native to the Indian subcontinent .
Taipidon anceyana was a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Charopidae .
Hydrornis is a genus of pitta .
Drombus globiceps is one of ten species of goby in the genys Drombus .
Anodontia alba , or the buttercup lucine , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Lucinidae .
Cyathea exilis is a species of tree fern endemic to the Cape York Peninsula in Queensland , Australia , where it grows in vine forest on a substrate of sandstone .
Chrysotachina amazonica is a species of flies in the genus Chrysotachina of the family Tachinidae .
Edraianthus pumilio ( silvery dwarf harebell ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Campanulaceae , native to Dalmatia in southern Croatia .
Paphiopedilum acmodontum is a species of plants in the Orchidaceae family .
Prunus huantensis is a South American species of plants native to Peru , Ecuador , and Bolivia .
Aparallactus lineatus , or the lined centipede - eater , is a species of venomous rear - fanged snake in the family Atractaspididae .
Synaphea spinulosa is a species of small shrub in the flowering plant family Proteaceae .
Pseudomuscari azureum ( syn . Muscari azureum ) , the azure grape hyacinth , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , native to Turkey .
Spelaeogriphacea is an order of crustaceans that grow to no more than 10 millimetres ( 0.39 in ) .
In taxonomy , Nephroselmis is a genus of green algae .
Oberea atricilla is a species of flat - faced longhorn beetle in the tribe Saperdini in the genus Oberea , discovered by Fairmaire in 1893 .
The Balkhash perch ( Perca schrenkii ) is a species of perch found in Kazakhstan , ( in Lake Balkhash and Lake Alakol ) , Uzbekistan , and China .
Gonionemus is a genus of hydrozoans that uses adhesive discs near the middle of each tentacle to attach to eelgrass , sea lettuce , or various types of algae instead of swimming .
Amotosaurus is an extinct genus of tanystropheid protorosaur from the earliest Middle Triassic ( early Anisian stage ) of Black Forest , southwestern Germany .
Ranunculus arvensis , the corn buttercup , devil - on - all - sides or scratch bur , is a plant species of the genus Ranunculus .
Ordosiodon is an extinct genus of therocephalian therapsids from the Early Triassic of China .
Carabus pedemontanus vesubianus is a subspecies of black - coloured beetle from Carabidae family , that can be found in France and Italy .
The Senegal lemniscomys or Senegal one - striped grass mouse ( Lemniscomys linulus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Cyttopsis is a genus of parazens .
Chalcogenia elegans is a beetle species in the genus Chalcogenia .
Caecum searleswoodii is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Caecidae .
Hyospathe is a genus of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family , native to South America and Central America .
Neptunea despecta is a species of large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Sparganium ( Bur - reed ) is a genus of flowering plants , described as a genus by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Trichomycterus chaberti is a species of cave - dwelling pencil catfish endemic to Bolivia .
It is known from a rib , a humerus , a femur , and three vretebrae of the single species and holotype , Ashoroa laticosta .
The Wenatchee Mountains checker - mallow , Sidalcea oregana var . calva , is a very rare flowering plant variety that occurs only in five locations in the Wenatchee Mountains of Chelan County , Washington , United States .
Clavularia crassa is a species of colonial soft coral in the family Clavulariidae .
Schwantesia is a genus of plant in the family Aizoaceae .
Pyrgulopsis deserta is a species of freshwater snail in the family Hydrobiidae , the mud snails .
Allium rothii is a plant species found in Israel , Palestine , Syria , Egypt , and Jordan .
Sabal miamiensis , the Miami palmetto , is a rare plant species known only from Dade County , Florida , in the vicinity of the City of Miami .
Hallirhoidae is an extinct family of lithistid demosponges found throughout the world from the Cretaceous to the Eocene , whereupon they became extinct .
Sphinctomyrmex is a genus of ants in the subfamily Dorylinae .
Lawrencia spicata , commonly known as Salt Lawrencia , is a species of plant in the mallow family , Malvaceae .
Allium praecox is a species of wild onion known by the common name early onion .
The Large - fruited Catasetum ( Catasetum macrocarpum ) is a species of orchid .
Scutellosaurus ( pron.:``skoo - TELL - oh - SORE - us '' ) is an extinct genus of thyreophoran ornithischian dinosaur that lived approximately 196 million years ago during the early part of the Jurassic Period in what is now Arizona , USA .
Baphia cymosa is a plant species native to the République du Gabon in central Africa .
Berberis thunbergii ( Japanese barberry , Thunberg 's barberry , or Red barberry ) is a species of Berberis , native to Japan and eastern Asia , though widely naturalized in China and in North America .
Merycoides is an extinct genus of oreodont of the subfamily Merycoidodontinae endemic to North America during the Whitneyan stage of the Oligocene - Late Oligocene epochs ( 30.8 - -24.8 mya ) , existing for approximately 6 million years .
Notropis potteri ( chub shiner ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Myoxanthus reymondii is a species of orchid occurring from western Venezuela to Ecuador .
Rhogeessa is a genus of bats within the vesper bats family , Vespertilionidae .
Chrysactinia A. Gray is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , native to Mexico and to the southwestern United States .
Tropidocarpum californicum , the king 's gold , is a plant species endemic to a small region in California .
Margariscus margarita , the Pearl Dace , is a species of cyprinid fish .
Hyponephele brevistigma is a butterfly species belonging to the Nymphalidae family .
Encephalartos laurentianus is a species of cycad that is native to Angola and the Congo .
Phyllostegia glabra is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name ulihi phyllostegia .
Hydrophis cantoris is a species of venomous sea snake found in the Indian Ocean and its seas , bays and gulfs .
Sternbergia minoica is a plant species endemic to the Island of Crete in the Mediterranean .
Cristatella mucedo is a bryozoan in the Cristatellidae family , and the only species of the Cristatella genus .
Hyphydrus ovatus is a species of diving beetles in the family Dytiscidae .
The Tadami clawed salamander ( Onychodactylus fuscus ) is a species of clawed salamander from Japan .
Cattleya warneri ( the `` Warner 's Cattley 's orchid '' ) is a labiate Cattleya species of orchid .
Chorizanthe valida is a rare species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family known by the common name Sonoma spineflower .
Bletia patula , common name Haitian pine - pink , is a species of orchid .
Gongora quinquenervis is a species of orchid , and the type species of the genus Gongora .
The family Pythidae is a small group of beetles with no vernacular common name , though recent authors have coined the name dead log bark beetles .
Pomaderris oraria , commonly known as Bassian Pomaderris , is a shrub species native to the states of Victoria and Tasmania in Australia .
Carpilius convexus is a species of crab that lives in the Indo - Pacific , from Hawaii to the Red Sea and South Africa .
Nobuea kurodai is a species of tropical land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Cyclophoridae .
The Ceraphronidae are a small hymenopteran family with 14 genera and some 360 known species , though a great many species are still undescribed .
Pselnophorus is a genus of moths in the plume moth family , Pterophoridae .
Ranunculus acraeus , more commonly known as Alpine Buttercup , is a species of the buttercup family , Ranunculaceae , found in New Zealand .
Toragnostus is a genus of trilobites restricted to the late Middle Cambrian .
Siproeta is a genus of butterflies in the Nymphalidae family found in Central America , the Caribbean , and South America .
Hoogstraal 's lemniscomys or Hoogstraal 's striped grass mouse ( Lemniscomys hoogstraali ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Phellodendron chinense is a plant species in the genus Phellodendron .
The thorny - headed worm family Polymorphidae contains endoparasites which as adults feed mainly in fish and aquatic birds .
Carl Peter Thunberg originally described the species as Aitonia capensis in honour of William Aiton , but John Lindley later renamed it to Nymania in honour of Carl Fredrik Nyman .
Carex praegracilis is a species of sedge known by the common names clustered field sedge , field sedge , and expressway sedge .
The Laysan millerbird ( Acrocephalus familiaris familiaris ) was a subspecies of the millerbird , similar in appearance to the remaining subspecies , the Nihoa millerbird .
Neisseria flava ( Latin : flava , yellow , golden ) is a bacterium belonging to a group of species under the genus Neisseria that is considered non - pathogenic .
Rugathodes is a genus of theridiid spiders .
Tulipa sylvestris , the wild tulip or woodland tulip , is a Eurasian and North African species of wild tulip , a plant in the lily family .
Phaedrysmocheilus is an Early Triassic Tainoceratid genus ( Nautiloidea , Cephalopoda ) from Siberia .
The Roper River scrub robin ( Drymodes superciliaris colcloughi ) , also known as the allied scrub robin , is a putative subspecies of the northern scrub robin , a bird in the Petroicidae , or Australasian robin family .
Pectinariidae , or the trumpet worms or ice cream cone worms , are a family of marine polychaete worms that build tubes using grains of sand roughly resembling ice cream cones or trumpets .
Eriastrum luteum is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common names yellow woollystar and yellow - flowered eriastrum .
Neottia smallii ( syn . Listera smallii ) , the kidneyleaf twayblade or Appalachian twayblade , is a species of terrestrial orchid found in the eastern United States .
Charina umbratica , known commonly as the southern rubber boa , is a species of snake in the family Boidae .
While more recent research suggests that its sister parvorder , Corvida , is not a monophyletic grouping , the Passerida as a distinct clade are widely accepted .
Oreophryne frontifasciata is a species of frog of the Microhylidae family .
Myrmecia tarsata is a bull ant species native to Australia .
Zitha laminalis is a species of snout moth in the genus Zitha .
Mahonia zimapana is a shrub in the Berberidaceae described as a species in 1901 .
Leucorrhinia proxima , the belted whiteface or red - waisted whiteface , is a species of dragonfly in the family Libellulidae .
Palatodonta is an extinct genus of basal placodontiform marine reptile known from the early Middle Triassic ( early Anisian stage ) of the Netherlands .
Plants , also called green plants , are multicellular eukaryotes of the kingdom Plantae .
Iris leptophylla is a species in the genus Iris , it is also in the subgenus of Iris and in the Pseudoregelia section .
Carabus pseudomonticola is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Carabinae subfamily , that can be found in France and Spain .
Peperomia argyreia ( Watermelon Peperomia or Watermelon Begonia ) is a species of plant in the Piperaceae family .
Bilacunaria is a genus of flowering plant in the Apiaceae , with four species .
Cirsium is a genus of perennial and biennial flowering plants in the Asteraceae , one of several genera known commonly as thistles .
Pristimantis fetosus ( `` rana camuflada '' in Spanish ) is a species of frog from the Craugastoridae family .
Conus variegatus , common name the variable cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Callirhoe bushii is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common name Bush 's poppy - mallow .
Xenomedea rhodopyga , common name the redrump blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny endemic to the Gulf of California .
Calvatia is a genus of puffball mushrooms that includes the spectacular giant puffball C. gigantea .
Hypsoblennius striatus , the Striated blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the eastern central Pacific ocean , around Costa Rica and Panama .
Pyrrocoma lanceolata is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name lanceleaf goldenweed .
Leptataspis acuta is a species of froghoppers belonging to the family Cercopidae .
Phiocricetomys is an extinct genus of rodent from Africa .
Drosera andersoniana , the sturdy sundew , is an erect perennial tuberous species in the genus Drosera that is endemic to Western Australia .
Candaharia rutellum is a species of air - breathing land slug , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Parmacellidae .
Cheiloceras is a subglobular to thickly lenticular goniatite with a closed umbilicus from the Upper Devonian and type genus for the Cheiloceratidae .
Rubus apogaeus , the falling dewberry , is an uncommon North American species of flowering plant in the rose family .
Rhinopias is a genus of scorpionfish native to the Indian and Pacific oceans .
Tityus stigmurus is a species of scorpion from the family Buthidae that can be found in Brazil .

Hydroida is an obsolete cnidarian order which united such animals as hydras , hydromedusae , and many marine attached hydroids .
Grevillea insignis , commonly known as Wax Grevillea , is a shrub species which is endemic to the south - west of Western Australia .
Jabouilleia is a genus of scimitar babblers , placed in the Pellorneidae family .
Eurycorymbus cavaleriei is a species of plant in the Sapindaceae family and the single species in the genus Eurycorymbus .
The western horse lubber grasshopper , Taeniopoda eques , is a relatively large grasshopper species of the Romaleidae family found in the arid lower Sonoran life zone of the southwestern United States and Northern Mexico .
Mormyrus longirostris , commonly referred as the eastern bottle - nosed mormyrid , is a medium - sized fish species belonging to the elephant - snout fish family Mormyridae .
Anthopleura xanthogrammica , or the giant green anemone , is a species of intertidal sea anemone of the family Actiniidae .
Homoeodera edithia , the Edith 's Fungus Weevil is a species of beetle belonging to the family Anthribidae .
Ideorhipistena occipitalis is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Ideorhipistena .
Vicia dumetorum is a species of legume in the vetch genus .
Hieracium insolitum is a species of plant endemic to Turkey .
Tydeus eriophyes is a species of mite belonging to the family Tydeidae .

Icriocarcinus is an extinct genus of crab from the Maastrichtian or Campanian of Baja California , Mexico , and Merced County , California , United States .
Phelsuma is a large genus of mostly small lizards in the family Gekkonidae .
Allium maowenense is a plant species endemic to the Sichuan region of China .
Buriadiaceae is a family of plants that existed in the Carboniferous to Permian .
Gymnosoma indicum is an Asian species of fly in the family Tachinidae .
Rhinogobius flumineus is a species of goby endemic to Japan where they are found in the mid- to upper reaches of rivers .

Artemisia douglasiana , commonly known as California Mugwort , Douglas 's Sagewort or Dream Plant , is western North American species of aromatic herbs in the sunflower family .

Grylloblatta is a genus of insects in the family Grylloblattidae .
Osmia cornuta is a species of bee in the genus Osmia .
Nanobagrus stellatus is a species of bagrid catfish endemic to Indonesia where it is found in the Batain Hari basin of Sumatra .
Amanita pseudoporphyria , also known as Hongo 's false death cap , is a species of agaric fungus from the genus Amanita that grows solitarily or gregarious in coniferous forests .
Arctostaphylos parryana , with the common name Parry manzanita , is a species of manzanita .
Laringa is a genus of nymphalid butterfly found in South - east Asia .
Glyphostoma gabbii , common name Gabb 's tooth turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Clathurellidae .
Drosophila yakuba is an African species of fruit fly that is predominantly found in open savanna , and was one of 12 fruit fly genomes sequenced for a large comparative study .
Hymenogaster is a genus of fungi in the Hymenogastraceae family .
Diamphidia or Bushman arrow - poison beetle , is an African genus of leaf beetle .
Betaguttavirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Guttaviridae .
Sepia reesi is a species of cuttlefish native to the southeastern Indian Ocean .
Cardiocrinum is a genus of bulbous plants of the lily family first described as a genus in 1846 .
Nephthytis swainei is a species of flowering plants in the family Araceae , native to tropical West Africa ( Ivory Coast , Ghana , Congo - Brazzaville , Gabon , Cameroon ) .
Epidendrum ibaguense ( pronounced ee - bah - GAIN - say ) is a species of epiphytic orchid of the genus Epidendrum which occurs in Trinidad , French Guyana , Venezuela , Colombia and Northern Brazil .
Melicope haleakalae , Haleakala melicope , was a species of plant in the Rutaceae family .
Dorstenia tuberosa is a species of herb in the Moraceae plant family which is native to Cuba .
Aorotrema is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Tornidae within the superfamily Truncatelloidea .

Rubus vermontanus is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the rose family .
Agoniates is genus of characiform fishes from tropical South America .
Double anglers are a family , Diceratiidae , of anglerfishes .
Stearoceras is an extinct prehistoric nautiloid genus from the Lower Pennsylvanian ( Upper Carboniferous ) - Lower Permian with a fair worldwide distribution .
Dosinia elegans , or the elegant dosinia , is a species of bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae .
Oroxylum is a genus of plant belonging to the family Bignoniaceae .
Vellozia is a plant genus in the family Velloziaceae , described as a genus in 1788 .
Hoplocorypha lobata is a species of praying mantis found in Senegal .
Cephaloleia delectabilis is a species of rolled - leaf beetle in the family Chrysomelidae , first found in Mexico .

Phallus flavidus is a species of fungus in the stinkhorn family .
Achnatherum pinetorum is a species of grass known by the common names pinewoods needlegrass and pine needlegrass .
Eragrostis cilianensis is a species of grass known by several common names , including stinkgrass , candy grass , and gray lovegrass .

Sawyeria marylandensis is a species of amoebae , placed in the monotypic genus Sawyeria , and belonging to the group Heterolobosea .
Horkelia hendersonii is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Henderson 's horkelia .
Brachynotus sexdentatus is a species of crab in the family Varunidae .
Phacelia cicutaria , with the common names caterpillar phacelia or caterpillar scorpionweed , is an annual species of Phacelia .
Anoteropsis is a genus of wolf spiders that is endemic to New Zealand .
The Euantennariaceae are a family of fungi with an uncertain taxonomic placement in the class Dothideomycetes .
Egadyla antelmei is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Egadyla .
Pholcus velitchkovskyi is a cellar spider species found in Russia , Ukraine and Iran .
Caesalpinia kavaiensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Hawaii .
Lemdadella is an extinct genus of redlichiid trilobites that lived during the late Atdabanian stage , which lasted from 530 to 524 million years ago during the early part of the Cambrian Period .
Drosera allantostigma is a species of pygmy sundew from Australia .
Sorbus wilmottiana , the Willmott 's whitebeam , is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Allomerus decemarticulatus is an Amazonian ant species found in the tropics of South America .
Oedipoda is a genus of grasshoppers , including the blue - winged grasshopper , Oedipoda caerulescens .
Ceanothus ferrisiae ( sometimes spelled ferrisae ) is a rare species of shrub in the buckthorn family Rhamnaceae .
Ecnomiohyla valancifer is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
Lufengpithecus hudienensis is a prehistoric species of orangutan from the Late Miocene of China .
Oxythyrea funesta is a phytophagous beetle species belonging to the family Cetoniidae , subfamily Cetoniinae .
Rickettsia asiatica is a tick - borne pathogenic species borne by Ixodes ovatus .
Erythrina tahitensis is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family endemic to French Polynesia .
Pterostylis coccina is a species of orchid endemic to Australia , where it occurs from New South Wales to Victoria .
Mandevilla brachysiphon is a plant species with the common name Huachuca Mountain rocktrumpet .
The Mangaia swiftlet ( Aerodramusa manuoi ) is an extinct species of bird in the swift family .
Vallonia excentrica , common name the eccentric vallonia , is a species of very small air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Valloniidae .
Eucrosia calendulina is a species of plant that is endemic to Peru .
Cymbella is a diatom genus in the family Cymbellaceae .

Starksia lepicoelia , known commonly as the Blackcheek blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Caribbean Sea and adjacent Atlantic Ocean .
Pseudostomatella papyracea , common name the papery stomatella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .

Xylorhiza is a genus of flowering plants in the sunflower family , are known as woodyasters .
Hydrelia is a genus of moths in the family Geometridae .
Brosmolus longicaudus , Longtail cusk , is a species of viviparous brotula native to the reefs around Australia .
Chasmaporthetes , also known as hunting or running hyena , is an extinct genus of hyenas endemic to North America , Africa , and Asia during the Pliocene - Pleistocene epochs , living from 4.9 million to 780,000 years ago , existing for about 4.12 million years .
Tarchonantheae is a tribe of plants within the Asteraceae , or sunflower family , of flowering plants .
Riograndia is a genus of tritheledontid cynodont from the Late Triassic of South America .
The Luehdorfiini are a tribe of swallowtail butterflies .
Artoriopsis is a genus of wolf spiders that is endemic to Australia .
Victoria gordoni is a species of moth in the family Geometridae from Africa .
Ophryotrocha scutellus , is a species of polychaete worm .
The Mauritius starling ( Cryptopsar ischyrhynchus ) is an extinct species of starling , described in 2014 by Julian P. Hume , based on subfossils from Mauritius .
Allium macrostylum is a Central Asian species of wild onion native to the Tien Shan Mountains in Kyrgyzstan .
Mittendorf 's lemniscomys or Mittendorf 's striped grass mouse ( Lemniscomys mittendorfi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Nassarius coronatus , common name the crown nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Ptilium crista - castrensis , the knights plume moss or ostrich - plume feathermoss , is a moss species within the family Hypnaceae , in the class Bryopsida , subclass Bryidae and order Hypnales .
Stachyphrynium is a genus of plants native to China , the Indian Subcontinent , and Southeast Asia .
Hapalorestes is a genus of hapalodectid that lived during the early to middle Eocene .
Brabejum is a genus of a single species of large evergreen tree , Brabejum stellatifolium , commonly called wild almond , bitter almond or ghoeboontjie .
Murzinarctia is a monotypic genus of moth in the family Arctiidae .
Psephophorus is an extinct genus of sea turtle that lived from the Oligocene to the Pliocene .
Allium caspium is a species of onions named for the Caspian Sea .
Panulena perrugosa was a species of air - breathing land snail or semislug , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Helicarionidae .
Lasioderma falli is a species of beetles in the genus Lasioderma of the family Anobiidae .
Ectenolites is a genus of small , slender , cylindrial Ellesmeroceratids that resemble Ellesmeroceras but are smaller and proportionally narrower .
Austroraptor ( pron.:``AWE - stroh - RAP - ter '' ) is an extinct genus of dromaeosaurid dinosaur that lived about 70 million years ago during the Cretaceous Period in what is now modern Argentina .
Viola arvensis is a species of violet known by the common name field pansy .
Sapphirina darwinii is a species of parasitic copepod .
Vicia cracca ( tufted vetch , cow vetch , bird vetch , blue vetch , boreal vetch ) , is a species of vetch native to Europe and Asia .
The Trogulidae are a family of harvestmen with about 45 known species .
Amphiplica is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Caymanabyssiidae .
The sooty albatrosses are small albatrosses from the genus Phoebetria .
Vitis vinifera ( common grape vine ) is a species of Vitis , native to the Mediterranean region , central Europe , and southwestern Asia , from Morocco and Portugal north to southern Germany and east to northern Iran .
Glycyrrhiza is a genus of about 18 accepted species in the legume family ( Fabaceae ) , with a subcosmopolitan distribution in Asia , Australia , Europe , and the Americas .
Phestilla melanobrachia is a species of sea slug , an aolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tergipedidae .
Acanthogonatus quilocura is a mygalomorph spider of Chile , its name referring to the seemingly unending number of species within this genus ( `` locura '' meaning madness in Spanish ) .

Protonectarina sylveirae , commonly referred to as the Brazilian wasp , is a neotropical swarm - founding wasp species that ranges widely across South America .
The spider species Araneus diadematus is commonly called the European garden spider , diadem spider , cross spider , or crowned orb weaver .
Tatuidris , or armadillo ant , is a rare genus of ants consisting of a single species , Tatuidris tatusia .
Onychoteuthis borealijaponica , the boreal clubhook squid , is a species of squid in the family Onychoteuthidae .
Homidia pentachaeta is a species of soil - dwelling springtail belonging to the family Entomobryidae .
Salix rupifraga is a species of willow native to mountains of Honshū ( Japan ) .
Potamoidea is a superfamily of freshwater crabs , comprising the two families Potamidae and Potamonautidae .
Archaeornithura is an extinct genus of ornithuromorphs from the early Cretaceous period .
Batella is a genus of snapping shrimp comprising three species :
Proxilodon is an extinct genus of recumbirostran microsaur amphibian from the Early Permian Speiser Formation of Kansas , USA .
Schistocerca americana is a species of grasshopper in the family Acrididae known commonly as the American grasshopper and American bird grasshopper .
Cigaritis is a genus of butterfly in the family Lycaenidae . The members ( species ) are found in Afro - Asia and the Oriental region .
Phylidonyris is a genus of birds in the honeyeater family .
Europolemur is a genus of adapiformes primates that lived in Europe during the middle Eocene .
Lioconcha castrensis , common name the zigzag venus , is a species of saltwater clam , a marine bivalve mollusc in the family Veneridae , the venus clams .
Paroedopa punctigera is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Paroedopa of the family Ulidiidae .
Liceida ( also Liceales ) is an order of Amoebozoa .
Zakerana mysorensis ( Mysore frog ) is a species of frog that is endemic to the Western Ghats , India .
The genus is monotypic containing the single species Thaumaina uranothauma

Tetramolopium is a genus of plants in the aster tribe within the daisy family .
Sibara is a genus of ten plant species in the mustard family known commonly as the winged rockcresses .
Onychodus ( /ɒˈnɪkədəs/ , from Greek meaning `` claw - tooth '' ) is a genus of prehistoric lobe - finned fish which lived during the Devonian period ( Eifelian - Famennian stages , around 374 to 397 million years ago ) .

Anophthalmus hitleri ( Slovene : Hitlerjev brezokec ) is a species of blind cave beetle found only in five humid caves in Slovenia .
Pogogyne nudiuscula is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Otay mesa mint .
Doulingoceras is a genus of ammonoid within the ceratitid order , found in China , that lived during the Late Permian during the time span from about 260.5 to 254 million years ago .
Miltonia candida , the Snow - white Miltonia , is a species of orchid endemic to southeastern Brazil .
Epicauta vittata is a species of beetle in the family Meloidae , the blister beetles .
Paphiopedilum glaucophyllum , common name The Shiney Green Leaf Paphiopedilum or Tropical Ladys - Slipper , is a species of flowering plants in the genus Paphiopedilum belonging to the Orchidaceae family .
Cellana denticulata , or the denticulate limpet , is a species of true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Orthops campestris is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Mirinae , that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Azores , Faroe Islands , Iceland and African islands such as Canary Islands and Cyprus .
Petradoria is a genus of North American subshrubs in the aster tribe within the daisy family .
Heterogaster artemisiae is a species of seed bug that has been reported as a pest of common thyme in Hungary .
Dittrichia graveolens , commonly known as stinkwort or stinking fleabane , is a plant species in the sunflower family , native to southern Europe , North Africa , and western Asia as far east as Pakistan .
Draba hispida , common name Three - toothed whitlow grass , is a species of plants belonging to the family Brassicaceae .
Thelymitra villosa , commonly called the custard orchid is a species of orchid which is endemic to Western Australia .
Zingiberaceae ( /ˌzɪndʒɪbəˈreɪsiː/ ) or the ginger family is a family of flowering plants made up of more than 1300 species of aromatic perennial herbs with creeping horizontal or tuberous rhizomes .
Allium atropurpureum is a plant species native to Hungary , the Balkans , and Turkey .
Steatoda bipunctata is a species of cob - web spider , of the genus Steatoda , in the family Theridiidae .
Clarkia australis is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name Small 's southern clarkia .
Actinistia is a subclass of mostly fossil lobe - finned fishes .
Stenotus acaulis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name stemless mock goldenweed .
The bushtits or long - tailed tits , Aegithalidae , are a family of small , drab passerine birds with moderately long tails .
Lucernariopsis is a stalked jellyfish genus .
Petrosavia is a genus in the family Petrosaviaceae .
Ectrosia is a genus of Asian , Australian , and Pacific Island plants in the grass family .
Amaranthus grandiflorus is a species of Amaranthus found in Australia .
The Eiao Marquesan warbler ( Acrocephalus percernis aquilonis ) is a subspecies of the northern Marquesan reed warbler found only in the dry upland forest on Eiao in the northern Marquesas Islands .
Delena is a small genus of huntsman spiders occurring in Australia and New Zealand .
Leptospermum recurvum is a species of Leptospermum native to Malaysia .
The Glacier Bay water shrew ( Sorex alaskanus ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Hipponix incurvus is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Hipponicidae , the hoof snails .
Austrorossia enigmatica is a species of bobtail squid native to the southeastern Atlantic Ocean ; it occurs off the coast of southern Africa from Namibia to Cape Province .
Spirulida is an order of cephalopods comprising one extant species ( Spirula spirula ) and several extinct taxa .
Of the Simsia calva species , the average height ranges from 30 - -150 cm ( 12 - -59 in ) .
Eremothera chamaenerioides is a species of evening primrose known by the common name long - capsule suncup .

Ijimaia is a genus of jellynose fishes , one of four in the order Ateleopodiformes .
Tetramolopium capillare is a rare species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name pamakani .
Boraginales is a valid taxonomic name at the rank of order for a group of flowering plants .
Spiders ( order Araneae ) are air - breathing arthropods that have eight legs and chelicerae with fangs that inject venom .
Zaireichthys wamiensis is a species of loach catfish endemic to Tanzania .
Conus sazanka , common name Sazanka 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Otopleura nodicincta , common name the nodulose pyram , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Harmonia hallii ( formerly Madia hallii ) is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names Hall 's harmonia and Hall 's madia .

Therocephalia is an extinct suborder of eutheriodont therapsids from the Permian and Triassic .
Gleditsia assamica is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is found only in India .
Tiarocarpus is a genus of Afghan plants in the thistle tribe within the daisy family .

Penicillium inflatum is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium which produces sterigmatocystin .

Sphyraena sphyraena is normally a pelagic species found high in the water column , but smaller fish often found near bottom of the water column .
Lycodon laoensis , commonly known as the Laotian wolf snake , is a species of colubrid snake , which is endemic to Asia .

Indiophonus pilosus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Indiophonus .
Rubus adenophorus is a species of deciduous shrub in the genus Rubus in the family Rosaceae native to China , where it was discovered in 1907 .
Dillhoffia is an extinct monotypic genus of flowering plant with a single species , Dillhoffia cachensis known from Ypresian age Eocene fossils found in British Columbia , Canada , and Washington , USA .
Thecladoris tylonotoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Thecladoris .

Rhacophorus viridis ( Okinawan tree frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Morus celtidifolia , the Texas mulberry , is a plant species native to South America , Central America , Mexico , and the southwestern United States , ranging from Argentina north as far as Arizona and Oklahoma .
Pteronia is a genus of flowering plant in the aster tribe within the sunflower family .
Hibiscus rosa - sinensis , known colloquially as Chinese hibiscus , China rose , Hawaiian hibiscus , and shoeblackplant , is a species of tropical hibiscus , a flowering plant in the Hibisceae tribe of the family Malvaceae , native to East Asia .

Choristis discotypa is a species of moth of the Tortricoidea superfamily .
Streptomyces heilongjiangensis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from the root surface of the soybean Glycine max in Hulin in the Heilongjiang province in China .
Herpetopoma benthicola is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Chilodontidae .
Procambarus brazoriensis , the Brazoria crayfish , is a species of crayfish which is endemic to Brazoria County , Texas .
Halaelurus sellus , commonly known as the Rusty Catshark in Australia , is a species of catshark in the genus Halaelurus .
Saperdoglenea gleneoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Saperdoglenea .
Koompassia malaccensis is a tropical rainforest tree species up to 60 m tall in the Fabaceae family .
Proparamenia is a genus of cavibelonian solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like marine mollusks .
Histiostoma is a genus of mites , including the species Histiostoma polypori .
Pelargonium quercifolium is a species of geranium known by the common name oakleaf geranium or oak - geranium .
Haemulon carbonarium , the Caesar grunt , is a species of grunt native to the western Atlantic Ocean from Florida to Brazil and also in the Caribbean Sea and the Gulf of Mexico .
Ferganasaurus was a genus of dinosaur first formally described in 2003 by Alifanov and Averianov .
Temnothorax albipennis is a species of small ant in the subfamily Myrmicinae .
Eudistylia polymorpha , the giant feather duster worm , is a species of marine polychaete worm belonging to the family Sabellidae .
Lupinus aridorum is a rare species of lupine known by the common name scrub lupine .
Achondrostoma occidentale , the western ruivaco , is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Euphorbia peplus ( petty spurge , radium weed , cancer weed , or milkweed ) is a species of Euphorbia , native to most of Europe , northern Africa , and western Asia , where it typically grows in cultivated arable land , gardens , and other disturbed land .
Terateleotris aspro is a species of freshwater sleeper endemic to the Mekong basin in Laos .
Anatoma atlantica is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Anatomidae .
Agyneta similis is a species of sheet weaver found in Finland , Iceland , Kazakhstan and Russia .
Phazaca leucocera is a species of moth of the family Uraniidae .
Cotoneaster lacteus , the late cotoneaster or milkflower cotoneaster , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Cotoneaster of the family Rosaceae , native to the Yunnan Province of China .
It contains only one species Hansreisseria gilvescens , which is found on the Canary Islands .
Eudendrium rugosum is a marine species of cnidaria , a hydroid ( Hydrozoa ) in the family Eudendriidae .
Areticulata is a genus of moths of the Nepticulidae family , it contains only one species Areticulata leucosideae , which is found in South Africa .
Nannostomus britskii , commonly known as the spotstripe pencilfish , is a freshwater species of fish belonging to the Lebiasinidae family of characins .
Pellia epiphylla ( sometimes known as overleaf pellia or common pellia ) is a species of thallose liverwort .
Thelypodium laxiflorum , the droopflower thelypody , is a plant species native to the southwestern United States .
Smilax zeylanica is a plant species in the genus Smilax .
The Turkestan red pika ( Ochotona rutila ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Gyposaurus ( meaning `` vulture lizard '' , referring to the outdated hypothesis that prosauropods were carnivores ) is a genus of basal sauropodomorph dinosaur from the early Jurassic of South Africa and China .
Cryptolacerta ( `` Hidden lizard '' from Greek ) is an extinct genus of lacertibaenian lizard which lived during the Eocene epoch ( Lutetian stage , about 47 million years ago ) in what is now Germany .
Passiflora arbelaezii is a species in the Passifloraceae family native to eastern Nicaragua and western Colombia .
Delminichthys is a genus of cyprinid fish which is found in the karst region of the Balkans , Eastern Europe .
Calliostoma palmeri , common name Palmer 's top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Juncus digitatus is a rare species of rush known by the common name finger rush .
Leptynia montana is a species of stick insect from Heteronemiidae family which is endemic to Spain .
Solidago ulmifolia , commonly known as elmleaf goldenrod , is a North American species of goldenrod in the sunflower family .
The Darien pocket gopher ( Orthogeomys dariensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
Ocyptamus is a large and diverse genus of over 300 species of hoverfly mostly found in the Neotropical region .
The sole known species , Auranticordis quadriverberis , is a heart shaped cell with four flagellae .
Cotula moseleyi , also known as Nightingale Brassbuttons , is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Smeringodynerus is a Nearctic genus of potter wasps .
Cyrtopodion amictopholis is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
Takydromus is a genus of lizards , commonly called grass lizards or oriental racers .
Chasmanthe floribunda is a species of flowering plants in the iris family which is known by the common name African flag .
The Aderidae , ant - like leaf beetles , are a family of beetles that bear some resemblance to ants .
Hymenoxys richardsonii ( common names pingue hymenoxys and pingue rubberweed ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Kukulcania arizonica , commonly called the Arizona black hole spider is a species of spider belonging to the family Filistatidae .
Gracillariidae is an important family of insects in the order Lepidoptera and the principal family of leaf miners that includes several economic , horticultural or recently invasive pest species such as the horse - chestnut leaf miner , Cameraria ohridella .
Nominosuchus is a genus of protosuchian - grade crocodylomorph .
The blue - eyes are a family of atheriniform fish , the Pseudomugilidae , related to the rainbowfishes .
The Alabama cavefish is one of the rarest troglobitic fish species in North America .
Chondrocladia turbiformis is a recently discovered species of carnivorous sponge .
Ixonanthaceae is a pantropical flowering plant family of trees or shrubs up to 90 m tall ( Allantospermum borneense ) , consisting of about 30 species in 4 or 5 genera .
Ephippion guttifer , commonly known as the prickly puffer , is a species of pufferfish native to the coasts of the eastern Atlantic Ocean from Gibraltar to Angola .
The Troglosironidae are a family of harvestmen with thirteen described species in a single genus , Troglosiro .
Oidaematophorus is a genus of moth in the Pterophoridae family with a cosmopolitan distribution .
Dyera is a genus of tropical trees up to 80 m in height .
Psalodon is an extinct genus of North American mammal that lived during the Upper Jurassic period .
Rhombosolea is a genus of righteye flounders .
Barbucca is a genus of loaches native to Southeast Asia .
Charmoses dumigani is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Charmoses .
Veratrum viride , known as Indian poke , Indian hellebore , false hellebore , green false hellebore or giant false - helleborine , is a species of Veratrum native to eastern and western ( but not central ) North America .
Brackenridgea is a plant genus of about 10 species in the family Ochnaceae .
The sole species is Paratrygon aiereba , the discus ray , which is native to South American rivers in the Amazon and Orinoco basins .
Nebria suensoni is a species of ground beetle from the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Xinjiang province of China .
Acrocercops affinis is a moth of the Gracillariidae family , known from California , U.S.A. The hostplant for the species is an unidentified species of Quercus .
Cryptococcus antarcticus is a species of Cryptococcus that has been isolated from soil in Antarctica , as the name suggests .
Istiblennius rivulatus is a species of combtooth blenny found on coral reefs in the western Indian ocean .
Azorella caespitosa is a species of Azorella flowering plant , found in the Falkland Islands .
Pomatias raricosta is a species of land snail with an operculum , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Pomatiidae .
Solmsia is a genus , containing two species , of flowering plants belonging to the family Thymelaeaceae . It was named to honor Hermann zu Solms - Laubach by Henri Ernest Baillon .
Calantica darwini is a species of barnacle .
The Cordulegastridae are a family of Odonata ( dragonflies ) from the suborder Anisoptera .
Allium monticola is an uncommon species of wild onion known by the common name San Bernardino Mountains onion .
Phyllocnistis finitima is a moth of the Gracillariidae family , known from Arizona , U.S.A. The hostplant for the species is Senecio cruentus .
Charaxes dowsetti is a member of the Charaxes jasius species group .
Citrus reshni also known as Cleopatra mandarin is a citrus tree that is commonly used in agriculture as a rootstock of different cultivated species of citrus , mostly orange , grapefruit , tangerine and lemon .
Lytrosis unitaria , the common lytrosis moth , is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Acanthus ebracteatus is a species of shrubby herb that grows in the undergrowth of mangroves of south - east Asia .
Morelia tracyae , more commonly known as the Halmahera python , is a species of python found only on the Indonesian island of Halmahera .
Horkelia marinensis is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common name Point Reyes horkelia .
Scrophularia desertorum is a species of flowering plant in the figwort family known by the common name desert figwort .
Kinoceras is an extinct genus of cephalopod from the Silurian of North America .
Potentilla longifolia is a plant species in the genus Potentilla found in Russia and Mongolia .
Nematobrycon is a genus of characins endemic to the Atrato and San Juan River basins in western Colombia .
Starksia brasiliensis is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the Atlantic coast of Brazil .
Discodeles opisthodon ( common name : Faro webbed frog or Faro Island webbed frog ) is a species of frog in the Ceratobatrachidae family .
The Arabian serin or olive - rumped serin ( Crithagra rothschildi ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Atlanta selvagensis is a species of sea snail , a holoplanktonic marine gastropod mollusk in the family Atlantidae .
