Carabus hispanus is a species of beetle in family Carabidae native to southwestern France , with the Massif Central as the northern boundary of its distribution range .
Carabus exiguus fanianus is a bronze - coloured subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily that is endemic to Shaanxi , China .
Lobophylliidae is a family of large polyp stony corals .
Crepis atribarba is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names slender hawksbeard and dark hawksbeard .
Ruppia cirrhosa is a species of aquatic plant known by the common names spiral ditchgrass and spiral tasselweed .
Acentrogobius cyanomos , or the Threadfin blue goby is a amphidromous benthopelagic species of goby found in brackish and salt water in Bangladesh , India , Indonesia , Malaysia , and Thailand .
Octomeria linearifolia is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Pernambuco to Paraná ) .
Laguncula is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Viviparidae .
Fagus grandifolia ( American beech or North American beech ) is the species of beech tree native to the eastern United States and Canada .
Rosa prattii is a wild rose species native to China , with pink flowers .
Rostratula is a genus of painted - snipes .
Neocurtimorda mordelloides is a species of beetle in the Neocurtimorda genus which is part of the Mordellidae family .
Stomatepia is a genus of cichlids endemic to Lake Barombi Mbo in western Cameroon .
Lethrinops marginatus , also known as the Lethrinops ' rounded head ' in the aquarium fish trade , is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is widespread and occurs in shallow waters over sandy substrates .
Calamagrostis ophitidis , serpentine reedgrass , is a species of bunch grass in the Poaceae family .
Abdera hoffeinsorum is an extinct species of false darkling beetle in the genus Abdera .
Nemadus colonoides is a species of beetle in the Leiodidae family that can be found in such European countries as Belarus , Belgium , Bulgaria , Croatia , Czech Republic , France , Germany , Italy , Latvia , Poland , Romania , Slovakia , Slovenia , Scandinavia , and the Netherlands .
Nevromus austroindicus is a species of dobsonfly found in the Western Ghats of India .
Atta colombica is one of 41 species of leafcutter ant .
The Bearded Catasetum ( Catasetum barbatum ) is a species of orchid .
Caledoniscincus atropunctatus is a species of lizard in the family Scincidae endemic to New Caledonia .
Maningrida arnhemensis is a species of small , air - breathing land snail with an operculum , a pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the superfamily Amphiboloidea .
Cardamine pensylvanica is a species of Cardamine known by the common name Pennsylvania bittercress .
Chorisoneura texensis , the Small Texas Cockroach , is a small species of cockroach ( family Blattellidae ) native to the Southeastern United States .
Deconica montana , commonly known as the mountain moss Psilocybe , is a common species of mushroom that is usually found growing in mossy areas , often in montane regions around the world .
Pandanus tonkinensis is a plant species endemic to Vietnam .
Chloe Cracker ( Hamadryas chloe ) is a species of cracker butterfly in the family Nymphalidae .

Arnoglossum sulcatum ( Georgia Indian plantain ) is a North American species of plants in the sunflower family .
Entoloma alboumbonatum is a species of fungus in the agaric genus Entoloma .
The Synlestidae are a family of damselflies commonly known as sylphs or malachites .
Koeleria is a common and widespread genus of plants in the grass family , found on all continents except Antarctica and on various oceanic islands .
Tanna japonensis , also called the evening cicada or higurashi ( Japanese : 蜩 , 茅蜩 , ひぐらし ) , is a species of cicada , a family of insects , and a member of the genus Tanna .
Psilopterus ( Greek for `` bare wing '' ) is an extinct genus of phorusrhacid ( `` terror bird '' ) from the Middle Oligocene to Late Miocene of Argentina .
Alburnus timarensis also known as the Karasu Sha Kuli , is a species of Cyprinidae fish endemic to Turkey .
The round - eared elephant shrew ( Macroscelides proboscideus ) or round - eared sengi ( called the Karoo round - eared elephant shrew to distinguish it from its sister species ; formerly misleadingly named the `` short - eared elephant shrew '' ) , is a species of elephant shrew ( sengi ) in the family Macroscelididae .
Doraops zuloagai is the only species in the genus Doraops of the catfish ( order Siluriformes ) family Doradidae .
Himatanthus bracteatus is a species of the genus Himatanthus ( Apocynaceae ) , native Venezuela , Colombia , the Guianas , Brazil , Peru , and Ecuador .
Laplatasaurus ( meaning `` La Plata lizard '' ) is a genus of titanosauran sauropod dinosaur that lived during the Late Cretaceous in South America .
Grewia asiatica ( Phalsa or Falsa ) ( Urdu : فالسہ , Hindi : फ़ालसा ) is a species of Grewia native to southern Asia from Pakistan , India east to Cambodia , and widely cultivated in other tropical countries .
Castilleja angustifolia ( synonym Castilleja chromosa ) is a species of wildflower known by the common names northwestern Indian paintbrush and desert Indian paintbrush .

Tachymenis is a genus of venomous snakes belonging to the family Colubridae .
Cornucopiae is a genus of Mediterranean and Middle Eastern plants in the grass family .
Carex disticha is a Eurasian species of sedge known as the brown sedge or , in North America , tworank sedge .
Pseudoricopis excavatipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudoricopis .
Cellana testudinaria is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nacellidae .
Glossiphoniidae are the family called freshwater jawless leeches or glossiphoniids .
Danuria angusticollis is a species of praying mantis in the genus Danuria .
Loricatosaurus ( meaning `` armored lizard '' ) is a genus of stegosaurid dinosaur from Callovian - age ( Middle Jurassic ) rocks of England and France .
Lycopodium obscurum , commonly called rare clubmoss , ground pine , prince 's pine or princess pine , is North American a species of clubmoss in the family Lycopodiaceae .
Pseudoniscus is an extinct genus of xiphosuran .
Schizothorax richardsonii or common snowtrout is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Schizothorax .
Ypsolophidae is a family of moths with some 160 species .
Borassus madagascariensis is a species in the palm family Arecales endemic to Madagascar .
Cyclostrema tortuganum , common name the Tortugas cyclostreme , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Liotiidae .
Giraffoidea is a superfamily that includes the families of Climacoceratidae , Antilocapridae , and Giraffidae .
Blennophis anguillaris , the Snaky klipfish , is a species of clinid found in the subtropical waters of the Atlantic Ocean around South Africa .
Gogangra viridescens is a species of sisorid catfish found in Bangladesh , Bhutan , India , Nepal and Pakistan .
Heterorhabditis bacteriophora also known as beneficial nematodes is a species of nematode worm that is used in gardening .
Streptomyces achromogenes is a species of gram - positive bacterium that belongs in the genus Streptomyces .
Polygonum achoreum , common names Blake 's knotweed , leathery knotweed or striate knotweed , is a North American species of plants in the buckwheat family .
Melipona scutellaris is a eusocial stingless bee species of the order Hymenoptera and the genus Melipona .
The Black Blood - red Dendrobium ( Dendrobium atroviolaceum ) is a species of orchid , endemic to eastern Papua New Guinea .
Luciobarbus kottelati is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Luciobarbus from the Büyük Menderes River basin in Turkey .

Acleris caledoniana , the Caledonian Button , is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .

Meiolania ( `` small roamer '' ) is an extinct genus of basal turtle from the Oligocene to Holocene , with the last relict populations at New Caledonia which survived until 2,000 years ago .
Dactylagnus peratikos is a species of sand stargazer found along the Atlantic coast of Costa Rica and Panama .
Floridiscrobs dysbatus is a species of very small aquatic snail , an operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Lamplughsaura is a genus of saurischian dinosaur from the Sinemurian - age ( Early Jurassic ) Dharmaram Formation of India , dating from between 196 to 190 million years ago .
Papilio sakontala is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in India .
Sericomyiini is a tribe of hoverflies consisting mainly of large bumblebee or wasp mimics .
Biarmosuchus is an extinct genus of biarmosuchian therapsid that lived around 267 mya during the Middle Permian period . Biarmosuchus was discovered in the Perm region of Russia .
Oceanic dolphins are a widely distributed family of fully aquatic marine mammals .
Mitra nodulosa , common name : the nodulose mitre , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Proedromys is a genus of rodent in the family Cricetidae from China .
Poiretia algira is a species of land snail in the family Spiraxidae .
Echinostoma revolutum is the most widely distributed species of all 20 Echinostomatidae species and it is found from Asia and Oceania to Europe and the Americas .
The daggertooth ( Anotopterus pharao , meaning `` without fins on its back , of the Pharaoh '' ) is a species of daggertooth .
Marsupiocrinus is an extinct genus of crinoid that lived from the Silurian to the Early Devonian in North America .
Polyxenida is an order of millipedes readily distinguished by a unique body plan consisting of a soft , non - calcified body ornamented with tufts of bristles -- traits that have inspired the common names `` bristly millipedes '' or `` pincushion millipedes '' .
Medicago constricta is an annual , non - climbing species of the genus Medicago .
Pachymerium caucasicum is a species of centipede in Geophilidae family .
Hymenoxys lemmonii is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names Lemmon 's rubberweed , Lemmon 's bitterweed , and alkali hymenoxys .
Palpimanoidea or palpimanoids are a group of araneomorph spiders , originally treated as a superfamily .
Macropus is a marsupial genus that belongs to the family Macropodidae .
Anoectochilus is a genus of about 50 orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) belonging to the subfamily Orchidoideae .
It contains the single species Androtium astylum .
Cryptophagidae is a family of beetles with representatives found in all ecozones .
Platysteira is a genus of bird in the Platysteiridae family .
Odostomia acutidens , common name the sharp - tooth odostome , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
Hispidoberyx ambagiosus is a species of spiny - scale pricklefish found in the Indian and Pacific Oceans at depths from 560 to 1,019 m ( 1,837 to 3,343 ft ) .
Vriesea costae is a species of bromeliad in the genus Vriesea .
Analipus japonicus or `` sea fir '' is a brown alga species in the genus Analipus .
Bergenia crassifolia , the badan , Siberian tea , Mongolian tea , leather bergenia , winter - blooming bergenia , heartleaf bergenia , elephant - ears , heart - leaved bergenia or elephant 's ears , is a plant species in the genus Bergenia .

Tomopterna luganga is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family found in Tanzania and possibly Kenya .
Apachea barberella is a moth in the Oecophoridae family , and the only species in the genus Apachea .
The Unionidae are a family of freshwater mussels , the largest in the order Unionoida , the bivalve mollusks sometimes known as river mussels , or simply as unionids .

Gentiana parryi ( Parry 's gentian ) is a species of the genus Gentiana .

Pseudomyrmex leptosus is a species of ant in the genus Pseudomyrmex .

Smilax biltmoreana , Biltmore 's carrionflower , is a North American plant species native to the southeastern United States .

Panicum ( panicgrass ) is a large genus of about 450 species of grasses native throughout the tropical regions of the world , with a few species extending into the northern temperate zone .
Glaucium corniculatum , the blackspot hornpoppy or red horned - poppy , is a species of the Glaucium genus in the poppy family ( Papaveraceae ) .

Eptesicus taddeii is a species of medium - sized bat belonging to the family Vespertilionidae .

Campanula latifolia , the giant bellflower , is a species of bellflower in the family Campanulaceae .

Hieracium longipilum , hairy hawkweed , is a North American plant species in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family .
Cochranella euknemos , sometimes known as the San Jose Cochran frog , is a species of frog in the Centrolenidae family .
Cranioceras is an extinct genus of artiodactyl from the Miocene to the Pliocene in the United States .
Crataegus collina is a type of hawthorn that is closely related to C. punctata , the dotted hawthorn , and sometimes considered to be the same species .
Lutjanus is a genus of snappers found in the Atlantic , Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Stegastes nigricans , the dusky farmerfish , is a species of damselfish found around coral reefs at a depth of one to 12 meters , in tropical climates between 30 ° S and 30 ° N.
Liaoconodon is an extinct genus of early mammal from the early Cretaceous ( early Aptian stage , approximately 120 Ma ) .
Leiocephalus loxogrammus , commonly known as the San Salvador Curly - tailed Lizard , is a lizard species from the family of curly - tailed lizards ( Leiocephalidae ) .
Doumea is a genus of loach catfishes native to Africa .
Leptolepis ( `` delicate scale '' ) is an extinct genus of teleost fish that lived from the Middle Jurassic period until the Early Cretaceous .
Telfairia is a small genus of flowering plants in the squash family which are native to Africa .
Lacistema lucidum is a species of plant in the Lacistemataceae family .
The one species named by Kielan - Jaworowska and Nesov is Uzbekbaatar kizylkumensis , found in the Upper Cretaceous strata of Uzbekistan .
Hygrophorus goetzii ( Hygrophorus goetzei is an orthographical variant spelling ) is a species of fungus in the family Hygrophoraceae .
Macrometopia is a South American genus of hoverfly , restricted to the high Andes .
Papilio hectorides is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found in Argentina , Paraguay , Uruguay and Brazil .
Diadema setosum is a species of long - spined sea urchin belonging to the family Diadematidae .
Breuningiana pulchra is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Breuningiana .
Treubiaceae is a family of liverworts in the order Treubiales .
Streptanthus breweri is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Brewer 's jewelflower .
Erronea adusta , common name the chocolate beauty or tanned / dark onyx cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Mammillaria plumosa ( feather cactus ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Cactaceae , native to Northeastern Mexico .
The Tapanti moss salamander or Nototriton tapanti is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Chalcolyne metallica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Chalcolyne .
Pentaceratops ( five - horned face ) is a genus of herbivorous ceratopsid dinosaur from the late Cretaceous Period of what is now North America .
Carabus is a genus of beetle in family Carabidae .
Deinandra lobbii , called threeray tarweed , is a North American species of plants in the tarweed tribe within the ( sunflower family ) .
Bedotia is a genus of the family Bedotiidae of fishes endemic to Madagascar .
Nigma hortensis is a spider species found in Spain , France and Algeria .
Hibiscus cravenii is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family , Malvaceae , that is endemic to the Northern Territory in Australia .
It has one known species , Eremiolirion amboense , native to Angola and Namibia .
Anisomorpha is a genus of walking stick insect capable of secreting a substance from glands on the metathorax that can cause an intense burning irritation of the eyes ( and in some cases temporary blindness ) and mouth of potential predators on contact .
Bruchidius siliquastri is a species of bean weevil .
Pechuel - loeschea , common name Stinkbush or Bitterbos , is a genus of African plants in the elecampane tribe within the sunflower family , and named after the German plant collector and geographer Eduard Pechuël - Loesche ( 1840 - 1913 ) .
Avicennia marina , commonly known as grey mangrove or white mangrove , is a species of mangrove tree classified in the plant family Acanthaceae ( formerly in the Verbenaceae or Avicenniaceae ) .
Pseudaesopia japonica , the wavyband sole or Seto sole , is a species of sole native to the western Pacific Ocean , where found over sandy mud bottoms .
Monardella beneolens is a rare species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name sweet - smelling monardella .
Mexianthus is a genus of Mexican flowering plants in the boneset tribe within the sunflower family .
Stenothecidae is an extinct family of fossil univalved Cambrian molluscs which may be either gastropods or monoplacophorans .
Amietophrynus perreti , or the Perret 's toad , is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Neoveitchia is a genus of palm trees .
Clathrina gardineri is a species of calcareous sponge in the genus Clathrina from India and Seychelles .
Kirengeshoma palmata ( yellow wax bells ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Hydrangaceae , native to Japan and eastern China ( Huangshan and Tianmushan ) .
Crupina is a small genus of plants in the thistle tribe within the daisy family .
Frigidoalvania janmayeni is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Rissoidae .
Artemisia arborescens ( tree wormwood ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Asteraceae , native to the Mediterranean region .
Semibalanus is a genus of barnacles , comprising two species :
Porcupinefishes or balloonfishes , are any of the various species of the genus Diodon , the type genus of Diodontidae .
Ductina is a genus of extinct , small to average sized , eyeless phacopid trilobite , that lived during the Devonian .
Mitra magnifica is a species of medium - large sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mitridae , the miters or miter snails .
Amblypharyngodon is a genus of fishes in the family Cyprinidae .
Ronnbergia neoregelioides is a species in the genus Ronnbergia .
Psychidocossus infantilis is a moth in the Cossidae family , and the only species in the genus Psychidocossus .
Leptotyphlops teaguei , or the Northern blind snake , is a species of snake in the Leptotyphlopidae family .
The Nodosinellacea is a superfamily of fusulinds ( microganular foraminifera ) in which the test is of one or more distinct chambers with the wall single layered or with a microgranular outer layer and fibrous inner layer .
Eleutherodactylus haitianus is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family endemic to the Cordillera Central , Dominican Republic , at elevations of 1,545 - -2,455 m ( 5,069 - -8,054 ft ) asl .
The Phascogales ( members of the eponymous genus Phascogale ) , also known as wambengers , are carnivorous Australian marsupials of the family Dasyuridae .
Cylindropuntia prolifera , known by the common name Coastal cholla , is a species of cactus .
Portunus sayi , the sargassum swimming crab , is a species of pelagic crab in the family Portunidae .

Tenellia adspersa , common name the miniature aeolis , is a species of very small sea slug , an aeolid nudibranch , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Tergipedidae .
Pseudaristobia octofasciculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudaristobia .
Mimacalolepta dunni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Mimacalolepta .

Thaumastopeus agni is a species of beetle described by Wallace in 1867 .

Acer pseudosieboldianum , the Korean maple or purplebloom maple , is a species of maple .
Apodemus is the genus of Muridae ( true mice and rats ) which contains the Eurasian field mice .
Petalonyx is a small genus of flowering plants native to the southwestern United States and northern Mexico .
Conus cylindraceus , common name the cylindrical cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Bombus cerdanyensis is an extinct species of bumble bee in the family Apidae known from a fossil found in Europe .
Chimonanthus nitens is a species of the genus of wintersweets Chimonanthus and member of the family Calycanthaceae ( syn . Meratia nitens ( Oliver ) Rehder & Wilson ; C. campanulatus R.H.Chang & C.S.Ding ; C. grammatus M.C.Liu ; C. zhejangensis M.C.Liu ) .
Pterolabis is a genus of earwigs in the subfamily Isolabiinae .
Carabus alexandrae is a species of black coloured ground beetle from Carabinae subfamily , that is endemic to Gansu , China .
Downingia elegans is a species of flowering plant in the bellflower family known by the common names elegant calicoflower and Californian lobelia .
Ctenobrycon spilurus , the silver tetra , is a species of tropical freshwater fish sometime referred to as the silver dollar tetra .
Leccinum pseudoscabrum is an edible species of fungus in the genus Leccinum .
Leonurus is a genus of flowering plants in the family Lamiaceae .
Rhododendron keleticum ( 独龙杜鹃 ) is a rhododendron species native to southeast Xizang and northwest Yunnan , China , as well as Myanmar , where it grows at altitudes of 3000 - -3900 meters .
Bulbophyllum pandanetorum is a rare species of epiphytic plant in the Orchidaceae family .
Choristoneura metasequoiacola is a species of moth of the Tortricidae family .
Phasianella ventricosa , common name the swollen pheasant shell or common pheasant shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae .
Eucephalus glabratus is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Siskiyou aster .
Virola elongata ( syn . Virola theiodora ) is a species of tree in the Myristicaceae family .
Korthalsia rogersii is an endangered endemic rattan species , thought to be extinct from the insular habitat of the Andaman Islands in the Indian Ocean until 1993 .
Aristolochia ringens is a species of perennial plant in the Aristolochiaceae family .
A monotypic genus , it contains the single species Pyrenochium pini .
Penelopides is the genus of relatively small , primarily frugivorous hornbills found in forests of the Philippines and the Indonesian island of Sulawesi .
Elimia showalteri , common name the compact elimia , is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Pleuroceridae .
Mycena urania , commonly known as the violet bonnet , is a species of mushroom in the Mycenaceae family .
Pterocarpus santalinoides is a tree species in the legume family ( biology ) ( Fabaceae ) ; it is locally known as mututi .
Macrocranion is a genus of extinct mammal from the Eocene epoch of Europe and North America .
Brownea is a genus of about 30 species in the family Fabaceae , subfamily Caesalpinioideae .
Aforia circinata , common name the ridged turrid , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cochlespiridae .
Liochirus cycloderus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Liochirus .
The Apaturinae are a subfamily of butterflies that includes many species commonly called `` emperors '' .
Lecidea is a genus of curstose lichens with a carbon black ring or outer margin ( exciple ) around the fruiting body disc ( apothecium ) , usually ( or always ) found growing on ( saxicolous ) or in ( endolithic ) rock .
Valsa sordida is a species of fungus within the Valsaceae family .
Molinia caerulea ( purple moor - grass ) is a species of flowering plant in the grass family Poaceae , native to Europe , west Asia , and north Africa .
Bromus catharticus is a species of brome grass known by the common names rescuegrass , grazing brome , prairie grass , and Schrader 's bromegrass .
Rhombodera extensicollis ( giant shield mantis ) is a species of praying mantis of the Genus Rhombodera .
Microhyla ornata ( commonly known as the ornate narrow - mouthed frog , ornate narrow - mouthed toad , or ornamented pygmy frog ) is a species of microhylid frog found in South Asia .
Ericameria parryi ( syn . Chrysothamnus parryi ) is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Parry 's rabbitbrush .
Astragalus osterhoutii is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common name Osterhout milkvetch .
Entomophthora muscae is a species of pathogenic fungus in the order Entomophthorales which causes a fatal disease in flies .
Neoregelia hoehneana is a species of bromeliad , in the genus Neoregelia .
Acastocephala is a genus of trilobite from the middle Silurian , known from the United Kingdom .
Pittocaulon praecox is the type species for the genus Pittocaulon and family Asteraceae .
Agonum nitidum is a species of ground beetle in the genus Agonum .
The tabulate corals , forming the order Tabulata , are an extinct form of coral .
Parapriacanthus is a genus of sweepers native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
Tipula nubeculosa is a species of cranefly .
Ranunculus parviflorus is a species of buttercup known by the common name smallflower buttercup .
Argyrotheca is a genus of very small to minute lampshells ( maximum 5 millimetres or 0.20 inches long ) .
Pavoclinus litorafontis , the Slinky klipfish , is a species of clinid found around False Bay , South Africa , in the southeastern Atlantic ocean .
Siphonaria cookiana is a species of small air - breathing sea snail or false limpet , a marine pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Siphonariidae , the false limpets .
Colostethus mertensi is a species of frog in the Dendrobatidae family , currently threatened by habitat loss .
Eragrostis lehmanniana is a species of grass known by the common name Lehmann lovegrass .
Ifremeria nautilei is a species of large , deepwater hydrothermal vent sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Provannidae , and the only species in the genus Ifremeria .
Trichia is a genus of slime molds in the family Trichiaceae .
Lepanthes pantomima is a species of orchid that occurs from Mexico ( Chiapas ) to Central America .
Jasminum angulare ( Wild Jasmine ) is a species of jasmine , in the family Oleaceae that is indigenous to South Africa .
Tanganyicia rufofilosa is a species of tropical freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Paludomidae .
The Websdaneaceae are a family of smut fungi in the class Ustilaginomycetes .
Rodolia cardinalis ( common names vedalia beetle or cardinal ladybird ) is a species of ladybird beetle that is sometimes described as endemic to Australia .
Peachella is an extinct genus of trilobites , fossil marine arthropods , with species of average size ( about 3.5 centimetres or 1.4 inches long ) .
Asiadodis squilla is a species of praying mantis in the genus Asiadodis in the order Mantodea .
Ivesia pickeringii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names silky mousetail and Pickering 's ivesia .
Metrosideros elegans is a species of plant endemic to New Caledonia in the family Myrtaceae .
Cyathea klossii is a species of tree fern native to western New Guinea , where it grows in rain forest from the lowlands up to an elevation of about 750 m. The trunk of this plant is erect , 1 - -2 m tall , and only 1 - -2 cm in diameter .
The Hispaniolan masked curly - tailed lizard ( Leiocephalus personatus ) is a lizard species from the family of curly - tailed lizards ( Leiocephalidae ) .
Dusisiren is an extinct genus of dugong related to the Steller 's Sea Cow that lived in the North Pacific during the Neogene .
Caenidae , or the Small Squaregill Mayflies , is a family of insects consisting of 4 genera comprising 26 individual species .
Triopha catalinae , commonly known as the sea clown triopha , is a species of colorful sea slug , a nudibranch , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Polyceridae .
Laemostenus is a genus of ground beetles present on all continents on Earth , except Antarctica .
Pseudohaje goldii , commonly known as Goldie 's tree cobra or Gold 's tree cobra ( in error ) , is a species of venomous tree cobra ( Pseudohaje means `` false cobra '' ) endemic to Central and Western Africa .
Oligographa is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing one species Oligographa juniperi , which is known from South Africa and Mozambique .
Piceoerpeton is an extinct genus of prehistoric amphibian , containing species known from the latest Cretaceous ( late Maastrichtian ) , Paleocene and Eocene of North America .
The smooth hawksbeard , Crepis capillaris , is a species in the dandelion tribe within the sunflower family , native to Europe .
Grandisonia larvata is a species of caecilian in the family Indotyphlidae , endemic to the Seychelles islands of Mahé , Praslin , La Digue , and Silhouette .
Oradectes ( meaning `` margin biter '' , from Latin ora ( margin ) and dectes ( biter ) ) is an extinct genus of diadectid reptiliomorph .
Hosta cathayana is a species of shade - tolerant foliage plants in the genus Hosta .
Banksia ser . Dryandroideae is a taxonomic series in the plant genus Banksia .
Carrolla craddocki is an extinct species of Carrolla , an extinct genus , of the prehistoric amphibian lepospondyl microsaur that lived in the Lower Permian in North America .
Cyathea corcovadensis is a species of tree fern native to Paraguay and Serra do Mar in southern Brazil , where it grows in primary and secondary forest , as well as scrub , at an altitude of 250 - 2100 m. The erect trunk is short , usually about 30 - -60 cm tall .
Tribolonotus gracilis is a species of skink endemic to New Guinea .
Bothriocidaris ( meaning best furrow or best trench ) is an extinct genus of echinoid from the Ordovician .
Cosmopepla conspicillaris is a species of insect in the Pentatomidae family .
Euterpe edulis , commonly known as juçara , jucara ( misspell of the former name , of Luso - Tupian origin ) , jussara ( an archaic alternative spelling ) , açaí - do - sul or palmiteiro , is a palm species in the genus Euterpe .
The Two - colored Cymbidium ( Cymbidium bicolor , Chinese : 硬葉蘭 or 硬叶兰 ) is a species of orchid found in South China to Tropical Asia .
Dendropoma squamiferum is a species of irregularly - coiled sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Vermetidae , the worm snails .

Myxine mcmillanae , the Caribbean hagfish , is a species of hagfish .
Lipoptena cervi , the deer ked or deer fly , is a species of biting fly in the family of louse flies , Hippoboscidae .
Acanthobrama centisquama ( the long - spine bream ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Oeceoclades humbertii is a terrestrial orchid species in the genus Oeceoclades that is endemic to southeastern Madagascar , where it grows in xerophilous bush at altitudes from 500 to 600 m ( 1,600 to 2,000 ft ) .
Abelia chinensis is a species of Abelia described by Robert Brown .
The Mojave fringe - toed lizard ( Uma scoparia ) , is a species of medium - sized , white or grayish , black - spotted diurnal lizard in the family Phrynosomatidae .

Elmerimys is an extinct genus of rodent known from Miocene fossils found in Africa .
Hylarana glandulosa , commonly known as the rough - sided frog or the glandular frog , is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
The Arabian ostrich or Syrian ostrich ( Struthio camelus syriacus ) is an extinct subspecies of the ostrich which lived on the Arabian Peninsula and in the Near East until the mid-20th century .
Striatura is a genus of minute air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Gastrodontidae .

Primobucco is an extinct genus of bird placed in its own family , Primobucconidae .

Odontoponera is a small Southeast Asia genus of ants in the subfamily Ponerinae .
Anatalavis is genus of prehistoric birds related to ducks and geese , perhaps in particular the magpie - goose .

The Bedotiidae are a family of fish known as the Madagascar rainbowfish , Madagascan rainbowfish , or Malagasy rainbowfish due to their endemism to Madagascar .
Lachenalia contaminata ( wild hyacinth ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , native to the Western Cape of South Africa .

Cherokeea attakullakulla is a moth in the Noctuidae family and only species in the genus Cherokeea .
Pentacrinites is an extinct genus of crinoid that lived from the Middle Triassic to the Eocene of Asia , Europe , North America , and New Zealand .
Avitoluvarus ( `` Ancient Louvar '' ) is a genus of extinct louvar that lived in the Tethys Ocean during the early Paleogene .
Wiseana copularis is a species of moth belonging to the family Hepialidae .
Meuschenia is a genus of filefishes native to the coastal waters around Australia .
Calochortus plummerae is a species of mariposa lily known by the common name Plummer 's mariposa lily .
Pikaia gracilens is an extinct genus of chordate animal known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale of British Columbia .
Haptodus is an extinct genus of basal sphenacodont , a clade that includes therapsids and hence , mammals .
Helianthus exilis is a species of sunflower known by the common name serpentine sunflower .
Convolvulaceae , known commonly as the bindweed or morning glory family , is a family of about 60 genera and more than 1,650 species of mostly herbaceous vines , but also trees , shrubs and herbs .
Darkling beetle is the common name of the large family of beetles , Tenebrionidae .
The Tellinoidea are a taxonomic superfamily of saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs .
Nicetiodes apianella is a species of snout moth , and the only species in the genus Nicetiodes .

Neoepimorius lineola is a species of snout moth in the genus Neoepimorius .

Nebria assidua is a species of ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Nepal .
Anekes inflata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk , unranked in the superfamily Seguenzioidea .
Conus fulmen , common name the thunderbolt cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Caridina serratirostris is a species of freshwater shrimp that lives in the Indo - west Pacific region , from Madagascar to Fiji , including northern Queensland .
Eobelinae are an extinct beetle subfamily that throve in the late Mesozoic .
The Malindi pipit ( Anthus melindae ) is a species of bird in the Motacillidae family .
Notiophanes is a genus of moths in the Arrhenophanidae family , consisting of only one species Notiophanes fuscata , which is endemic to Queensland , Australia .
Ashorocetus is a monotypic genus of an extinct primitive baleen whale of the family Aetiocetidae .
Ficus verruculosa , the water fig , is a species of fig from sub - saharan Africa .
The Amazon weasel ( Mustela africana ) , also known as the tropical weasel , is a species of weasel that lives in the Amazon Rainforest in South America .
It contains a single species , Unescoceratops koppelhusae .
Cavisternum is a genus of Goblin spider .
Snowdenia is a genus of African and Arabian plants in the grass family .
Walkomiella is an extinct conifer - like gymnosperm genus which occurred in India and Africa in the Lower Permian , and in Australia in the Upper Permian .
Amphiesma pealii , commonly known as the Assam keelback , is a species of natricine snake endemic to India .
Fuligo septica is a species of plasmodial slime mold , and a member of the Myxomycetes class .
Galeichthys peruvianus is a species of sea catfish that is found in the Pacific Ocean off the coast of Peru .
Fungi of the genus Hypholoma are quite well known due to the commonness of sulphur tuft ( Hypholoma fasciculare ) on stumps in temperate woodlands .
Cotoneaster acuminatus ( commonly known as acuminate cotoneaster ) is a species of flowering plant in the Rosaceae family that is native to the Himalayas .
Cerastium arvense is a species of flowering plant in the pink family known by the common names field mouse - ear and field chickweed .
Sebastes inermis ( Japanese red rockfish , Japanese red sea perch ) is a species of rockfish native to the northwestern Pacific Ocean where it occurs off the coasts of Japan and the Korean Peninsula .

Tithoniidae is an extinct family of sea urchins .
Pleurosternidae is an extinct family of Testudines turtles .

Chaetadelpha is a genus of plants in the dandelion family containing the single species Chaetadelpha wheeleri , or Wheeler 's skeletonweed .
Conus axelrodi , common name Axelrod 's cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .

Tuberaria lignosa is a species of perennial rock - rose native to the western Mediterranean region .
Trematolestes is an extinct genus of temnospondyl amphibian from the Lower Keuper ( Ladinian , Middle Triassic ) of southern Germany .
Lepidotrichidae is a family of basal insects belonging to the order Thysanura .
Ornithocephalus gladiatus is a species of orchid found from Grenada , Trinidad , the Guianas , Venezuela , Ecuador , Peru , Bolivia and Brazil .
Sarotherodon is a genus of tilapiine cichlids endemic to Africa and the Middle East .
Haematera pyrame is a South American species of butterflies belonging to the family Nymphalidae .
Anagotus is a weevil genus in the tribe Aterpini .
Thorius smithi ( common name : Smith 's salamander ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Phalaris arundinacea , sometimes known as reed canary grass , is a tall , perennial bunchgrass that commonly forms extensive single - species stands along the margins of lakes and streams and in wet open areas , with a wide distribution in Europe , Asia , northern Africa and North America .
Lomasuchus is an extinct genus of peirosaurid notosuchian known from the Late Cretaceous ( Santonian stage ) of Neuquén Province , western central Argentina .
The genus contains a single described species , Nanotermes isaacae placed tentatively in the subfamily Termitinae .
Pluchea is a genus of flowering plants in the stinkwort tribe within the sunflower family .
Caesia is a genus of herbs in the family Xanthorrhoeaceae , native to Australia , New Guinea , Madagascar and Southern Africa .
Arctostaphylos ( /ˌɑːrktoʊˈstæfᵻləs , -lɒs/ ; arkto bear + staphyle grape ) is a genus of plants comprising the manzanitas ( /ˌmænzəˈniːtəz/ ) and bearberries .
Lijndenia barteri ( synonyms : Spathandra barteri , Memecylon dinklagei , Memecylon pynaertii , and basionym Memecylon barteri ) is a species of shrub in the Melastomataceae family .
Royle 's pika ( Ochotona roylei ) is a species of mammal in the family Ochotonidae .
Clover or trefoil are common names for plants of the genus Trifolium ( Latin , tres `` three '' + folium `` leaf '' ) , consisting of about 300 species of plants in the leguminous pea family Fabaceae .
Doumea chappuisi is a species of loach catfish found in the coastal rivers of Guinea , Ivory Coast , Liberia and Guinea - Bissau .
Diplopoma is a genus of operculate land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks gastropod in the family Pomatiidae .
Nambashag is an extinct genus of early cormorant from Late Oligocene and Early Miocene ( about 26 - -24 mya ) deposits of South Australia .
Donaciella is a genus of leaf beetles from the subfamily of Donaciinae .
Lobelia inflata ( Indian tobacco , puke weed ) is a species of Lobelia native to eastern North America , from southeastern Canada ( Nova Scotia to southeast Ontario ) south through the eastern United States to Alabama and west to Kansas .
Diandrya is a genus of cestode parasites that are known from marmots ( Marmota spp . )
Platystele is a genus of orchids , comprising about 95 species .
Streptomyces diastaticus is an alkaliphilic and thermophilic bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces .
Larix kaempferi , known as Japanese larch or karamatsu ( 唐松 ) in Japanese ) is a species of larch native to Japan , in the mountains of Chūbu and Kantō regions in central Honshū .
It contains only one species , Duthiastrum linifolium , endemic to South Africa ( Cape Provinces , Free State , Northern Provinces ) .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Thindia cupressi , found in Uttar Pradesh , India .
Ptychohyla salvadorensis ( common name : Salvador stream frog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in El Salvador , Guatemala , and Honduras .
Lethogoleos andersoni , or the Forgetful Snake - eel , is a species of eel in the family Ophichthidae .
Aloe albiflora is a species of aloe indigenous to Madagascar with narrow , muricate leaves and widely campanulate , snow - white flowers that are 10 mm long and 14 mm across the mouth .
Nannoglanis fasciatus is a species of three - barbeled catfish endemic to Ecuador where it is found in the Napo River basin .
Atlantic thread herring has a slightly milder taste than most species of herring , it can be served raw , pickled , grilled or cooked .
Lophiodon is an extinct genus of mammal related to tapirs .
Afrotropical ecozone Charaxes cacuthis is a member of the species group Charaxes etesipe The clade members are Charaxes etesipe Nominate Charaxes penricei Charaxes achaemenes Charaxes paradoxa Charaxes cacuthis
The Ceylon paradise flycatcher ( Terpsiphone paradisi ceylonensis ) , also known as the Sri Lanka paradise flycatcher is a subspecies of the Indian paradise flycatcher .
Cicindela allardi is a species of Carabidae , or ground beetle , in the genus Cicindela .
It includes only one known species , Sinopodophyllum hexandrum , native to Afghanistan , Bhutan , northern India , Kashmir , Nepal , Pakistan , and western China ( Gansu , Qinghai , Shaanxi , Sichuan , Tibet , Yunnan ) .
Catacamas virus is a single - stranded , enveloped novel RNA virus species in the hantavirus genus of the Bunyaviridae family isolated in Oryzomys couesi near the town of Catacamas in eastern Honduras .
Aeneator comptus is a species of large sea snail , a whelk , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Murchisonellidae is a taxonomic family of sea snails , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Murchisonelloidea .
Omphalodes cappadocica ( Cappadocian navelwort ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Boraginaceae , native to woodland habitats in Turkey .
Isotomidae is a family of springtails , comprising the following genera :
Qantassaurus ( /ˌkwɑːntəˈsɔrəs/ KWAHN - tə - SOR - əs ) is a genus of two - legged , plant - eating ornithischian dinosaur that lived in Australia about 115 million years ago , when the continent was still partly south of the Antarctic Circle .
Limnanthes montana is a species of meadowfoam known by the common name mountain meadowfoam .
Neoepaphra pulchella is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Neoepaphra .
Recilia formosielus is a species of bugs from the Cicadellidae family that is endemic to Taiwan .
Origanum libanoticum ( Lebanese oregano , hopflower oregano , cascading hopflower oregano , ornamental oregano or cascading oregano ) is a species of herbaceous flowering plant in the family Lamiaceae , native to the mountains of Lebanon and Syria .
Capsicum pubescens is a species of the genus Capsicum ( pepper ) , known as rukutu , ruqutu ( Quechua , hispanicized rocoto ) and luqutu ( Aymara , hispanicized locoto ) and in Mexico known as the `` Manzano '' pepper which means `` apple '' for its apple - shaped fruit .
Polyalthia nitidissima is a species of tree in the Annonaceae family .
Phasmatocoris spectrum is a thread - legged bug species from the genus Phasmatocoris .
Murex aduncospinosus , also known as the Short - spined murex , is a species of large predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
Homocerynea is a genus of moths of the Erebidae family .
Yunganastes is a small genus of craugastorid frogs distributed in southern Peru and Bolivia .
Rhizocarpon geographicum ( the map lichen ) is a species of lichen , which grows on rocks in mountainous areas of low air pollution .
Schistonema is a species of plants in the Apocynaceae first described as a genus in 1906 .
Eucalyptus tereticornis is a species of tree native to eastern Australia .
Peracle charlotteae is an extinct species of fossil pelagic sea snail , or `` sea butterfly '' , a planktonic marine gastropod mollusk in the family Peraclidae .
Phacelia campanularia is a species of flowering plant in the borage family , Boraginaceae , known by the common names desertbells , desert bluebells , California - bluebell , desert scorpionweed , and desert Canturbury bells .
Kelps are large seaweeds ( algae ) belonging to the brown algae ( Phaeophyceae ) in the order Laminariales .
Notiophilus is a genus of ground beetle native to the Palearctic , the Nearctic , the Near East and North Africa .
Iberoformica is a small genus of ants in the subfamily Formicinae .
Tulipa clusiana , the lady tulip , is an Asian species of tulip native to Afghanistan , Iran , Iraq , Pakistan and the western Himalayas .
Allium tulipifolium is an Asian species of wild onion native to Xinjiang , Kazakhstan and Altay Krai .
Galloperdix is a genus of three species of birds in the pheasant family , Phasianidae .
Banksia speciosa , commonly known as the showy banksia , is a species of large shrub or small tree in the family Proteaceae .
Rhynchonella is an extinct genus of brachiopod found in Silurian to Eocene strata worldwide .
Xerolenta obvia is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Polydrusus is a genus of weevils containing dozens of species , some of which are commonly found in Europe and northeastern North America .
Tomocerus is a genus of springtails described by Nicolet in 1841 .
The Heterenchelyidae or mud eels are a small family of eels native to the Atlantic , Mediterranean , and eastern Pacific .
Berosus trilobus is a species of hydrophilid beetle from the Dominican Republic and Cuba .
